INSERT INTO products VALUES (40, 'en', 'YRLt-lDVNH3njfvw8F-Zt', '/wsb3-40', true, 'vmc7BEbim5NjfgCUrtohY', 'WSB3-40', true, '<p>Wall-mounted controllers with upstroke control WSB3-40 and WSB3-40H are the basic and most popular features (control) of the iNELS system.</p><p>&nbsp;Built-in micro-switch with low upstroke offers elegant and pleasant control.</p><p>&nbsp;Controllers WSB3-40 and WSB3-40H are supplied with 4-channels.</p><p>&nbsp;Two-colored indication LEDs located in each controller can signal the status of controlled appliances or the status of any sensor or actuator in the system.</p><p>&nbsp;Wall buttons in WSB3 series are compatible with both types of frames LOGUS90 (85.6x85.6 or 94x94 mm), therefore you can combine them with double and triple frames and classic products of the series.</p><p>&nbsp;Each controller is equipped with a temperature sensor. It is also equipped with two analog/digital inputs (AIN/DIN), which can be used to connect two potentialless contacts or one external temperature sensor TC/TZ (e.g. for measuring floor temperature).</p><p>&nbsp;Compared to standard wall buttons WSB3-20 and WSB3-20H are more flexible and multifunctional. You can, for example, control appliances with a short and long push of the button&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(e.g.: dimming, shutter control, scenes).</p><p>&nbsp;Each button can control any appliance in the system and can use a variety of centralized or time-controlled features. Accordingly, the customer can choose the simplicity/complexity of the operation. The big advantage is the possibility to change the method of control by only making software modifications without physical interventions into the structure of the building.</p><p>&nbsp;Each button (fold) can have different functional modes besides lighting control:<br>a) Classic wall-switch&nbsp;- upper button ON, bottom button OFF<br>b) Button controller (impulse relay)&nbsp;- first press ON, second press OFF<br>c) Dimmer&nbsp;- short press – ON/OFF<br>d) Time switch&nbsp;- ON after press, automatically OFF after set time<br>e) Setting light scenes – for example: for watching TV:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- shutters down<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- main light 30% intensity<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- wall-lamps 50% intensity</p><p>&nbsp;WSB3 in LOGUS90 design is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'WSB3-40', 'Wall switch button, 4 buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":210,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132336', '3233 standard', 13, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/manual_wsb3-40x.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/WSB3-40/3D/3d.html', '', 1760615039898, 1760615039898, '/wsb3-40                                                                                                                                                         wsb3-40                                                                                                                                                          <p>wall-mounted controllers with upstroke control wsb3-40 and wsb3-40h are the basic and most popular features (control) of the inels system.</p><p>&nbsp;built-in micro-switch with low upstroke offers elegant and pleasant control.</p><p>&nbsp;controllers wsb3-40 and wsb3-40h are supplied with 4-channels.</p><p>&nbsp;two-colored indication leds located in each controller can signal the status of controlled appliances or the status of any sensor or actuator in the system.</p><p>&nbsp;wall buttons in wsb3 series are compatible with both types of frames logus90 (85.6x85.6 or 94x94 mm), therefore you can combine them with double and triple frames and classic products of the series.</p><p>&nbsp;each controller is equipped with a temperature sensor. it is also equipped with two analog/digital inputs (ain/din), which can be used to connect two potentialless contacts or one external temperature sensor tc/tz (e.g. for measuring floor temperature).</p><p>&nbsp;compared to standard wall buttons wsb3-20 and wsb3-20h are more flexible and multifunctional. you can, for example, control appliances with a short and long push of the button&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(e.g.: dimming, shutter control, scenes).</p><p>&nbsp;each button can control any appliance in the system and can use a variety of centralized or time-controlled features. accordingly, the customer can choose the simplicity/complexity of the operation. the big advantage is the possibility to change the method of control by only making software modifications without physical interventions into the structure of the building.</p><p>&nbsp;each button (fold) can have different functional modes besides lighting control:<br>a) classic wall-switch&nbsp;- upper button on, bottom button off<br>b) button controller (impulse relay)&nbsp;- first press on, second press off<br>c) dimmer&nbsp;- short press – on/off<br>d) time switch&nbsp;- on after press, automatically off after set time<br>e) setting light scenes – for example: for watching tv:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- shutters down<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- main light 30% intensity<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- wall-lamps 50% intensity</p><p>&nbsp;wsb3 in logus90 design is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_wsb3-40_wsb3-40h.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_wsb3-40.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (43, 'en', '97EU3d-7MlUeV-avfGEx6', '/grt3-100', true, 'WZAuFR7pexAymVIvDhFZm', 'GRT3-100', true, '<p>Glass room thermo-regulator GRT3-100 is part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (GRMS) and serves to regulate the temperature in the&nbsp;room.</p><p>The glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the iNELS&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (GRT3-100/B) and white (GRT3-100/W) versions.&nbsp;</p><p>The GRT3-100 thermo-regulator has a display that displays the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. To adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>The GRT3-100 is equipped with 5 x 8 A relay output for fan speed and&nbsp;valves. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/ TZ (for example temperature measurement of the room or the floor).</p><p>GRT3-100 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.&nbsp;</p><p>Thermo-regulator GRT3-100 also features touch buttons whose functions can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/ cooling,&nbsp;or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>The thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>GRT3-100 is designed for mounting into the wall.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GRT3-100', 'Glass room thermo-regulator', '[{"image":{"uploadId":395,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191746', '9174 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1763987663067, 1763987663067, '/grt3-100                                                                                                                                                        grt3-100                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass room thermo-regulator grt3-100 is part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (grms) and serves to regulate the temperature in the&nbsp;room.</p><p>the glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the inels&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (grt3-100/b) and white (grt3-100/w) versions.&nbsp;</p><p>the grt3-100 thermo-regulator has a display that displays the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. to adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>the grt3-100 is equipped with 5 x 8 a relay output for fan speed and&nbsp;valves. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/ tz (for example temperature measurement of the room or the floor).</p><p>grt3-100 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.&nbsp;</p><p>thermo-regulator grt3-100 also features touch buttons whose functions can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/ cooling,&nbsp;or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>the thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>grt3-100 is designed for mounting into the wall.</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (92, 'en', 'yiOQH_hymoPJS1NCM2Bit', '/rfmb-62', true, 'yDTnLuR1aGXG6iSMVjyks', 'RFMB-62', true, '<p>The metall front plate design controller with two output relays.</p><p>The 6 buttons controls on the built-in allow you to directly&nbsp;control the built-in output relays as well as, other iNELS Wireless units.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>Possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>Each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>Power supply AC 230V is galvanically isolated from the output relay&nbsp;contacts.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768906800000, '[]', 'RFMB-62', 'Wireless metal pushbutton controller with switching relays', '[{"image":{"uploadId":484,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 21, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1768913791343, 1768913791343, '/rfmb-62                                                                                                                                                         rfmb-62                                                                                                                                                          <p>the metall front plate design controller with two output relays.</p><p>the 6 buttons controls on the built-in allow you to directly&nbsp;control the built-in output relays as well as, other inels wireless units.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>power supply ac 230v is galvanically isolated from the output relay&nbsp;contacts.</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (7, 'en', 'pENbTpmU1zREIQmNo6mdr', '/psm3-100inels', true, 'o8L3FWFuooazeNJwTs9AC', 'PSM3-100/iNELS', true, '<p>Used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation iNELS.</p><p>Through BUS separators from the supply voltage BPS3-01M and&nbsp;BPS3-02M, it supplies BUS lines from which iNELS peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>Rated output voltage 27V DC with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>High efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>Low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>Protection: Overload, Over voltage and Short circuit.</p><p>Continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'PSM3-100/iNELS', 'Power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":178,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184786', '8478 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-100_inels/share_dokumentace/en/manual_psm3_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/PSM3-100_iNELS/3D/3d.html', '', 1759148519350, 1760601616288, '/psm3-100inels                                                                                                                                                   psm3-100/inels                                                                                                                                                   <p>used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation inels.</p><p>through bus separators from the supply voltage bps3-01m and&nbsp;bps3-02m, it supplies bus lines from which inels peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>rated output voltage 27v dc with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>high efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>protection: overload, over voltage and short circuit.</p><p>continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-100_inels/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_psm3-30_inels_psm3-60_inels_psm3-100_inels.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-100_inels/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_psm3-100_inels_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (57, 'en', '5hLWFVF1N8S2Xnaf-b6MJ', '/gsb3-90s', true, '0PW0JVJE3AMVjudtHrX2z', 'GSB3-90/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S are part of a comprehensive range of glass iNELS control units and&nbsp;can be advantageously used in all projects for example as a part of guest&nbsp;room management system (GRMS).</p><p>GSB3-40/S is equipped with four, GSB3-60/S six and GSB3-90/S nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily modify by the software.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is&nbsp;available in elegant black (GSB3-40/SB, GSB3-60/SB, GSB3-90/SB) and&nbsp;white (GSB3-40/SW, GSB3-60/SW, GSB3-90/SW) versions.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the module (94x94 mm) from the line of&nbsp;luxury switches and sockets LOGUS90 and are therefore fully in line with&nbsp;the design of frames for the sockets of this series, where you can just as&nbsp;for the controllers choose white and black glass frames.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>The glass touch controllers are also equipped with a sensor of ambient&nbsp;light intensity. Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example also switch the lighting circuits in the room.</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances At once.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S and GSB3-90/S are designed for mounting into an&nbsp;installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-90/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":415,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188188265', '8826 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90s/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763993916116, 1763994373181, '/gsb3-90s                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-90/s                                                                                                                                                        <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s are part of a comprehensive range of glass inels control units and&nbsp;can be advantageously used in all projects for example as a part of guest&nbsp;room management system (grms).</p><p>gsb3-40/s is equipped with four, gsb3-60/s six and gsb3-90/s nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily modify by the software.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is&nbsp;available in elegant black (gsb3-40/sb, gsb3-60/sb, gsb3-90/sb) and&nbsp;white (gsb3-40/sw, gsb3-60/sw, gsb3-90/sw) versions.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the module (94x94 mm) from the line of&nbsp;luxury switches and sockets logus90 and are therefore fully in line with&nbsp;the design of frames for the sockets of this series, where you can just as&nbsp;for the controllers choose white and black glass frames.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>the glass touch controllers are also equipped with a sensor of ambient&nbsp;light intensity. based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example also switch the lighting circuits in the room.</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s and gsb3-90/s are designed for mounting into an&nbsp;installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90s/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90s/share_dokumentace/en/eu_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-90s_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (41, 'en', 'CboiQt6tI5lRnrQUiE8fR', '/pms3-01', true, '8SWcHPKXowAjpItSa8HE0', 'PMS3-01', true, '<p>The PMS3-01 is a highly versatile and compact motion sensor designed&nbsp;for ceiling or surface mounting applications. With its ultra-slim design,&nbsp;the PMS3-01 seamlessly integrates into various environments, providing&nbsp;reliable and efficient motion detection capabilities.</p><p>The sensor is powered by a 27 VDC power source, specifically the iNELS&nbsp;BUS system, ensuring stable and efficient operation.</p><p>The PMS3-01 utilizes infrared for precise and reliable motion detection.&nbsp;</p><p>The sensor provides a wide 360-degree detection angle, ensuring comprehensive&nbsp;coverage of the monitored area.</p><p>The sensor''s reach is up to 6m max, allowing the user to install the unit&nbsp;at a height of 2.5 m-3.5 m, providing flexibility for different applications.</p><p>The PMS3-01 features a software setting for adjusting time settings. The&nbsp;time setting can be configured, allowing customization of the sensor''s&nbsp;activation duration.</p><p>Designed to operate effectively in various environmental conditions,&nbsp;the sensor has a wide working temperature range of -10°C to +40°C,&nbsp;ensuring reliable performance in different settings.</p><p>The PMS3-01 can be seamlessly integrated and combined with other&nbsp;iNELS units using the iDM3 software. This allows for the implementation&nbsp;of additional logic and functions, enabling automation and customized&nbsp;control scenarios based on specific requirements.</p><p>The PMS3-01 features a compact form factor with dimensions of 115 x&nbsp;24 mm, facilitating easy installation and integration into different ceiling&nbsp;or surface mounting applications.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1761822000000, '[]', 'PMS3-01', 'Ultra slim PIR motion detector', '[{"image":{"uploadId":298,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191357', '9135 standard', 16, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/pms3-01/share_dokumentace/en/manual_pms3-01.pdf', '', '', '', 1761832873400, 1761832873400, '/pms3-01                                                                                                                                                         pms3-01                                                                                                                                                          <p>the pms3-01 is a highly versatile and compact motion sensor designed&nbsp;for ceiling or surface mounting applications. with its ultra-slim design,&nbsp;the pms3-01 seamlessly integrates into various environments, providing&nbsp;reliable and efficient motion detection capabilities.</p><p>the sensor is powered by a 27 vdc power source, specifically the inels&nbsp;bus system, ensuring stable and efficient operation.</p><p>the pms3-01 utilizes infrared for precise and reliable motion detection.&nbsp;</p><p>the sensor provides a wide 360-degree detection angle, ensuring comprehensive&nbsp;coverage of the monitored area.</p><p>the sensor''s reach is up to 6m max, allowing the user to install the unit&nbsp;at a height of 2.5 m-3.5 m, providing flexibility for different applications.</p><p>the pms3-01 features a software setting for adjusting time settings. the&nbsp;time setting can be configured, allowing customization of the sensor''s&nbsp;activation duration.</p><p>designed to operate effectively in various environmental conditions,&nbsp;the sensor has a wide working temperature range of -10°c to +40°c,&nbsp;ensuring reliable performance in different settings.</p><p>the pms3-01 can be seamlessly integrated and combined with other&nbsp;inels units using the idm3 software. this allows for the implementation&nbsp;of additional logic and functions, enabling automation and customized&nbsp;control scenarios based on specific requirements.</p><p>the pms3-01 features a compact form factor with dimensions of 115 x&nbsp;24 mm, facilitating easy installation and integration into different ceiling&nbsp;or surface mounting applications.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/pms3-01/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_pms3-01.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/pms3-01/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_pms3-1.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (44, 'en', '3Lv_jIO5moZU-IPcvmJBl', '/gcr3-230', true, 'P1h5G0FMQzM1zFe6s-Q6J', 'GCR3-230', true, '<p>Glass card reader GCR3-230 is part of a comprehensive range of glass&nbsp;iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects, e.g.&nbsp;guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>GCR3-230 card reader is designed for reading smart cards, which are intended&nbsp;to enter the hotel room or any other part of the building.</p><p>GCR3-230 supports RFID media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 MHz.&nbsp;Supported card types Mifare 1k, 4k, Ultralight, DesFire, ISO/IEC 14443-4 (CD97BX, CD light, P5CN072 (SMX) Innovision jewel (IRT5001), FeliCa&nbsp;(RCS_860, RCS_854)</p><p>The GCR3 is a design component of the iNELS system and is available in&nbsp;elegant black (GCR3-30/B, GCR3-230/B ) and white (GCR3-30/ W, GCR3-230/ W) variants. The GCR3-30 models feature a square design, while the&nbsp;GCR3-230 models come in a round design.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request. The room number as&nbsp;well as the logo of the hotel can also be engraved on each component.</p><p>The controller is also equipped with 3x capacitive touch buttons with different&nbsp;functions or macro (set of functions). It is therefore possible to use&nbsp;one button to control several applications. For eg. the Function of bell and&nbsp;with two icons to indicate the status of guest requests, e.g. “Do Not Disturb" and "Make Up Room", whose state guests can set from other glass&nbsp;switch panels.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colours - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.&nbsp;</p><p>Reader GCR3-230 is equipped with a sensor for ambient light intensity and a proximity sensor. Based on information from the sensor it can e.g.&nbsp;switch the lighting circuits in the corridor.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are&nbsp;designed for mounting into an installation.</p><p>GCR3-230 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GCR3-230', 'Glass card reader, round', '[{"image":{"uploadId":398,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191722', '9172 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-230/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gcr3-30_230.pdf', '', '', '', 1763987758141, 1763987758141, '/gcr3-230                                                                                                                                                        gcr3-230                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass card reader gcr3-230 is part of a comprehensive range of glass&nbsp;inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects, e.g.&nbsp;guest room management system (grms).</p><p>gcr3-230 card reader is designed for reading smart cards, which are intended&nbsp;to enter the hotel room or any other part of the building.</p><p>gcr3-230 supports rfid media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 mhz.&nbsp;supported card types mifare 1k, 4k, ultralight, desfire, iso/iec 14443-4 (cd97bx, cd light, p5cn072 (smx) innovision jewel (irt5001), felica&nbsp;(rcs_860, rcs_854)</p><p>the gcr3 is a design component of the inels system and is available in&nbsp;elegant black (gcr3-30/b, gcr3-230/b ) and white (gcr3-30/ w, gcr3-230/ w) variants. the gcr3-30 models feature a square design, while the&nbsp;gcr3-230 models come in a round design.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request. the room number as&nbsp;well as the logo of the hotel can also be engraved on each component.</p><p>the controller is also equipped with 3x capacitive touch buttons with different&nbsp;functions or macro (set of functions). it is therefore possible to use&nbsp;one button to control several applications. for eg. the function of bell and&nbsp;with two icons to indicate the status of guest requests, e.g. “do not disturb" and "make up room", whose state guests can set from other glass&nbsp;switch panels.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colours - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.&nbsp;</p><p>reader gcr3-230 is equipped with a sensor for ambient light intensity and a proximity sensor. based on information from the sensor it can e.g.&nbsp;switch the lighting circuits in the corridor.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are&nbsp;designed for mounting into an installation.</p><p>gcr3-230 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-230/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gcr3-30_230.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-230/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gcr3-30_230.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (31, 'en', 'tnDF3Uuym6BvX42INmAEi', '/ti3-60m', true, '8RR1TPs_QxvJd6felj-wI', 'TI3-60M', true, '<p>Unit TI3-60M is designed to connect up to six external temperature sensors.</p><p>Units range TI3 support the connection of the following temperature sensors:<br>- TC / TZ - 2-wire connections<br>- Ni1000, Pt1000, Pt100 - 2-wire and 3-wire connections.</p><p>It is used in cases where it is necessary to read the temperature, eg floor/room, indoor/outdoor temperature, process equipment - boiler, solar heating, etc.</p><p>Unit status is indicated by green RUN LED on the front panel:<br>- If the supply voltage is connected (the unit is powered via the BUS), but there is no communication with the master, RUN LED is lit continuously.<br>- If the supply voltage is connected and the unit communicates via standard BUS, RUN LED flashes.</p><p>The status on individual temperature inputs is indicated by the relevant red LED on the front panel:<br>- LIT - temperature sensor disconnection<br>- FLASHES - exceeding of the temperature range<br>- UNLIT - ok.</p><p>TI3-60M in 3-module is designed for switchboard mounting on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'TI3-60M', 'Temperature input, 6-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":203,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132893', '3289 standard', 11, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ti3-60m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/TI3-60M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760099402156, 1760601025647, '/ti3-60m                                                                                                                                                         ti3-60m                                                                                                                                                          <p>unit ti3-60m is designed to connect up to six external temperature sensors.</p><p>units range ti3 support the connection of the following temperature sensors:<br>- tc / tz - 2-wire connections<br>- ni1000, pt1000, pt100 - 2-wire and 3-wire connections.</p><p>it is used in cases where it is necessary to read the temperature, eg floor/room, indoor/outdoor temperature, process equipment - boiler, solar heating, etc.</p><p>unit status is indicated by green run led on the front panel:<br>- if the supply voltage is connected (the unit is powered via the bus), but there is no communication with the master, run led is lit continuously.<br>- if the supply voltage is connected and the unit communicates via standard bus, run led flashes.</p><p>the status on individual temperature inputs is indicated by the relevant red led on the front panel:<br>- lit - temperature sensor disconnection<br>- flashes - exceeding of the temperature range<br>- unlit - ok.</p><p>ti3-60m in 3-module is designed for switchboard mounting on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ti3-60m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ti3-60m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (58, 'en', 'fQgpu0yJnjmMy8usYbTCL', '/gsb3-90', true, '2ha1sZwwT3jFaVmydkux1', 'GSB3-90', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-40, GSB3-60 and GSB3-90 are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of glass iNELS control units and can be&nbsp;advantageously used in all projects for example as a part of the guest room&nbsp;management system (GRMS).&nbsp;</p><p>GSB3-40 is equipped with four, GSB3-60 six and GSB3-90 nine touch buttons&nbsp;whose functions can easily modify by the software.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a white LED&nbsp;indicating the status of the controlled output.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is&nbsp;available in elegant black (GSB3-40/B, GSB3-60/B, GSB3-90/B) and white&nbsp;(GSB3-40/W, GSB3-60/W, GSB3-90/W) versions.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the module (94x94 mm) from the line of&nbsp;luxury switches and sockets LOGUS90 and are therefore fully in line with&nbsp;the design of frames for the sockets of this series, where you can just as&nbsp;for the controllers choose white and black glass frames.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>GSB3-40, GSB3-60 and GSB3-90 are designed for mounting into an installation&nbsp;box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'GSB3-90', 'Glass switch button', '[{"image":{"uploadId":406,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188188289', '8828 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764328660969, 1764328660969, '/gsb3-90                                                                                                                                                         gsb3-90                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-40, gsb3-60 and gsb3-90 are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of glass inels control units and can be&nbsp;advantageously used in all projects for example as a part of the guest room&nbsp;management system (grms).&nbsp;</p><p>gsb3-40 is equipped with four, gsb3-60 six and gsb3-90 nine touch buttons&nbsp;whose functions can easily modify by the software.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a white led&nbsp;indicating the status of the controlled output.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is&nbsp;available in elegant black (gsb3-40/b, gsb3-60/b, gsb3-90/b) and white&nbsp;(gsb3-40/w, gsb3-60/w, gsb3-90/w) versions.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the module (94x94 mm) from the line of&nbsp;luxury switches and sockets logus90 and are therefore fully in line with&nbsp;the design of frames for the sockets of this series, where you can just as&nbsp;for the controllers choose white and black glass frames.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>gsb3-40, gsb3-60 and gsb3-90 are designed for mounting into an installation&nbsp;box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/eu_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-90_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (32, 'en', 'hoAcikIfESiLUJbLrVJuN', '/ibwl3-20b-sl', true, 'VVCeSrL-DU28OLJZd0-Dt', 'IBWL3-20B-SL', true, '<p>The IBWL3-xx module enables seamless integration of iNELS wireless&nbsp;devices (such as controllers and detectors) with the wired iNELS BUS&nbsp;system, enhancing control and flexibility.</p><p>The IBWL3-XX expands system capabilities by enabling wireless devices&nbsp;to trigger events and interact with other BUS elements, making it ideal&nbsp;for smart home and building automation.</p><p>Two options available:</p><p>IBWL3-02B-SL: Supports up to 8 wireless devices and includes 2 built-in&nbsp;relays for direct control of wired components.</p><p>IBWL3-20B-SL: Supports up to 8 wireless devices and features 2 dry&nbsp;contact inputs for external devices.</p><p>Wireless devices are paired using unique RF addresses through the iNELS Design Manager (iDM3), allowing the control unit (CU3-XX) to recognize&nbsp;and create logic with BUS system elements.</p><p>Each IBWL3 module can connect up to 8 wireless devices.&nbsp;</p><p>The module is housed in a compact box design and powered directly by the 27V iNELS BUS, ensuring simple installation and a sleek, unified look.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'IBWL3-20B-SL', 'iNELS BUS wireless link', '[{"image":{"uploadId":206,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188193993', '9399', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', NULL, NULL, '', 1760100741403, 1760100741403, '/ibwl3-20b-sl                                                                                                                                                    ibwl3-20b-sl                                                                                                                                                     <p>the ibwl3-xx module enables seamless integration of inels wireless&nbsp;devices (such as controllers and detectors) with the wired inels bus&nbsp;system, enhancing control and flexibility.</p><p>the ibwl3-xx expands system capabilities by enabling wireless devices&nbsp;to trigger events and interact with other bus elements, making it ideal&nbsp;for smart home and building automation.</p><p>two options available:</p><p>ibwl3-02b-sl: supports up to 8 wireless devices and includes 2 built-in&nbsp;relays for direct control of wired components.</p><p>ibwl3-20b-sl: supports up to 8 wireless devices and features 2 dry&nbsp;contact inputs for external devices.</p><p>wireless devices are paired using unique rf addresses through the inels design manager (idm3), allowing the control unit (cu3-xx) to recognize&nbsp;and create logic with bus system elements.</p><p>each ibwl3 module can connect up to 8 wireless devices.&nbsp;</p><p>the module is housed in a compact box design and powered directly by the 27v inels bus, ensuring simple installation and a sleek, unified look.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ibwl3-20b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ibwl3-xxb-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ibwl3-20b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ibwl3-20b-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (42, 'en', 'MInm6qkwyP1-XtScWaV5g', '/mcd3-01', true, '-CegOpBryFsEO-uObkuwO', 'MCD3-01', true, '<p>The MCD3-01 is a highly versatile and compact motion sensor designed&nbsp;for ceiling or surface mounting applications. With its ultra-slim&nbsp;design, the MCD3-01 seamlessly integrates into various environments,&nbsp;providing reliable and efficient motion detection capabilities.</p><p>The sensor is powered by a 27 VDC power source, specifically the iNELS&nbsp;BUS system, ensuring stable and efficient operation.</p><p>The MCD3-01 utilizes a 5.8 GHz continuous wave (CW) radar system&nbsp;operating in the ISM band, offering precise and reliable motion detection.</p><p>The sensor provides a wide 360-degree detection angle, ensuring comprehensive&nbsp;coverage of the monitored area.</p><p>The sensor''s reach is adjustable, allowing the user to set the detection&nbsp;range. The reach can be configured within the range of 2 to 10 meters&nbsp;in radius, providing flexibility for different applications.</p><p>The MCD3-01 features a software setting for adjusting time settings.&nbsp;The time setting can be configured, allowing customization of the sensor''s&nbsp;activation duration.</p><p>Designed to operate effectively in various environmental conditions,&nbsp;the sensor has a wide working temperature range of -10°C to +40°C,&nbsp;ensuring reliable performance in different settings.</p><p>The MCD3-01 can be seamlessly integrated and combined with other&nbsp;iNELS units using the iDM3 software. This allows for the implementation&nbsp;of additional logic and functions, enabling automation and customized&nbsp;control scenarios based on specific requirements.</p><p>The MCD3-01 features a compact form factor with dimensions of 115 x&nbsp;24 mm, facilitating easy installation and integration into different ceiling&nbsp;or surface mounting applications.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1761822000000, '[]', 'MCD3-01', 'Ultra slim microwave motion detector', '[{"image":{"uploadId":297,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191234', '9123 standard', 16, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/mcd3-01/share_dokumentace/en/manual_mcd3-01.pdf', '', '', '', 1761832979604, 1761832979604, '/mcd3-01                                                                                                                                                         mcd3-01                                                                                                                                                          <p>the mcd3-01 is a highly versatile and compact motion sensor designed&nbsp;for ceiling or surface mounting applications. with its ultra-slim&nbsp;design, the mcd3-01 seamlessly integrates into various environments,&nbsp;providing reliable and efficient motion detection capabilities.</p><p>the sensor is powered by a 27 vdc power source, specifically the inels&nbsp;bus system, ensuring stable and efficient operation.</p><p>the mcd3-01 utilizes a 5.8 ghz continuous wave (cw) radar system&nbsp;operating in the ism band, offering precise and reliable motion detection.</p><p>the sensor provides a wide 360-degree detection angle, ensuring comprehensive&nbsp;coverage of the monitored area.</p><p>the sensor''s reach is adjustable, allowing the user to set the detection&nbsp;range. the reach can be configured within the range of 2 to 10 meters&nbsp;in radius, providing flexibility for different applications.</p><p>the mcd3-01 features a software setting for adjusting time settings.&nbsp;the time setting can be configured, allowing customization of the sensor''s&nbsp;activation duration.</p><p>designed to operate effectively in various environmental conditions,&nbsp;the sensor has a wide working temperature range of -10°c to +40°c,&nbsp;ensuring reliable performance in different settings.</p><p>the mcd3-01 can be seamlessly integrated and combined with other&nbsp;inels units using the idm3 software. this allows for the implementation&nbsp;of additional logic and functions, enabling automation and customized&nbsp;control scenarios based on specific requirements.</p><p>the mcd3-01 features a compact form factor with dimensions of 115 x&nbsp;24 mm, facilitating easy installation and integration into different ceiling&nbsp;or surface mounting applications.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/mcd3-01/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_mcd3-01.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/mcd3-01/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_mcd3-1.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (59, 'en', 'ZkqEIDDaTDpfuCd5zFp3S', '/gsb3-60s', true, 'yN4TmSPjas5_baDCxvT7G', 'GSB3-60/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-XX/S are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the GSB3-240/S, GSB3-260/S, and GSB3-290/S models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, GSB3-240/S are equipped with four, GSB3-60/S, GSB3-260/S six&nbsp;and GSB3-90/S, GSB3-290/S nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/&nbsp;TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/SB) and white (GSB3-XXX/SW) versions.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>In addition to all the features in symbol models. The glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the SBP/SWP version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>SWP/SBP models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'GSB3-60/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":416,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188156264', '5626 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60s/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764329370558, 1764329370558, '/gsb3-60s                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-60/s                                                                                                                                                        <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-xx/s are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the gsb3-240/s, gsb3-260/s, and gsb3-290/s models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, gsb3-240/s are equipped with four, gsb3-60/s, gsb3-260/s six&nbsp;and gsb3-90/s, gsb3-290/s nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/&nbsp;tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/sb) and white (gsb3-xxx/sw) versions.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>in addition to all the features in symbol models. the glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the sbp/swp version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>swp/sbp models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60s/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60s/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-60s.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (69, 'en', 'JORCFg31PhEi5TekCgtJO', '/telva-2', true, 'h0woOq7y-6l7A65AlmFX7', 'TELVA-2', true, '<p>Thermodrive is intended for opening or closing valves in heating, cooling or air conditioning systems. It is also suitable for use in a floor&nbsp;heating or ceiling cooling manifolds.</p><p>Available in NO (open without voltage), NC (closed without voltage)&nbsp;and for 230 V and 24 V.</p><p>The internal principle of operation of thermodrive mechanism = its&nbsp;movement so that the valve opens/closes is provided by an electric&nbsp;heating element with expansion material, which expands due to temperature changes in the supply voltage.</p><p>Thermodrive is maintenance-free and works completely silently.</p><p>Thermodrive is fi tted with a metal nut M30 x 1.5, thanks to which it becomes a 100% fixed part of the valve with this corresponding thread&nbsp;size after installation.</p><p>The stated nut size predetermines the use of a thermocouple with&nbsp;valves from manufacturers such as Herz, HoneyWell, Danfoss, Oventrop and others.</p><p>Telva thermo drive:</p><p>is characterized by absolutely quiet and maintenance-free operation</p><p>is designed for installation - control of heating and cooling systems</p><p>method of mounting the actuator on the controlled valve using an M30 x 1.5 nut</p><p>any working position</p><p>Type of use:</p><p>Floor heating – the RFTC-50/G wireless controller measures the room temperature and, based on the set program, sends a command to the RFSA-66M switching element to open/close&nbsp; the TELVA thermodrive&nbsp;on the distributor.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'TELVA-2', 'Electric Thermal Actuator', '[{"image":{"uploadId":495,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188181976', '8197', 16, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/accessories/telva-2/share_dokumentace/en/manual_telva-2.pdf', '', '', '', 1764332887340, 1764332887340, '/telva-2                                                                                                                                                         telva-2                                                                                                                                                          <p>thermodrive is intended for opening or closing valves in heating, cooling or air conditioning systems. it is also suitable for use in a floor&nbsp;heating or ceiling cooling manifolds.</p><p>available in no (open without voltage), nc (closed without voltage)&nbsp;and for 230 v and 24 v.</p><p>the internal principle of operation of thermodrive mechanism = its&nbsp;movement so that the valve opens/closes is provided by an electric&nbsp;heating element with expansion material, which expands due to temperature changes in the supply voltage.</p><p>thermodrive is maintenance-free and works completely silently.</p><p>thermodrive is fi tted with a metal nut m30 x 1.5, thanks to which it becomes a 100% fixed part of the valve with this corresponding thread&nbsp;size after installation.</p><p>the stated nut size predetermines the use of a thermocouple with&nbsp;valves from manufacturers such as herz, honeywell, danfoss, oventrop and others.</p><p>telva thermo drive:</p><p>is characterized by absolutely quiet and maintenance-free operation</p><p>is designed for installation - control of heating and cooling systems</p><p>method of mounting the actuator on the controlled valve using an m30 x 1.5 nut</p><p>any working position</p><p>type of use:</p><p>floor heating – the rftc-50/g wireless controller measures the room temperature and, based on the set program, sends a command to the rfsa-66m switching element to open/close&nbsp; the telva thermodrive&nbsp;on the distributor.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/accessories/telva-2/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_telva.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (20, 'en', 'rdfmvsR-CVM75V_-louTS', '/ea3-022m', true, 'pukJBck3RhhH_PbnZ-Gnq', 'EA3-022M', true, '<p>Equipped with 22 relay outputs (of which 1x changeover contact&nbsp;– roller blinds, blinds).</p><p>&nbsp;Switch lighting and socket circuits (6 A and 10 A relay) with common potential at the "COMx" terminal.</p><p>&nbsp;Control of roller blinds, blinds (24 - 230 V AC/DC)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Relay control of the fan coil unit - heating/cooling, 3 fan speeds (24 - 230 V AC/DC).</p><p>&nbsp;Connection to BUS, communication with CU3.</p><p>&nbsp;EA3-022M in design 6-MODULE is designed to be mounted into a switchboard, onto DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'EA3-022M', 'Switching actuator without controls and indicator, 22-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":190,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188135238', '3523 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ea3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ea3-022m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/EA3-022M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922376194, 1760601283496, '/ea3-022m                                                                                                                                                        ea3-022m                                                                                                                                                         <p>equipped with 22 relay outputs (of which 1x changeover contact&nbsp;– roller blinds, blinds).</p><p>&nbsp;switch lighting and socket circuits (6 a and 10 a relay) with common potential at the "comx" terminal.</p><p>&nbsp;control of roller blinds, blinds (24 - 230 v ac/dc)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;relay control of the fan coil unit - heating/cooling, 3 fan speeds (24 - 230 v ac/dc).</p><p>&nbsp;connection to bus, communication with cu3.</p><p>&nbsp;ea3-022m in design 6-module is designed to be mounted into a switchboard, onto din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ea3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ea3-022m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ea3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ea3-022m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (45, 'en', 'cejQs_HTz-pOm6-Xymoey', '/gcr3-30', true, 'prxuv-rl8gXTo2xIsJ4Qo', 'GCR3-30', true, '<p>Glass card reader GCR3-30 is part of a comprehensive range of glass&nbsp;iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects, e.g.&nbsp;guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>GCR3-30 card reader is designed for reading smart cards, which are intended&nbsp;to enter the hotel room or any other part of the building.</p><p>GCR3-30 supports RFID media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 MHz.&nbsp;Supported card types Mifare 1k, 4k, Ultralight, DesFire, ISO/IEC 14443-4 (CD97BX, CD light, P5CN072 (SMX) Innovision jewel (IRT5001), FeliCa&nbsp;(RCS_860, RCS_854)&nbsp;</p><p>The GCR3 is a design component of the iNELS system and is available in&nbsp;elegant black (GCR3-30/B, GCR3-230/B ) and white (GCR3-30/ W, GCR3-230/ W) variants. The GCR3-30 models feature a square design, while the&nbsp;GCR3-230 models come in a round design.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request. The room number as&nbsp;well as the logo of the hotel can be also engraved on each component.</p><p>The controller is also equipped with 3x capacitive touch buttons with different&nbsp;functions or macro (set of functions). It is therefore possible to use&nbsp;one button to control several applications. For eg. the function of the bell and two icons to indicate the status of guest requests, e.g. “Do Not Disturb"&nbsp;and "Make Up Room", whose state guests can set from other glass&nbsp;switch panels.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colours - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>Reader GCR3-30 is equipped with a sensor for ambient light intensity&nbsp;and proximity sensor. Based on information from the sensor it can e.g.&nbsp;switch the lighting circuits in the corridor.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are&nbsp;designed for mounting into an installation.</p><p>GCR3-30 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GCR3-30', 'Glass card reader, sharp', '[{"image":{"uploadId":394,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191708', '9170 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-30/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gcr3-30_230.pdf', '', '', '', 1763988792625, 1763988792625, '/gcr3-30                                                                                                                                                         gcr3-30                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass card reader gcr3-30 is part of a comprehensive range of glass&nbsp;inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects, e.g.&nbsp;guest room management system (grms).</p><p>gcr3-30 card reader is designed for reading smart cards, which are intended&nbsp;to enter the hotel room or any other part of the building.</p><p>gcr3-30 supports rfid media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 mhz.&nbsp;supported card types mifare 1k, 4k, ultralight, desfire, iso/iec 14443-4 (cd97bx, cd light, p5cn072 (smx) innovision jewel (irt5001), felica&nbsp;(rcs_860, rcs_854)&nbsp;</p><p>the gcr3 is a design component of the inels system and is available in&nbsp;elegant black (gcr3-30/b, gcr3-230/b ) and white (gcr3-30/ w, gcr3-230/ w) variants. the gcr3-30 models feature a square design, while the&nbsp;gcr3-230 models come in a round design.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request. the room number as&nbsp;well as the logo of the hotel can be also engraved on each component.</p><p>the controller is also equipped with 3x capacitive touch buttons with different&nbsp;functions or macro (set of functions). it is therefore possible to use&nbsp;one button to control several applications. for eg. the function of the bell and two icons to indicate the status of guest requests, e.g. “do not disturb"&nbsp;and "make up room", whose state guests can set from other glass&nbsp;switch panels.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colours - red,&nbsp;green, blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>reader gcr3-30 is equipped with a sensor for ambient light intensity&nbsp;and proximity sensor. based on information from the sensor it can e.g.&nbsp;switch the lighting circuits in the corridor.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are&nbsp;designed for mounting into an installation.</p><p>gcr3-30 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-30/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gcr3-30_230.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gcr3-30/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gcr3-30_230.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (14, 'en', '7jRPQWM0fpkbBRh0oM_kc', '/sa3-02m', true, 'aOki_BStEXnW_D90IwPhw', 'SA3-02M', true, '<p>SA3-02M is a switching actuator containing 2 independent relays with changeover potentialless contacts.&nbsp;</p><p>Maximum load per contact is 16 A/4000 VA/AC1.</p><p>Each of the two output contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>Both relays are individually decorated input terminals, and therefore can switch various independent potentials.</p><p>The actuator is designed for switching up to two various appliances and loads relay output (potentialless contact).&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to changeover contacts, it can be used to control one 230 V power (such as blinds, shutters or awnings) with appropriate bridging, the contacts can secure hardware blocking the possibility of simultaneous switching of the phase on both outputs, see example of connection.</p><p>LEDs on the front panel signal the status of each output.</p><p>Contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually by control buttons on the front panel.</p><p>Switching actuators SA3 are normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.</p><p>SA3-02M in 1-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'SA3-02M', 'Switching actuator, 2-channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":184,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132374', '3237 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-02m.pdf', NULL, NULL, '', 1759151118904, 1760012314981, '/sa3-02m                                                                                                                                                         sa3-02m                                                                                                                                                          <p>sa3-02m is a switching actuator containing 2 independent relays with changeover potentialless contacts.&nbsp;</p><p>maximum load per contact is 16 a/4000 va/ac1.</p><p>each of the two output contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>both relays are individually decorated input terminals, and therefore can switch various independent potentials.</p><p>the actuator is designed for switching up to two various appliances and loads relay output (potentialless contact).&nbsp;</p><p>thanks to changeover contacts, it can be used to control one 230 v power (such as blinds, shutters or awnings) with appropriate bridging, the contacts can secure hardware blocking the possibility of simultaneous switching of the phase on both outputs, see example of connection.</p><p>leds on the front panel signal the status of each output.</p><p>contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually by control buttons on the front panel.</p><p>switching actuators sa3 are normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.</p><p>sa3-02m in 1-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-02m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-02m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (60, 'en', 'K2PgE7GQffvztGpc8GnBC', '/gsb3-40s', true, 'isgvIsp0rQqitcKrXs1kw', 'GSB3-40/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-XX/S are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the GSB3-240/S, GSB3-260/S, and GSB3-290/S models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, and GSB3-240/S is equipped with four, GSB3-60/S, GSB3-260/S six&nbsp;and GSB3-90/S, GSB3-290/S nine touch buttons whose functions can easily&nbsp;modify by the software.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/SB) and white (GSB3-XXX/SW) versions.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>In addition to all the features in symbol models. The glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the SBP/SWP version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>SWP/SBP models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'GSB3-40/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":414,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188156240', '5624 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40sp/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764329571350, 1764329571350, '/gsb3-40s                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-40/s                                                                                                                                                        <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-xx/s are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the gsb3-240/s, gsb3-260/s, and gsb3-290/s models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, and gsb3-240/s is equipped with four, gsb3-60/s, gsb3-260/s six&nbsp;and gsb3-90/s, gsb3-290/s nine touch buttons whose functions can easily&nbsp;modify by the software.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/sb) and white (gsb3-xxx/sw) versions.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>in addition to all the features in symbol models. the glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the sbp/swp version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>swp/sbp models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40sp/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40sp/share_dokumentace/en/eu_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-40sp_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (65, 'en', 'P9Xd9eGXsYHKJQW57su34', '/msb3-90', true, 'vKMe1TFsa37l9cYqlVFX9', 'MSB3-90', true, '<p>Metal switch buttons MSB3-90/XX are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>MSB3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>MSB3-90/XX is equipped with nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>The metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>The metal switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>MSB3-90/XX are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'MSB3-90', 'Metal switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":485,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191333', '9133 standard', 15, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/manual_msb3-x0_bus_a4_en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764330717261, 1764330717261, '/msb3-90                                                                                                                                                         msb3-90                                                                                                                                                          <p>metal switch buttons msb3-90/xx are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>msb3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>msb3-90/xx is equipped with nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>the metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>the metal switch button is a design component of the inels system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>msb3-90/xx are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_msb3-40-60-90.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-90/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_msb3-90.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (5, 'en', '_oUzdvnp4SR5DKwtPeTyv', '/inels-bridge', true, 'We3XZc796Cm8E5tjI_wpl', 'iNELS Bridge', true, '<p>iNELS Bridge works as a gateway for connecting third-party devices and&nbsp;integrating them into the iNELS environment.</p><p>It is a one-module hardware containing a powerful Linux-based computer.</p><p>The unit comes with an option of pre-installed Home Assistant with iNELS&nbsp;driver.</p><p>The server uses the open Home Assistant platform, which contains more&nbsp;than 1000 existing integrations.</p><p>The connection server provides a communication environment between the iNELS BUS System and the third-party devices, for which their protocols are also translated and submitted.</p><p>iNELS Bridge is equipped with an ethernet port for fast and easy communication.</p><p>The configuration is happening on its own web interface, where the default&nbsp;IP address is not fixed. (The IP address is assigned from the DHCP&nbsp;server and it‘s needed to be known when we‘re connected to the network).</p><p>The device can be powered by 24VDC input, and it also supports Power&nbsp;over Ethernet (Passive POE), providing flexibility in power options.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'iNELS Bridge', 'Third-party integration gateway', '[{"image":{"uploadId":170,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188185097', '8509', 3, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/inels_bridge/share_dokumentace/en/inels-bridge_manual.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/iNELS_Bridge/3D/3d.html', '', 1759147414394, 1760601664496, '/inels-bridge                                                                                                                                                    inels bridge                                                                                                                                                     <p>inels bridge works as a gateway for connecting third-party devices and&nbsp;integrating them into the inels environment.</p><p>it is a one-module hardware containing a powerful linux-based computer.</p><p>the unit comes with an option of pre-installed home assistant with inels&nbsp;driver.</p><p>the server uses the open home assistant platform, which contains more&nbsp;than 1000 existing integrations.</p><p>the connection server provides a communication environment between the inels bus system and the third-party devices, for which their protocols are also translated and submitted.</p><p>inels bridge is equipped with an ethernet port for fast and easy communication.</p><p>the configuration is happening on its own web interface, where the default&nbsp;ip address is not fixed. (the ip address is assigned from the dhcp&nbsp;server and it‘s needed to be known when we‘re connected to the network).</p><p>the device can be powered by 24vdc input, and it also supports power&nbsp;over ethernet (passive poe), providing flexibility in power options.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/inels_bridge/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_inels_bridge.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/inels_bridge/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_inels_bridge.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (6, 'en', 'VK8YHW-9j5Yx9EPceibKz', '/ps3-30dali', true, 'qGArbxkpyhv_ykY-FCHTf', 'PS3-30/DALI', true, '<p>PS3-30/DALI provides 30 W total power for both iNELS BUS (27 V DC)&nbsp;and DALI devices (16 V DC), ensuring efficient power distribution for&nbsp;central units, external masters, and peripheral devices including DALI&nbsp;BUS.</p><p>PS3-30/DALI includes an internally integrated bus isolator to power&nbsp;one branch of the iNELS BUS, maintaining a reliable and isolated power&nbsp;supply for connected peripheral units.</p><p>It is equipped with electronic protection against short circuits, overvoltage,&nbsp;power overload, and temperature overload, ensuring safe and&nbsp;stable operation.</p><p>Offers over 85% efficiency, optimizing energy consumption and reducing&nbsp;heat generation.</p><p>Compact Design: 3-module unit designed for easy mounting on DIN&nbsp;rail EN60715, allowing for streamlined installation in switchboards and&nbsp;control panels.</p><p>It supports a wide input voltage range of 100-240 V AC and operates in&nbsp;temperatures from -20°C to +55°C, suitable for various environmental&nbsp;conditions.</p><p>Meets safety standards EN 60950-1 and EN 62368-1, EMC standards EN&nbsp;55032 and EN 55024, and is RoHS compliant, ensuring adherence to international&nbsp;safety and environmental regulations.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'PS3-30/DALI', 'Power Supply with BUS separator integrated with DALI power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":175,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188192606', '9260 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_dali/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ps3-30_dali_bus.pdf', NULL, NULL, '', 1759148377098, 1760011838889, '/ps3-30dali                                                                                                                                                      ps3-30/dali                                                                                                                                                      <p>ps3-30/dali provides 30 w total power for both inels bus (27 v dc)&nbsp;and dali devices (16 v dc), ensuring efficient power distribution for&nbsp;central units, external masters, and peripheral devices including dali&nbsp;bus.</p><p>ps3-30/dali includes an internally integrated bus isolator to power&nbsp;one branch of the inels bus, maintaining a reliable and isolated power&nbsp;supply for connected peripheral units.</p><p>it is equipped with electronic protection against short circuits, overvoltage,&nbsp;power overload, and temperature overload, ensuring safe and&nbsp;stable operation.</p><p>offers over 85% efficiency, optimizing energy consumption and reducing&nbsp;heat generation.</p><p>compact design: 3-module unit designed for easy mounting on din&nbsp;rail en60715, allowing for streamlined installation in switchboards and&nbsp;control panels.</p><p>it supports a wide input voltage range of 100-240 v ac and operates in&nbsp;temperatures from -20°c to +55°c, suitable for various environmental&nbsp;conditions.</p><p>meets safety standards en 60950-1 and en 62368-1, emc standards en&nbsp;55032 and en 55024, and is rohs compliant, ensuring adherence to international&nbsp;safety and environmental regulations.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_dali/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ps3-30_dali.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_dali/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ps3-30_dali_bus.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (46, 'en', 'IThuAxx4k8OxE1mguSG7A', '/zsb3-90', true, 'dRc3c086h0hQ8Gb4xEF8N', 'ZSB3-90', true, '<p>Glass switch buttons ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are part&nbsp;of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>ZSB3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black.</p><p>ZSB3-40/XX is equipped with four, ZSB3-60/XX six and ZSB3-90/XX nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>The glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>The glass switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and is&nbsp;available in white and black.</p><p>There is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further&nbsp;enhancing customization possibilities.</p><p>Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'ZSB3-90', 'Glass switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":409,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188192590', '9259 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1763989898567, 1763989898567, '/zsb3-90                                                                                                                                                         zsb3-90                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass switch buttons zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are part&nbsp;of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>zsb3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black.</p><p>zsb3-40/xx is equipped with four, zsb3-60/xx six and zsb3-90/xx nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>the glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>the glass switch button is a design component of the inels system and is&nbsp;available in white and black.</p><p>there is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further&nbsp;enhancing customization possibilities.</p><p>individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (124, 'en', 'NbuUyWXwGM-EEcbRNSZYz', '/rfsti-11b-sl', true, 'E5VGyg5OKnK3TnnS3-dvj', 'RFSTI-11B-SL', true, '<p>The temperature element measures the temperature with an external sensor and at the same time controls the heating circuit (electric underfloor heating, air conditioning, boiler…).</p><p>They can be combined with Detectors, Controllers or iNELS RF Control system components.</p><p>It measures the temperature in the range -20 to +50 °C and sends it to the system component in a regular 5 min. intervals. It sends a signal when the temperature changes suddenly.</p><p>The heating/cooling, hysteresis and off-set functions are set in the system component or application.</p><p>It allows the connection of a switched load up to 8 A (2,000 W).</p><p>Range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the controller and the device, use the RFRP-20 signal repeater or component with the RFIO2 protocol that supports this function.</p><p>Communication with bidirectional RFIO2 protocol.</p><p>The BOX version offers installation directly in the installation box, ceiling or cover of the controlled appliance. Easy installation thanks to screwless terminals.</p><p>External sensor TC (-20 to +80 °C) or TZ (-40 to +125 °C) with a length of 3 m, 6 m, 12 m.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFSTI-11B-SL', 'Switching units with external temperature sensor', '[{"image":{"uploadId":786,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184045', '8404', 30, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsti-11b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsti-11b-sl.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSTI-11B-SL/3D/3d.html', '', 1769168373132, 1769168373132, '/rfsti-11b-sl                                                                                                                                                    rfsti-11b-sl                                                                                                                                                     <p>the temperature element measures the temperature with an external sensor and at the same time controls the heating circuit (electric underfloor heating, air conditioning, boiler…).</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers or inels rf control system components.</p><p>it measures the temperature in the range -20 to +50 °c and sends it to the system component in a regular 5 min. intervals. it sends a signal when the temperature changes suddenly.</p><p>the heating/cooling, hysteresis and off-set functions are set in the system component or application.</p><p>it allows the connection of a switched load up to 8 a (2,000 w).</p><p>range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the controller and the device, use the rfrp-20 signal repeater or component with the rfio2 protocol that supports this function.</p><p>communication with bidirectional rfio2 protocol.</p><p>the box version offers installation directly in the installation box, ceiling or cover of the controlled appliance. easy installation thanks to screwless terminals.</p><p>external sensor tc (-20 to +80 °c) or tz (-40 to +125 °c) with a length of 3 m, 6 m, 12 m.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsti-11b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsti-11b-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsti-11b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsti-11b-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (70, 'en', '_Zp9MMdD2YdeHDGCNPGG2', '/add-ons', true, 'OEqpr3L-bokYnGeRLvaL4', 'ADD-ONS', true, '<p>Product code - Type of protocol</p><p>A-GRS4 - Modbus</p><p>A-ZGB - Zigbee</p><p>A-iBUS - iNELS BUS</p><p>connectivity options with protocol VRV&amp;VRF Systems</p><p>Product code - Supported Brand</p><p>A-VSM - Samsung</p><p>A-VDK - Daikin</p><p>A-VHT - Hitachi</p><p>A-VLG - LG</p><p>A-VME - Mitsubishi Electric</p><p>A-VMH - Mitsubishi Heavy</p><p>A-VMD - Midea/Chigo</p><p>A-VPA - Panasonic/Sanyo</p><p>A-VTO - Toshiba</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'ADD-ONS', 'Connectivity options', '[{"image":{"uploadId":501,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764334716694, 1764334716694, '/add-ons                                                                                                                                                         add-ons                                                                                                                                                          <p>product code - type of protocol</p><p>a-grs4 - modbus</p><p>a-zgb - zigbee</p><p>a-ibus - inels bus</p><p>connectivity options with protocol vrv&amp;vrf systems</p><p>product code - supported brand</p><p>a-vsm - samsung</p><p>a-vdk - daikin</p><p>a-vht - hitachi</p><p>a-vlg - lg</p><p>a-vme - mitsubishi electric</p><p>a-vmh - mitsubishi heavy</p><p>a-vmd - midea/chigo</p><p>a-vpa - panasonic/sanyo</p><p>a-vto - toshiba</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/inspinia_add-ons/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_inspinia%20add-ons.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (111, 'en', 'WGQsRB58RjCnCJ3dq3Sh2', '/rfdac-71b-sl', true, '1MwYxZkKsiZdidP5Du7ZC', 'RFDAC-71B-SL', true, '<p>The device with analog output 0(1)–10 V is used to control devices, luminaires,&nbsp;thermal actuators, and thermal heads – which are equipped&nbsp;with such an input.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless, or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>Potential free analog output 0(1)–10 V, contact relay 8 A.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s–30 min.&nbsp;</p><p>The analog controller may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>The programming button on the controller is also used for manual&nbsp;control of the output.</p><p>Memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.&nbsp;</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>The BOX design lets you mount it right in an installation box, a ceiling, or a light cover.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFDAC-71B-SL', 'Analog controller, 0(1)-10V', '[{"image":{"uploadId":769,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188182676', '8267', 27, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdac-71b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfdac-71b-sl.pdf', '', '', '', 1769002447428, 1769002447428, '/rfdac-71b-sl                                                                                                                                                    rfdac-71b-sl                                                                                                                                                     <p>the device with analog output 0(1)–10 v is used to control devices, luminaires,&nbsp;thermal actuators, and thermal heads – which are equipped&nbsp;with such an input.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless, or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>potential free analog output 0(1)–10 v, contact relay 8 a.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s–30 min.&nbsp;</p><p>the analog controller may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>the programming button on the controller is also used for manual&nbsp;control of the output.</p><p>memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.&nbsp;</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>the box design lets you mount it right in an installation box, a ceiling, or a light cover.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdac-71b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfdac-71b-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdac-71b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfdac-71b-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (47, 'en', 'XfkgNtuN4ttOdcwnbVfq-', '/zsb3-60', true, 'qMGYCo5AC8R82U5nI992B', 'ZSB3-60', true, '<p>Glass switch buttons ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are part&nbsp;of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>ZSB3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black.</p><p>ZSB3-40/XX is equipped with four, ZSB3-60/XX six and ZSB3-90/XX nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>The glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>The glass switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and is&nbsp;available in white and black.</p><p>There is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further&nbsp;enhancing customization possibilities.</p><p>Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'ZSB3-60', 'Glass switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":408,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188192576', '9257 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1763990003895, 1763990003895, '/zsb3-60                                                                                                                                                         zsb3-60                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass switch buttons zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are part&nbsp;of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>zsb3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black.</p><p>zsb3-40/xx is equipped with four, zsb3-60/xx six and zsb3-90/xx nine&nbsp;touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>the glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).&nbsp;it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>the glass switch button is a design component of the inels system and is&nbsp;available in white and black.</p><p>there is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further&nbsp;enhancing customization possibilities.</p><p>individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (71, 'en', 'Te4tT8kg7KkZJ6e35S3Q2', '/frame-for-ins4sq', true, 'OmD7gTTnDUbkoo0tmPt8W', 'FRAME FOR INS4SQ', true, '<p>The frames are aluminum with sharp or curved corners and are available in black, silver, gold</p><p><strong>Code of product - Type of frame</strong></p><p>FRM4H1.BSharp - black</p><p>FRM4H1.SSharp - silver</p><p>FRM4H1.GSharp - gold</p><p>FRM4P1.BCurve - black</p><p>FRM4P1.SCurve - silver</p><p>FRM4P1.GCurve - gold</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', NULL, '[]', 'FRAME FOR INS4SQ', 'Accessories for control panels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":497,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764334882148, 1764334882148, '/frame-for-ins4sq                                                                                                                                                frame for ins4sq                                                                                                                                                 <p>the frames are aluminum with sharp or curved corners and are available in black, silver, gold</p><p><strong>code of product - type of frame</strong></p><p>frm4h1.bsharp - black</p><p>frm4h1.ssharp - silver</p><p>frm4h1.gsharp - gold</p><p>frm4p1.bcurve - black</p><p>frm4p1.scurve - silver</p><p>frm4p1.gcurve - gold</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (125, 'en', 'YA0TV4kkVoNKpb3YC-LYw', '/rfsa-266m', true, 'YXtPMFX68UQsnr_VZKwME', 'RFSA-266M', true, '<p>Thanks to the 5-channel design of the switching component it can control&nbsp;the heating/cooling mode and 3 speed levels.</p><p>The RFSA-266M wireless switch unit can be combined with the RFTC-4.&nbsp;</p><p>The input channels are used to connect to the external TC/TZ temperature&nbsp;sensor.</p><p>The product is independently functional when connected to the MODBUS,&nbsp;otherwise, it must be connected to the control element, e.g. RFTC-4.</p><p>Support for both 2-pipe fan coil and 4-pipe fan coil.</p><p>Fancoil controls the cooling or heating of the room and provides up to&nbsp;3-speed levels.</p><p>In case of insufficient signal between the controller and the switch unit,&nbsp;use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or elements with RFIO2 protocol that&nbsp;support this function.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFSA-266M', 'Switch unit for fancoil control', '[{"image":{"uploadId":787,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189781', '8978', 30, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSA-266M/3D/3d.html', '', 1769169939892, 1769169939892, '/rfsa-266m                                                                                                                                                       rfsa-266m                                                                                                                                                        <p>thanks to the 5-channel design of the switching component it can control&nbsp;the heating/cooling mode and 3 speed levels.</p><p>the rfsa-266m wireless switch unit can be combined with the rftc-4.&nbsp;</p><p>the input channels are used to connect to the external tc/tz temperature&nbsp;sensor.</p><p>the product is independently functional when connected to the modbus,&nbsp;otherwise, it must be connected to the control element, e.g. rftc-4.</p><p>support for both 2-pipe fan coil and 4-pipe fan coil.</p><p>fancoil controls the cooling or heating of the room and provides up to&nbsp;3-speed levels.</p><p>in case of insufficient signal between the controller and the switch unit,&nbsp;use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or elements with rfio2 protocol that&nbsp;support this function.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-266m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsa-266m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-266m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-266m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (9, 'en', 'Cnfa-EXPHDCNR2uAFXeDZ', '/psm3-30inels', true, 'OPGF64Cz47nzWA2oQNRbg', 'PSM3-30/iNELS', true, '<p>Used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation iNELS.</p><p>Through BUS separators from the supply voltage BPS3-01M and&nbsp;BPS3-02M, it supplies BUS lines from which iNELS peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>Rated output voltage 27V DC with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>High efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>Low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>Protection: Overload, Over voltage and Short circuit.</p><p>Continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'PSM3-30/iNELS', 'Power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":177,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184762', '8476 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/manual_psm3_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/PSM3-30_iNELS/3D/3d.html', '', 1759148687967, 1760601565207, '/psm3-30inels                                                                                                                                                    psm3-30/inels                                                                                                                                                    <p>used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation inels.</p><p>through bus separators from the supply voltage bps3-01m and&nbsp;bps3-02m, it supplies bus lines from which inels peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>rated output voltage 27v dc with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>high efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>protection: overload, over voltage and short circuit.</p><p>continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_psm3-30_inels_psm3-60_inels_psm3-100_inels.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_psm3-30_inels_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (48, 'en', '-XzxYiiBxWiHOqi0abH-b', '/zsb3-40', true, 'gm9VtWqRXE3gA--O-HT46', 'ZSB3-40', true, '<p>Glass switch buttons ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are part of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects. ZSB3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black. ZSB3-40/XX is equipped with four, ZSB3-60/XX six and ZSB3-90/XX nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software. The glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor). Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors. Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once. The glass switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and is available in white and black. There is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further enhancing customization possibilities. Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.  ZSB3-40/XX, ZSB3-60/XX and ZSB3-90/XX are designed for mounting into an installation box. All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'ZSB3-40', 'Glass switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":403,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188192552', '9255 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1763990056909, 1763990056909, '/zsb3-40                                                                                                                                                         zsb3-40                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass switch buttons zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are part of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects. zsb3 comes with premium glass plates in the white and black. zsb3-40/xx is equipped with four, zsb3-60/xx six and zsb3-90/xx nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software. the glass switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor). advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors. each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once. the glass switch button is a design component of the inels system and is available in white and black. there is an option upon request to engrave text for each button, further enhancing customization possibilities. individual buttons can be illuminated in white.  zsb3-40/xx, zsb3-60/xx and zsb3-90/xx are designed for mounting into an installation box. all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (61, 'en', 'CCOxs2EFF5NfShgrxy_ti', '/gsb3-60', true, '-TPTv8YtmitDfL1TwHs6I', 'GSB3-60', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers GSB3-XXX are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40, GSB3-60, and GSB3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the GSB3-240, GSB3-260, and GSB3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>GSB3-40 and GSB3-240 are equipped with four, GSB3-60, GSB3-260 six and GSB3-&nbsp;90, GSB3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/B) and white (GSB3-XXX/W) versions.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue LED indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'GSB3-60', 'Glass switch button', '[]', '8595188132985', '3298 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', 1764329674832, 1764329674832, '/gsb3-60                                                                                                                                                         gsb3-60                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass touch controllers gsb3-xxx are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40, gsb3-60, and gsb3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the gsb3-240, gsb3-260, and gsb3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>gsb3-40 and gsb3-240 are equipped with four, gsb3-60, gsb3-260 six and gsb3-&nbsp;90, gsb3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/b) and white (gsb3-xxx/w) versions.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue led indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-60.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/eu_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-60_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (29, 'en', 'LQItDGW8XGVU6_HYOLJTy', '/im3-140m', true, 'TwuJJMCnJghJpFaYix2DJ', 'IM3-140M', true, '<p>Binary input unit IM3-140M is designed to connect up to 14 devices with potentialless contact (such as switches, buttons of other designs, fire and glass detectors and others).</p><p>Inputs IN1 - IN7 can be balanced.</p><p>Contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the drive can be NO or NC - Input parameters are configured in the software iDM3.</p><p>Inputs must be configured as balanced or double balanced - in an internal Electronic security system configurated in iDM3 software.</p><p>The unit generates a supply voltage of 12 V DC / 150 mA for powering external detectors, so it can power PIR detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>Active use 12 V DC output for powering detectors increases the nominal consumption units from BUS (see technical data).</p><p>The unit can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse output.</p><p>IM3-140M in 3-module is designed for switchboard mounting on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'IM3-140M', 'Binary input unit, 14-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":202,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132459', '3245 standard', 11, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-140m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_im3-140m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/IM3-140M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760099198000, 1760601086364, '/im3-140m                                                                                                                                                        im3-140m                                                                                                                                                         <p>binary input unit im3-140m is designed to connect up to 14 devices with potentialless contact (such as switches, buttons of other designs, fire and glass detectors and others).</p><p>inputs in1 - in7 can be balanced.</p><p>contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the drive can be no or nc - input parameters are configured in the software idm3.</p><p>inputs must be configured as balanced or double balanced - in an internal electronic security system configurated in idm3 software.</p><p>the unit generates a supply voltage of 12 v dc / 150 ma for powering external detectors, so it can power pir detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>active use 12 v dc output for powering detectors increases the nominal consumption units from bus (see technical data).</p><p>the unit can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse output.</p><p>im3-140m in 3-module is designed for switchboard mounting on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-140m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_im3-140m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-140m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_im3-140m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (28, 'en', 'bVtoFToeKU7ZaRdz15ovi', '/im3-80b', true, 'ISMybjTQz0B5S5Tetsf_k', 'IM3-80B', true, '<p>Binary input unit IM3-80B is used for the connection of 8 devices with potential-less contacts (switches, buttons, switches of other designs, PIR detectors, fire and gas detectors, etc.).</p><p>Part of the inputs can be used as a balance for alarm detectors:&nbsp;IM3-80B – inputs IN1 – IN5</p><p>Contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the unit can be NO or NC - input parameters are configured in the software iDM3.</p><p>Within the internal ESS configured in the iDM3 software, inputs must be set to balance or double balance.</p><p>The units generate a supply voltage of 12 V DC/75 mA for powering external intrusion detectors, so they can power PIR detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>Active use 12 V DC output for powering detectors increases the nominal consumption of units from BUS (see technical data).</p><p>The units can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse output.</p><p>The units are equipped with a temperature input for connecting an external two-wire temperature sensor TC/TZ (see accessories).</p><p>IM3-80B in case type B is designed for mounting into an installation box</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'IM3-80B', 'Binary input unit, 8-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":200,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132329', '3232 standard', 11, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-80b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_im3-x0b.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/IM3-80B/3D/3d.html', '', 1760099099961, 1760601105569, '/im3-80b                                                                                                                                                         im3-80b                                                                                                                                                          <p>binary input unit im3-80b is used for the connection of 8 devices with potential-less contacts (switches, buttons, switches of other designs, pir detectors, fire and gas detectors, etc.).</p><p>part of the inputs can be used as a balance for alarm detectors:&nbsp;im3-80b – inputs in1 – in5</p><p>contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the unit can be no or nc - input parameters are configured in the software idm3.</p><p>within the internal ess configured in the idm3 software, inputs must be set to balance or double balance.</p><p>the units generate a supply voltage of 12 v dc/75 ma for powering external intrusion detectors, so they can power pir detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>active use 12 v dc output for powering detectors increases the nominal consumption of units from bus (see technical data).</p><p>the units can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse output.</p><p>the units are equipped with a temperature input for connecting an external two-wire temperature sensor tc/tz (see accessories).</p><p>im3-80b in case type b is designed for mounting into an installation box</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-80b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_im3-40b_im3-80b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-80b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_im3-80b.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (27, 'en', '3LALXonvuF5vivo-X6CgL', '/im3-40b', true, 'oBaGjZM7utcTZNgCInaYY', 'IM3-40B', true, '<p>Binary input unit IM3-40B is used for the connection of 4&nbsp;devices with potential-less contacts (switches, buttons, switches of other designs, PIR detectors, fire and gas detectors, etc.).</p><p>Part of the inputs can be used as a balance for alarm detectors:&nbsp;IM3-40B – inputs IN1, IN2</p><p>Contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the unit can&nbsp;be NO or NC - input parameters are configured in the software iDM3.</p><p>Within the internal ESS configured in the iDM3 software, inputs must&nbsp;be set to balance or double balance.</p><p>The units generate a supply voltage of 12 V DC/75 mA for powering&nbsp;external intrusion detectors, so they can power PIR detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>Active use 12 V DC output for powering detectors increases the nominal&nbsp;consumption of units from BUS (see technical data).</p><p>The units can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse&nbsp;output.</p><p>The units are equipped with a temperature input for connecting an external&nbsp;two-wire temperature sensor TC/TZ (see accessories).</p><p>IM3-40B in case type B is designed for mounting into an installation&nbsp;box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'IM3-40B', 'Binary input units, 4-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":201,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132312', '3231 standard', 11, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_im3-x0b.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/IM3-40B/3D/3d.html', '', 1760098915178, 1760601120335, '/im3-40b                                                                                                                                                         im3-40b                                                                                                                                                          <p>binary input unit im3-40b is used for the connection of 4&nbsp;devices with potential-less contacts (switches, buttons, switches of other designs, pir detectors, fire and gas detectors, etc.).</p><p>part of the inputs can be used as a balance for alarm detectors:&nbsp;im3-40b – inputs in1, in2</p><p>contacts of external devices connected to the inputs of the unit can&nbsp;be no or nc - input parameters are configured in the software idm3.</p><p>within the internal ess configured in the idm3 software, inputs must&nbsp;be set to balance or double balance.</p><p>the units generate a supply voltage of 12 v dc/75 ma for powering&nbsp;external intrusion detectors, so they can power pir detectors, fire and gas detectors.</p><p>active use 12 v dc output for powering detectors increases the nominal&nbsp;consumption of units from bus (see technical data).</p><p>the units can be used for counting pulses of energy meters with pulse&nbsp;output.</p><p>the units are equipped with a temperature input for connecting an external&nbsp;two-wire temperature sensor tc/tz (see accessories).</p><p>im3-40b in case type b is designed for mounting into an installation&nbsp;box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_im3-40b_im3-80b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/im3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_im3-40b.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (33, 'en', 'ieOukYp8Cj7K0X4c_rh7D', '/ibwl3-02b-sl', true, '_jgdN2jcWziw2bskfcLwD', 'IBWL3-02B-SL', true, '<p>The IBWL3 module enables seamless integration of iNELS wireless&nbsp;devices (such as controllers and detectors) with the wired iNELS BUS&nbsp;system, enhancing control and flexibility.</p><p>The IBWL3 expands system capabilities by enabling wireless devices&nbsp;to trigger events and interact with other BUS elements, making it ideal&nbsp;for smart home and building automation.</p><p>IBWL3-02B-SL: Supports up to 8 wireless devices and includes 2 built-in&nbsp;relays for direct control of wired components.</p><p>Wireless devices are paired using unique RF addresses through the iNELS&nbsp;Design Manager (iDM3), allowing the control unit (CU3-XX) to recognize&nbsp;and create logic with BUS system elements.&nbsp;</p><p>Each IBWL3 module can connect up to 8 wireless devices.</p><p>The module is housed in a compact box design and powered directly by&nbsp;the 27V iNELS BUS, ensuring simple installation and a sleek, unified look.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'IBWL3-02B-SL', 'iNELS BUS wireless link', '[{"image":{"uploadId":205,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188193689', '9368', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', NULL, NULL, '', 1760101223995, 1760101248211, '/ibwl3-02b-sl                                                                                                                                                    ibwl3-02b-sl                                                                                                                                                     <p>the ibwl3 module enables seamless integration of inels wireless&nbsp;devices (such as controllers and detectors) with the wired inels bus&nbsp;system, enhancing control and flexibility.</p><p>the ibwl3 expands system capabilities by enabling wireless devices&nbsp;to trigger events and interact with other bus elements, making it ideal&nbsp;for smart home and building automation.</p><p>ibwl3-02b-sl: supports up to 8 wireless devices and includes 2 built-in&nbsp;relays for direct control of wired components.</p><p>wireless devices are paired using unique rf addresses through the inels&nbsp;design manager (idm3), allowing the control unit (cu3-xx) to recognize&nbsp;and create logic with bus system elements.&nbsp;</p><p>each ibwl3 module can connect up to 8 wireless devices.</p><p>the module is housed in a compact box design and powered directly by&nbsp;the 27v inels bus, ensuring simple installation and a sleek, unified look.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ibwl3-02b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ibwl3-xxb-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ibwl3-02b-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ibwl3-02b-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (35, 'en', 'krTBgDPWB1jm0B2S1xQ1X', '/dac3-04b', true, '-3tWTURGjUv-YILMsF53F', 'DAC3-04B', true, '<p>​The converter generates 4 analog voltage signals, which can be regulated according to type of controlled device, in a range 0-10 V or 1-10 V.</p><p>This is used for regulating and controlling devices that may be controlled by this signal (dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps and other types of light sources - e.g. LED panels from the assortment of ELKO Lighting, dimming actuator for LED and RGB strips RFDA-73M/ RGB, thermostatic heads, servo drives, elements for measuring and regulation and others).</p><p>Range of output voltage is adjustable in iDM3.</p><p>DAC3-04B is equipped with a temperature input for connecting a 2-wire external sensor <strong>TC / TZ.</strong></p><p><strong>DAC3-04B</strong> in version B is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'DAC3-04B', 'Digital-analog converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":204,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132572', '3257 standard', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_dac3-04b.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/DAC3-04B/3D/3d.html', '', 1760600943052, 1760600943052, '/dac3-04b                                                                                                                                                        dac3-04b                                                                                                                                                         <p>​the converter generates 4 analog voltage signals, which can be regulated according to type of controlled device, in a range 0-10 v or 1-10 v.</p><p>this is used for regulating and controlling devices that may be controlled by this signal (dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps and other types of light sources - e.g. led panels from the assortment of elko lighting, dimming actuator for led and rgb strips rfda-73m/ rgb, thermostatic heads, servo drives, elements for measuring and regulation and others).</p><p>range of output voltage is adjustable in idm3.</p><p>dac3-04b is equipped with a temperature input for connecting a 2-wire external sensor <strong>tc / tz.</strong></p><p><strong>dac3-04b</strong> in version b is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_dac3-04m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_dac3-04b.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (30, 'en', 'jSdGWcNqPXn23I9tJj_3F', '/ti3-40b', true, 'lrzXHTlVmXnbT9dGQj4xM', 'TI3-40B', true, '<p>The unit is designed for connection of up to four (TI3-40B) external temperature sensors.</p><p>Units range TI3 support the connection of the following temperature sensors:<br>- TC/TZ - 2-wire connections<br>- Ni1000, Pt1000, Pt100 - 2-wire and 3-wire connections</p><p>Used when necessary to take temperatures from different places<br>(for example large floor heating – diagonal layout of sensors, floor/ space, indoor/outdoor temperature, technological device – boiler, solar heating etc.)</p><p>Status of units indicated by green RUN LED on the front panel:<br>- if the supply voltage is connected (units are powered via the BUS), but there is no communication with the master, RUN LED is lit continuously.<br>- if the supply voltage is connected and the unit communicates via standard BUS, RUN LED flashes.</p><p>TI3-40B in version B is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'TI3-40B', 'Temperature input, 4-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":199,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132695', '3269 standard', 11, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ti3-x0b.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/TI3-40B/3D/3d.html', '', 1760099317823, 1760601062307, '/ti3-40b                                                                                                                                                         ti3-40b                                                                                                                                                          <p>the unit is designed for connection of up to four (ti3-40b) external temperature sensors.</p><p>units range ti3 support the connection of the following temperature sensors:<br>- tc/tz - 2-wire connections<br>- ni1000, pt1000, pt100 - 2-wire and 3-wire connections</p><p>used when necessary to take temperatures from different places<br>(for example large floor heating – diagonal layout of sensors, floor/ space, indoor/outdoor temperature, technological device – boiler, solar heating etc.)</p><p>status of units indicated by green run led on the front panel:<br>- if the supply voltage is connected (units are powered via the bus), but there is no communication with the master, run led is lit continuously.<br>- if the supply voltage is connected and the unit communicates via standard bus, run led flashes.</p><p>ti3-40b in version b is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ti3-40b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ti3-40b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ti3-40b.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (34, 'en', 'Ix5eoEoX2nJnwa2ttv9pV', '/adc3-60m', true, 'mU2FVq-btvobgR_4xwF6M', 'ADC3-60M', true, '<p>ADC3-60M is an analog-to-digital converter and is equipped with 6 analog inputs.</p><p>&nbsp;Analog inputs serve to connect temperature sensors or analog sensors that generate current or voltage signals.</p><p>&nbsp;The analog inputs have a resolution of a 14-bit AD converter.</p><p>&nbsp;The analog inputs have a common terminal COM.</p><p>&nbsp;Analog inputs/outputs are configurable in iDM3 independently as voltage (U) or current (I) or temperature.</p><p>&nbsp;We recommend Clima sensor as a meteostation. There are four types: five to eight outputs. The top series offers measures of: rainfall, brightness, twilight, speed of the wind, temperature and relative humidity.</p><p>&nbsp;The red LEDs in the front panel indicate exceeding the range, interruption of a sensor or overload of Uref output.</p><p>&nbsp;The temperature inputs at the top of the terminal are used to connect the following temperature sensors: TC, TZ.</p><p>&nbsp;ADC3-60M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on a DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'ADC3-60M', 'Analog-digital converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":208,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188133012', '3301 standard', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/adc3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_adc3-60m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/ADC3-60M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760101334695, 1760600968829, '/adc3-60m                                                                                                                                                        adc3-60m                                                                                                                                                         <p>adc3-60m is an analog-to-digital converter and is equipped with 6 analog inputs.</p><p>&nbsp;analog inputs serve to connect temperature sensors or analog sensors that generate current or voltage signals.</p><p>&nbsp;the analog inputs have a resolution of a 14-bit ad converter.</p><p>&nbsp;the analog inputs have a common terminal com.</p><p>&nbsp;analog inputs/outputs are configurable in idm3 independently as voltage (u) or current (i) or temperature.</p><p>&nbsp;we recommend clima sensor as a meteostation. there are four types: five to eight outputs. the top series offers measures of: rainfall, brightness, twilight, speed of the wind, temperature and relative humidity.</p><p>&nbsp;the red leds in the front panel indicate exceeding the range, interruption of a sensor or overload of uref output.</p><p>&nbsp;the temperature inputs at the top of the terminal are used to connect the following temperature sensors: tc, tz.</p><p>&nbsp;adc3-60m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on a din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/adc3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_adc3-60m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/adc3-60m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_adc3-60m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (23, 'en', 'GRau58s9WNRfRO9tlV7OV', '/lbc3-02m', true, '2l6Wf2pHs3Wn_oDC_D-tR', 'LBC3-02M', true, '<p>&nbsp;LBC3-02M is an analog 2-channel actuator designed to control dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps or other light sources controlled by signal 0(1) - 10 V DC.</p><p>&nbsp;In the iDM3, it is possible to set the output mode 0(1) - 10 V DC.</p><p>&nbsp;During analog voltage output (0)1-10 V DC control, the relay contact automatically switches the power supply to light ballast (0% = relay OFF, 1-100% = relay ON)</p><p>&nbsp;LBC3-02M contains 2 independent analog voltage outputs (0)1-10 VDC and their dependents 2 relays with potential-free contact.</p><p>&nbsp;Maximum contacts load 16 A/4000 VA/AC1.</p><p>&nbsp;Each of 2-channels is separately controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;LEDs on the front panel signal status of each channel.</p><p>&nbsp;With control buttons on the front panel, it is possible to change the status of each channel separately.</p><p>&nbsp;LBC3-02M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard/ DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'LBC3-02M', 'Dimming actuator for electronic ballasts, 2-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":196,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132688', '3268 standard', 10, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/lbc3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_lbc3-02m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/LBC3-02M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760005898696, 1760601224058, '/lbc3-02m                                                                                                                                                        lbc3-02m                                                                                                                                                         <p>&nbsp;lbc3-02m is an analog 2-channel actuator designed to control dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps or other light sources controlled by signal 0(1) - 10 v dc.</p><p>&nbsp;in the idm3, it is possible to set the output mode 0(1) - 10 v dc.</p><p>&nbsp;during analog voltage output (0)1-10 v dc control, the relay contact automatically switches the power supply to light ballast (0% = relay off, 1-100% = relay on)</p><p>&nbsp;lbc3-02m contains 2 independent analog voltage outputs (0)1-10 vdc and their dependents 2 relays with potential-free contact.</p><p>&nbsp;maximum contacts load 16 a/4000 va/ac1.</p><p>&nbsp;each of 2-channels is separately controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;leds on the front panel signal status of each channel.</p><p>&nbsp;with control buttons on the front panel, it is possible to change the status of each channel separately.</p><p>&nbsp;lbc3-02m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard/ din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/lbc3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_lbc3-02m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/lbc3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_lbc3-02m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (26, 'en', 'wAzR4ZBx_IsKmxDKCm7zR', '/da3-22m', true, 'Rk8eVplzftiTUhRNldNjF', 'DA3-22M', true, '<p>&nbsp;DA3-22M is a universal dimming 2-fold actuator enabling control of brightness intensity of dimmable light sources of the type ESL, LED and RLC with power supply 230 V.</p><p>&nbsp;DA3-22M has two MOSFET controlled outputs 230 V AC, maximum load is 2x 400 VA.</p><p>&nbsp;Option of connecting an external temperature sensor.</p><p>&nbsp;Each output channel is independently controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;Type of light source is set by a switch on the front panel.</p><p>&nbsp;Setting the min. brightness potentiometer on the front panel, flashing of different types of light sources is eliminated.</p><p>&nbsp;DA3-22M is equipped with two inputs 230 V AC, which can be controlled by mechanical switches (buttons, relays). Inputs are galvanically connected to potential L, which is permanently at the terminals IN1 and IN2.</p><p>&nbsp;By clicking on buttons on the front panel you can manually switch on or off the corresponding output.</p><p>&nbsp;Electronic overcurrent and thermal protection - switch off output in case of overload short circuit and overheating.</p><p>&nbsp;The power supply (potential L) must be protected by a protective element corresponding to the power input of the connected load, e.g. a safety fuse.</p><p>&nbsp;During installation, it is necessary to leave on each side of the actuator at least half the module space for better cooling.</p><p>&nbsp;DA3-22M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'DA3-22M', 'Universal dimming actuator, 2-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":197,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132626', '3262 standard', 10, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-22m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_da3-22m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/DA3-22M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760011303792, 1760601143173, '/da3-22m                                                                                                                                                         da3-22m                                                                                                                                                          <p>&nbsp;da3-22m is a universal dimming 2-fold actuator enabling control of brightness intensity of dimmable light sources of the type esl, led and rlc with power supply 230 v.</p><p>&nbsp;da3-22m has two mosfet controlled outputs 230 v ac, maximum load is 2x 400 va.</p><p>&nbsp;option of connecting an external temperature sensor.</p><p>&nbsp;each output channel is independently controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;type of light source is set by a switch on the front panel.</p><p>&nbsp;setting the min. brightness potentiometer on the front panel, flashing of different types of light sources is eliminated.</p><p>&nbsp;da3-22m is equipped with two inputs 230 v ac, which can be controlled by mechanical switches (buttons, relays). inputs are galvanically connected to potential l, which is permanently at the terminals in1 and in2.</p><p>&nbsp;by clicking on buttons on the front panel you can manually switch on or off the corresponding output.</p><p>&nbsp;electronic overcurrent and thermal protection - switch off output in case of overload short circuit and overheating.</p><p>&nbsp;the power supply (potential l) must be protected by a protective element corresponding to the power input of the connected load, e.g. a safety fuse.</p><p>&nbsp;during installation, it is necessary to leave on each side of the actuator at least half the module space for better cooling.</p><p>&nbsp;da3-22m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-22m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_da3-22m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-22m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_da3-22m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (49, 'en', '2cIJfUSLMb3linbfTbE4r', '/grt3-270', true, 'JXKjiYB7QnmZEAMYpKM1c', 'GRT3-270', true, '<p>Glass room thermo-regulator GRT3-270 is part of a comprehensive range&nbsp;of glass iNELS control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (GRMS) and serves to regulate the temperature in the room.</p><p>Comes with a bigger display and a new design compared to the previous&nbsp;version GRT3-50.</p><p>GRT3-270 thermo-regulator has a display for displaying the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. To adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>GRT3-270 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.</p><p>Thermo-regulator GRT3-270 also features touch buttons whose function&nbsp;can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/&nbsp;cooling or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>The thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>The glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the iNELS&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (GRT3-270/B) and white (GRT3-270/W) versions.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>GRT3-270 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GRT3-270', 'Glass room thermo-regulator', '[{"image":{"uploadId":399,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191555', '9155 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-270/share_dokumentace/en/manual_grt3-70_270.pdf', '', '', '', 1763990261204, 1763990261204, '/grt3-270                                                                                                                                                        grt3-270                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass room thermo-regulator grt3-270 is part of a comprehensive range&nbsp;of glass inels control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (grms) and serves to regulate the temperature in the room.</p><p>comes with a bigger display and a new design compared to the previous&nbsp;version grt3-50.</p><p>grt3-270 thermo-regulator has a display for displaying the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. to adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>grt3-270 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.</p><p>thermo-regulator grt3-270 also features touch buttons whose function&nbsp;can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/&nbsp;cooling or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>the thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>the glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the inels&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (grt3-270/b) and white (grt3-270/w) versions.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>grt3-270 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-270/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_grt3-70_grt3-270.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-270/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_grt3-70.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (126, 'en', 'z28rIiC1AcwGMM8p8Udib', '/rfmd-200', true, 'h0tcqy7L7cFEoLHCILQ_v', 'RFMD-200', true, '<p>The motion detector PIR is used to detect the presence of persons moving&nbsp;inside the building interior.</p><p>Use:</p><p>in combination with a switching unit for automatic control of lighting&nbsp;or triggering an alarm.</p><p>by means of the Smart RF gate, detection can be displayed on your&nbsp;smartphone in the form of notification; alarms are stored in the&nbsp;history, which is visualized in the iNELS application.</p><p>in combination with hotel elements (HRESK) it can serve as a room occupancy&nbsp;sensor</p><p>Sensitivity settings of the PIR detector for eliminating unwanted triggering.&nbsp;</p><p>Option of activation/deactivation of the LED indicator on the detector cover.</p><p>Power supply: 2x 1.5 V AA batteries, the battery life is around 1 year.</p><p>“Low Battery” Alerts by the double LED flashing or on iHC App.</p><p>The detectors are compatible with switching components marked&nbsp;with the RFIO2 communication protocol and the eLAN-Wireless system&nbsp;components.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFMD-200', 'Motion detector', '[{"image":{"uploadId":795,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189194', '8919', 31, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfmd-200/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfmd-200_a4_en-cz.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/DETEKTORY/RFMD-200/3D/3d.html', '', 1769170842104, 1769170842104, '/rfmd-200                                                                                                                                                        rfmd-200                                                                                                                                                         <p>the motion detector pir is used to detect the presence of persons moving&nbsp;inside the building interior.</p><p>use:</p><p>in combination with a switching unit for automatic control of lighting&nbsp;or triggering an alarm.</p><p>by means of the smart rf gate, detection can be displayed on your&nbsp;smartphone in the form of notification; alarms are stored in the&nbsp;history, which is visualized in the inels application.</p><p>in combination with hotel elements (hresk) it can serve as a room occupancy&nbsp;sensor</p><p>sensitivity settings of the pir detector for eliminating unwanted triggering.&nbsp;</p><p>option of activation/deactivation of the led indicator on the detector cover.</p><p>power supply: 2x 1.5 v aa batteries, the battery life is around 1 year.</p><p>“low battery” alerts by the double led flashing or on ihc app.</p><p>the detectors are compatible with switching components marked&nbsp;with the rfio2 communication protocol and the elan-wireless system&nbsp;components.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfmd-200/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfmd-200.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfmd-200/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfmd-200.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (25, 'en', 'Pdy_0FLttgon3dEMty7B6', '/da3-66m', true, 'lwSbvZhqbbK46NUF7gScA', 'DA3-66M', true, '<p>DA3-66M is a universal dimming 6-channel actuator, which is used to control&nbsp;the brightness of dimmable light sources such as ESL, LED and RLC with&nbsp;230 V power supply.</p><p>The DA3-66M has 6 semiconductor-controlled 230 V AC outputs. The maximum&nbsp;possible load is 150 VA for each channel.</p><p>The individual outputs of the dimmer can be connected in parallel and thus&nbsp;increase the maximum output load at the expense of the number of outputs.</p><p>Each output channel is independently controllable and addressable.</p><p>By setting min. brightness, the flickering of different types of light sources&nbsp;is eliminated.</p><p>Min. brightness and type of load are performed using SW IDM.</p><p>Use the control buttons on the front panel to manually control the output.</p><p>The actuator is equipped with electronic overcurrent and thermal protection,&nbsp;which switches off the output in case of overload, short circuit, or overheating.</p><p>The dimmer has 6 galvanically separated inputs which can be used both to&nbsp;control the dimmer and as a binary input to the INELS system.</p><p>The device supply (potential L) must be protected with a safety device&nbsp;corresponding to the power input of the connected load, e.g. with a quick-release fuse.</p><p>During installation, it is necessary to leave at least half a module of free&nbsp;space on each side of the actuator for better cooling.</p><p>DA3-66M is in 6-MODULE version and is intended for mounting in a switchboard&nbsp;on DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'DA3-66M', 'Dimmer Actuator, 6-channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":195,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188182065', '8206 standard', 10, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-66m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_da3-66m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/DA3-66M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760009389918, 1760601173572, '/da3-66m                                                                                                                                                         da3-66m                                                                                                                                                          <p>da3-66m is a universal dimming 6-channel actuator, which is used to control&nbsp;the brightness of dimmable light sources such as esl, led and rlc with&nbsp;230 v power supply.</p><p>the da3-66m has 6 semiconductor-controlled 230 v ac outputs. the maximum&nbsp;possible load is 150 va for each channel.</p><p>the individual outputs of the dimmer can be connected in parallel and thus&nbsp;increase the maximum output load at the expense of the number of outputs.</p><p>each output channel is independently controllable and addressable.</p><p>by setting min. brightness, the flickering of different types of light sources&nbsp;is eliminated.</p><p>min. brightness and type of load are performed using sw idm.</p><p>use the control buttons on the front panel to manually control the output.</p><p>the actuator is equipped with electronic overcurrent and thermal protection,&nbsp;which switches off the output in case of overload, short circuit, or overheating.</p><p>the dimmer has 6 galvanically separated inputs which can be used both to&nbsp;control the dimmer and as a binary input to the inels system.</p><p>the device supply (potential l) must be protected with a safety device&nbsp;corresponding to the power input of the connected load, e.g. with a quick-release fuse.</p><p>during installation, it is necessary to leave at least half a module of free&nbsp;space on each side of the actuator for better cooling.</p><p>da3-66m is in 6-module version and is intended for mounting in a switchboard&nbsp;on din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-66m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_da3-66m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-66m/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_confirmity_da3_66m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (62, 'en', '0JQMNkP-6a77_53amgn57', '/gsb3-40', true, 'kBvtrWRmeQC7NskZ0pVkl', 'GSB3-40', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers GSB3-XXX are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40, GSB3-60, and GSB3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the GSB3-240, GSB3-260, and GSB3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>GSB3-40 and GSB3-240 are equipped with four, GSB3-60, GSB3-260 six and GSB3-&nbsp;90, GSB3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/B) and white (GSB3-XXX/W) versions.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue LED indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'GSB3-40', 'Glass switch button', '[{"image":{"uploadId":400,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132954', '3295 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764329925724, 1764329943065, '/gsb3-40                                                                                                                                                         gsb3-40                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass touch controllers gsb3-xxx are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40, gsb3-60, and gsb3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the gsb3-240, gsb3-260, and gsb3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>gsb3-40 and gsb3-240 are equipped with four, gsb3-60, gsb3-260 six and gsb3-&nbsp;90, gsb3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/b) and white (gsb3-xxx/w) versions.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue led indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-40.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/eu_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-40_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (67, 'en', '0BAafsu1VjN6_A2Mi1Pwo', '/iou3-108m', true, '6MOgSDySLNHsnhy1qoIR9', 'IOU3 -108M', true, '<p>&nbsp;IOU3-108M is a combined actuator equipped with 8 binary inputs, 2 temperature inputs and 8 independent relays with switching potential-free contacts</p><p>&nbsp;Binary inputs IOU3-108M are used to connect up to 8 devices with a potentialfree contact (such as switches, buttons, burglar alarms and fire detectors or others).</p><p>&nbsp;The unit can be used to read pulses from energy meters with a pulse output.</p><p>&nbsp;The temperature inputs support the connection of the following temperature sensors: TC / TZ - 2-wire connection</p><p>&nbsp;They are used in cases where it is necessary to measure the temperature, eg floor/space, indoor/outdoor temperature, technological equipment - boiler rooms, solar heating, etc.</p><p>&nbsp;The maximum load capacity of the contacts is 10 A / 2500 VA / AC1.</p><p>&nbsp;Each of the output is individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;The relays are divided into four pairs, where each pair switches its common potential.</p><p>&nbsp;The actuator is designed for switching up to eight different appliances and loads via a relay output (potential-free contact).</p><p>&nbsp;IOU3-108M in 6-MODULE design is designed for mounting in a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'IOU3 -108M', 'Universal unit with 10 inputs and 8 outputs', '[{"image":{"uploadId":490,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188181884', '8188 standard', 17, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/iou3-108m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_iou3-108m.pdf', '', '', '', 1764332579905, 1764332579905, '/iou3-108m                                                                                                                                                       iou3 -108m                                                                                                                                                       <p>&nbsp;iou3-108m is a combined actuator equipped with 8 binary inputs, 2 temperature inputs and 8 independent relays with switching potential-free contacts</p><p>&nbsp;binary inputs iou3-108m are used to connect up to 8 devices with a potentialfree contact (such as switches, buttons, burglar alarms and fire detectors or others).</p><p>&nbsp;the unit can be used to read pulses from energy meters with a pulse output.</p><p>&nbsp;the temperature inputs support the connection of the following temperature sensors: tc / tz - 2-wire connection</p><p>&nbsp;they are used in cases where it is necessary to measure the temperature, eg floor/space, indoor/outdoor temperature, technological equipment - boiler rooms, solar heating, etc.</p><p>&nbsp;the maximum load capacity of the contacts is 10 a / 2500 va / ac1.</p><p>&nbsp;each of the output is individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;the relays are divided into four pairs, where each pair switches its common potential.</p><p>&nbsp;the actuator is designed for switching up to eight different appliances and loads via a relay output (potential-free contact).</p><p>&nbsp;iou3-108m in 6-module design is designed for mounting in a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/iou3-108m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_iou3-108m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/iou3-108m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_iou3-108m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (24, 'en', 'jzcFWevMXqz9gtaerEeY_', '/da3-03mrgbw', true, '_Tl1gOCo2hwxekYeM4NgD', 'DA3-03M/RGBW', true, '<p>The dimmer for LED strips is used for independent control of 12 channels,&nbsp;so it can be connected to, for example:</p><p>3 RGBW led strips</p><p>3 RGB led strips + 2 single colour strips</p><p>12 single colour LED strips</p><p>The 3-module design of the device with mounting in the switchboard&nbsp;allows the connection of a dimmable load of 3x 15 A or 12x 3.75 A,&nbsp;which represents, for example: 3 pieces of RGBW LED strips 24V&nbsp;20W/m = max 18m.</p><p>The dimmer is controlled by the central unit of the iNELS system.</p><p>The power supply of the LED strip is in the range of 0-50V DC.</p><p>Each of the output channels is separately controllable and addressable.&nbsp;</p><p>The actuator is equipped with electronic thermal protection, which&nbsp;switches off the output in case of overheating.</p><p>During installation, it is necessary to leave at least half a module of free&nbsp;space on each side of the actuator for better cooling.</p><p>DA3-03M/RGBW in 3-MODUL design is intended for installation in a switchboard&nbsp;on an EN60715 DIN rail.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'DA3-03M/RGBW', 'Dimming actuator for RGBW strips', '[{"image":{"uploadId":194,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184632', '8463 standard', 10, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-03m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_da3-03m_rgdw_1jaz-en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/DA3-03M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760009228182, 1760601189514, '/da3-03mrgbw                                                                                                                                                     da3-03m/rgbw                                                                                                                                                     <p>the dimmer for led strips is used for independent control of 12 channels,&nbsp;so it can be connected to, for example:</p><p>3 rgbw led strips</p><p>3 rgb led strips + 2 single colour strips</p><p>12 single colour led strips</p><p>the 3-module design of the device with mounting in the switchboard&nbsp;allows the connection of a dimmable load of 3x 15 a or 12x 3.75 a,&nbsp;which represents, for example: 3 pieces of rgbw led strips 24v&nbsp;20w/m = max 18m.</p><p>the dimmer is controlled by the central unit of the inels system.</p><p>the power supply of the led strip is in the range of 0-50v dc.</p><p>each of the output channels is separately controllable and addressable.&nbsp;</p><p>the actuator is equipped with electronic thermal protection, which&nbsp;switches off the output in case of overheating.</p><p>during installation, it is necessary to leave at least half a module of free&nbsp;space on each side of the actuator for better cooling.</p><p>da3-03m/rgbw in 3-modul design is intended for installation in a switchboard&nbsp;on an en60715 din rail.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-03m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_da3-03m_rgbw.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/da3-03m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_da3-03m_rgbw.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (22, 'en', 'kwKDxO-IdaiCJ12PMJhi6', '/ja3-014me', true, 'aillD39lMA6Jo1blWnJ6t', 'JA3-014M/E', true, '<p>JA3-014M/E is an actuator designed for controlling rollers, shutters,&nbsp;blinds, awnings, garage doors, entrance gates, etc.</p><p>It controls electric drives that are controlled in two directions and&nbsp;have a built-in limit switch.</p><p>The unit''s status is indicated by the green RUN LED on the front panel&nbsp;<br>- if the BUS voltage is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;BUS with the master, the LED RUN is on continuously.<br>- if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by BUS,&nbsp;the LED RUN flashes.</p><p>The software blocking of output relay contacts can be secure using&nbsp;the iNELS Design Manager software.</p><p>JA3-014M/E is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>JA3-014M/E in 6-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard&nbsp;on DIN rail EN60715.</p><p>JA3-014M/E is an economical option without manual control buttons&nbsp;on the front panel and status LEDs for the relay output. (possibility to&nbsp;control via iDM software).</p><p>The unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'JA3-014M/E', 'Shutter actuator, 14 channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":185,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189491', '8949 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ja3-014m_ja3-014m-e_a4_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/JA3-014M_E/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922484962, 1760601248670, '/ja3-014me                                                                                                                                                       ja3-014m/e                                                                                                                                                       <p>ja3-014m/e is an actuator designed for controlling rollers, shutters,&nbsp;blinds, awnings, garage doors, entrance gates, etc.</p><p>it controls electric drives that are controlled in two directions and&nbsp;have a built-in limit switch.</p><p>the unit''s status is indicated by the green run led on the front panel&nbsp;<br>- if the bus voltage is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;bus with the master, the led run is on continuously.<br>- if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by bus,&nbsp;the led run flashes.</p><p>the software blocking of output relay contacts can be secure using&nbsp;the inels design manager software.</p><p>ja3-014m/e is normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>ja3-014m/e in 6-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard&nbsp;on din rail en60715.</p><p>ja3-014m/e is an economical option without manual control buttons&nbsp;on the front panel and status leds for the relay output. (possibility to&nbsp;control via idm software).</p><p>the unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ja3-014m-e.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ja3-014m_e.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (50, 'en', 'k0TqYQWC3J96DUCIuLWFB', '/grt3-70', true, 'IhwzX-6tcG6e6axai_pK-', 'GRT3-70', true, '<p>Glass room thermo-regulator GRT3-70 is part of a comprehensive range&nbsp;of glass iNELS control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (GRMS) and serves to regulate the temperature in the room.</p><p>Comes with a bigger display and a new design compared to the previous&nbsp;version GRT3-50.</p><p>GRT3-70 thermo-regulator has a display for displaying the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. To adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>GRT3-70 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.</p><p>Thermo-regulator GRT3-70 also features touch buttons whose function&nbsp;can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/&nbsp;cooling or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>The thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>The glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the iNELS&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (GRT3-70/B) and white (GRT3-70/W) versions.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>GRT3-70 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GRT3-70', 'Glass room thermo-regulator', '[{"image":{"uploadId":405,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191531', '9153 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-70/share_dokumentace/en/manual_grt3-70_270.pdf', '', '', '', 1763990344692, 1763991576537, '/grt3-70                                                                                                                                                         grt3-70                                                                                                                                                          <p>glass room thermo-regulator grt3-70 is part of a comprehensive range&nbsp;of glass inels control units for apartments, and guest room management&nbsp;systems (grms) and serves to regulate the temperature in the room.</p><p>comes with a bigger display and a new design compared to the previous&nbsp;version grt3-50.</p><p>grt3-70 thermo-regulator has a display for displaying the current room&nbsp;temperature and desired temperature. to adjust the required temperature,&nbsp;it is possible to use the touch buttons with symbols "-" and "+".</p><p>grt3-70 is also suitable for controlling fan coils and fan speed can be&nbsp;easily adjusted by using the touch buttons with symbols.</p><p>thermo-regulator grt3-70 also features touch buttons whose function&nbsp;can be adjusted by software, for example, fan coil on/off, heating/&nbsp;cooling or comfort temperature for heating or cooling.</p><p>the thermo-regulator is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor&nbsp;for ambient temperature measurement.</p><p>the glass room thermo-regulator is a design component of the inels&nbsp;system and is available in elegant black (grt3-70/b) and white (grt3-70/w) versions.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated.</p><p>grt3-70 is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-70/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_grt3-70_grt3-270.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/grt3-70/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_grt3-70.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (68, 'en', '5Qqrq23mkM6QixnkSGnMS', '/fa3-612m', true, '93ogALdvhzPjFT0wLZ3Dq', 'FA3-612M', true, '<p>FA3-612M is a unit (actuator) designed to control fan coil units using analogue/digital inputs and analog/relay outputs.</p><p>&nbsp;Analog inputs for temperature, voltage or current measurement (URef reference voltage can also be used).</p><p>&nbsp;The digital inputs are galvanically isolated with positive logic (Sink) in the 24-230 V AC/DC voltage range.</p><p>&nbsp;Analog outputs 0-10 V.</p><p>&nbsp;Connection to the installation BUS.</p><p>&nbsp;Buttons for closing/opening the valve, fan and heating relay.</p><p>&nbsp;The LEDs on the front panel indicate FAN, RE, VALVE1, VALVE2, OVERRANGE, and OVERLOAD status.</p><p>&nbsp;FA3-612M in 6-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, o EAN code n DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'FA3-612M', 'Fan coil control actuator', '[{"image":{"uploadId":488,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188135276', '3527 standard', 17, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/fa3-612m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_fa3-612m.pdf', '', '', '', 1764332668731, 1764332668731, '/fa3-612m                                                                                                                                                        fa3-612m                                                                                                                                                         <p>fa3-612m is a unit (actuator) designed to control fan coil units using analogue/digital inputs and analog/relay outputs.</p><p>&nbsp;analog inputs for temperature, voltage or current measurement (uref reference voltage can also be used).</p><p>&nbsp;the digital inputs are galvanically isolated with positive logic (sink) in the 24-230 v ac/dc voltage range.</p><p>&nbsp;analog outputs 0-10 v.</p><p>&nbsp;connection to the installation bus.</p><p>&nbsp;buttons for closing/opening the valve, fan and heating relay.</p><p>&nbsp;the leds on the front panel indicate fan, re, valve1, valve2, overrange, and overload status.</p><p>&nbsp;fa3-612m in 6-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, o ean code n din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/fa3-612m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_fa3-612m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/fa3-612m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_fa3-612m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (72, 'en', 'dNTUNHCeNQlQ3krK9hiYX', '/mounting-boxes-for-ins8sq', true, 'P6Uaie0-dT_HXCd0s2r-L', 'MOUNTING BOXES FOR INS8SQ', true, '<p>the mounting box for the touch panel can be built into the wall or mounted to the wall surface</p><p>Code of product - Type of box</p><p>BOX-INS8Q - Flush mount box </p><p>BOX-INS8W - On-wall mount box</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'MOUNTING BOXES FOR INS8SQ', 'Accessories for control panels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":500,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764334987492, 1764334987492, '/mounting-boxes-for-ins8sq                                                                                                                                       mounting boxes for ins8sq                                                                                                                                        <p>the mounting box for the touch panel can be built into the wall or mounted to the wall surface</p><p>code of product - type of box</p><p>box-ins8q - flush mount box </p><p>box-ins8w - on-wall mount box</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (21, 'en', '-QELs9Dz5DFYYBrktGzp4', '/ja3-014m', true, 'ytdt7PJ9TX_Mlj3o4uj_G', 'JA3-014M', true, '<p>JA3-014M is an actuator designed for controlling rollers, shutters,&nbsp;blinds, awnings, garage doors, entrance gates, etc.</p><p>It controls electric drives that are controlled in two directions and&nbsp;have a built-in limit switch.</p><p>The unit''s status is indicated by the green RUN LED on the front panel&nbsp;<br>- if the BUS voltage is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;BUS with the master, the LED RUN is on continuously.<br>- if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by BUS,&nbsp;the LED RUN flashes.</p><p>The status of the output contacts is indicated by the Up/ Down LED:<br>- when the blind/roller blind is moving up/down, the corresponding&nbsp;LED lights up.<br>- if the number of switching operations per minute is exceeded, the&nbsp;corresponding LED flashes.</p><p>The contact status of each relay JA3-014M can be changed separately and&nbsp;manually by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>The software blocking of output relay contacts can be secure using&nbsp;the iNELS Design Manager software.</p><p>JA3-014M is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>JA3-014M in 6-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard&nbsp;on DIN rail EN60715.</p><p>The unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. The sync inputs are COM 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6&nbsp;and 7 against the N terminal.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'JA3-014M', 'Shutter actuator, 14 channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":188,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191258', '9125 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ja3-014m_ja3-014m-e_a4_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/JA3-014M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922440937, 1760601263800, '/ja3-014m                                                                                                                                                        ja3-014m                                                                                                                                                         <p>ja3-014m is an actuator designed for controlling rollers, shutters,&nbsp;blinds, awnings, garage doors, entrance gates, etc.</p><p>it controls electric drives that are controlled in two directions and&nbsp;have a built-in limit switch.</p><p>the unit''s status is indicated by the green run led on the front panel&nbsp;<br>- if the bus voltage is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;bus with the master, the led run is on continuously.<br>- if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by bus,&nbsp;the led run flashes.</p><p>the status of the output contacts is indicated by the up/ down led:<br>- when the blind/roller blind is moving up/down, the corresponding&nbsp;led lights up.<br>- if the number of switching operations per minute is exceeded, the&nbsp;corresponding led flashes.</p><p>the contact status of each relay ja3-014m can be changed separately and&nbsp;manually by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>the software blocking of output relay contacts can be secure using&nbsp;the inels design manager software.</p><p>ja3-014m is normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>ja3-014m in 6-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard&nbsp;on din rail en60715.</p><p>the unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. the sync inputs are com 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6&nbsp;and 7 against the n terminal.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ja3-014m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ja3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ja3-014m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (19, 'en', 'NShLONFsH0H9C63o_TmgK', '/sa3-022m', true, '1bzO6Mggj8n96YNDuTn2J', 'SA3-022M', true, '<p>Equipped with 22 relay outputs (of which 1x changeover contact&nbsp;– roller blinds, blinds).</p><p>&nbsp;Switch lighting and socket circuits (6 A and 10 A relay) with common potential at the "COMx" terminal.</p><p>&nbsp;Control of roller blinds, blinds (24 - 230 V AC/DC).</p><p>&nbsp;Relay control of the fan coil unit - heating/cooling, 3 fan speeds (24 - 230 V AC/DC).</p><p>&nbsp;Connection to BUS, communication with CU3.</p><p>&nbsp;The front panel LEDs indicate the status of each output.</p><p>&nbsp;SA3-022M in design 6-MODULE is designed to be mounted into a switchboard, onto DIN rail EN60715.</p><p><strong>TECHNICAL PARAMETERS</strong></p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'SA3-022M', 'Switching Actuator, 22-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":192,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188135269', '3526 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-022m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/SA3-022M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922317328, 1760601310518, '/sa3-022m                                                                                                                                                        sa3-022m                                                                                                                                                         <p>equipped with 22 relay outputs (of which 1x changeover contact&nbsp;– roller blinds, blinds).</p><p>&nbsp;switch lighting and socket circuits (6 a and 10 a relay) with common potential at the "comx" terminal.</p><p>&nbsp;control of roller blinds, blinds (24 - 230 v ac/dc).</p><p>&nbsp;relay control of the fan coil unit - heating/cooling, 3 fan speeds (24 - 230 v ac/dc).</p><p>&nbsp;connection to bus, communication with cu3.</p><p>&nbsp;the front panel leds indicate the status of each output.</p><p>&nbsp;sa3-022m in design 6-module is designed to be mounted into a switchboard, onto din rail en60715.</p><p><strong>technical parameters</strong></p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-022m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-022m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-022m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (51, 'en', 'L_HxJrJjxWhmik1xpPCGf', '/gsb3-290s', true, 'DgY0OTrJ3oaJ1YAQUXxhC', 'GSB3-290/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-XX/S are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the GSB3-240/S, GSB3-260/S, and GSB3-290/S models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, GSB3-240/S are equipped with four, GSB3-60/S, GSB3-260/S six&nbsp;and GSB3-90/S, GSB3-290/S nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/&nbsp;TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/SB) and white (GSB3-XXX/SW) versions.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>In addition to all the features in symbol models. The glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the SBP/SWP version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>SWP/SBP models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-290/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":397,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189675', '8967 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290s/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763992215668, 1763992215668, '/gsb3-290s                                                                                                                                                       gsb3-290/s                                                                                                                                                       <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-xx/s are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the gsb3-240/s, gsb3-260/s, and gsb3-290/s models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, gsb3-240/s are equipped with four, gsb3-60/s, gsb3-260/s six&nbsp;and gsb3-90/s, gsb3-290/s nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/&nbsp;tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/sb) and white (gsb3-xxx/sw) versions.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>in addition to all the features in symbol models. the glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the sbp/swp version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>swp/sbp models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290s/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290s/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-290_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (127, 'en', 'PWtKoamjaNgEymfeTgPYa', '/rfwd-100', true, 'vELTr4iKLBuf9j3Fgr3Py', 'RFWD-100', true, '<p>The Window/Door detector is used to detect openings where activation&nbsp;occurs when the magnet and the sensor become separated.</p><p>Use:<br>- in combination with the switching unit for automatic light control&nbsp;(cellar, garage, etc.).<br>- by means of the Smart RF gate, detection can be displayed on your&nbsp;smartphone in the form of a notification; alarms are stored in the&nbsp;history, which is visualized in the iNELS application.</p><p>Anti-tamper function: an alarm is triggered if there is an unauthorized&nbsp;interference to the detector.</p><p>Power supply: 1x 3 V CR 2032 battery, the battery life is around 1 year,&nbsp;thanks to the ability to turn off the LED indicator it is possible to extend&nbsp;up to 3 years.</p><p>“Low Battery” Alerts on Your iNELS App.</p><p>The detectors are compatible with switching components marked&nbsp;with the RFIO2 communication protocol and the eLAN-RF system&nbsp;components.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFWD-100', 'Window / Door detector', '[{"image":{"uploadId":788,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188150279', '5027', 31, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfwd-100/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfwd-100.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/DETEKTORY/RFWD-100/3D/3d.html', '', 1769170936420, 1769170936420, '/rfwd-100                                                                                                                                                        rfwd-100                                                                                                                                                         <p>the window/door detector is used to detect openings where activation&nbsp;occurs when the magnet and the sensor become separated.</p><p>use:<br>- in combination with the switching unit for automatic light control&nbsp;(cellar, garage, etc.).<br>- by means of the smart rf gate, detection can be displayed on your&nbsp;smartphone in the form of a notification; alarms are stored in the&nbsp;history, which is visualized in the inels application.</p><p>anti-tamper function: an alarm is triggered if there is an unauthorized&nbsp;interference to the detector.</p><p>power supply: 1x 3 v cr 2032 battery, the battery life is around 1 year,&nbsp;thanks to the ability to turn off the led indicator it is possible to extend&nbsp;up to 3 years.</p><p>“low battery” alerts on your inels app.</p><p>the detectors are compatible with switching components marked&nbsp;with the rfio2 communication protocol and the elan-rf system&nbsp;components.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfwd-100/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfwd-100.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/detektory/rfwd-100/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfwd-100_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (73, 'en', 'KlRxEQlHp8_LV84kC8Co5', '/mounting-box-for-ins10q', true, 'ot9yC75qysaN47DKnp3p-', 'MOUNTING BOX FOR INS10Q', true, '<p>box for mounting the EST10 touch control panel box into the wall</p><p><strong>Code of product - Type of box</strong></p><p>BOX-INS10Q - Flush mount box&nbsp;</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'MOUNTING BOX FOR INS10Q', 'Accessories for control panels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":498,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764335044521, 1764335044521, '/mounting-box-for-ins10q                                                                                                                                         mounting box for ins10q                                                                                                                                          <p>box for mounting the est10 touch control panel box into the wall</p><p><strong>code of product - type of box</strong></p><p>box-ins10q - flush mount box&nbsp;</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (18, 'en', '1hMyuXcZ9Y66cJ0ltTWyA', '/sa3-014me', true, '7i_uTKU5RcwDQdYujQ1rY', 'SA3-014M/E', true, '<p>SA3-014M/E is a switching actuator containing 14 independent relays&nbsp;with NO potentialless contacts, with the fact that switches the same&nbsp;potential. The maximum loadability of contacts is 10A/2500 VA/AC1.</p><p>Each of the fourteen output contacts is individually controllable and&nbsp;addressable. Actuator SA3-014M/E is powered by a bus voltage 27V DC.</p><p>The unit’s status is indicated by the green RUN LED on the front panel&nbsp;</p><p>if the bus supply is connected, but there is no communication via BUS&nbsp;with the master, the LED RUN is on continuously.</p><p>if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by BUS,&nbsp;the LED RUN fl ashes.</p><p>The contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually&nbsp;by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>The unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. The sync inputs are COM 1, 3, 5, 7,&nbsp;9, 11, and 13 against the N terminal.</p><p>SA3-014M/E is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.&nbsp;SA3-014M/E in design 6-MODULE is designed to be mounted into&nbsp;a switchboard, onto DIN rail EN60715.</p><p>SA3-014M/E is an economic option without manual control buttons on&nbsp;the front panel and status LEDs for the relay output. (possibility to control&nbsp;via iDM software).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'SA3-014M/E', 'Switching actuator, 14 channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":186,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189187', '8918 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-014m_014m-e_bus_a4_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/SA3-014M_E/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922245024, 1760601336306, '/sa3-014me                                                                                                                                                       sa3-014m/e                                                                                                                                                       <p>sa3-014m/e is a switching actuator containing 14 independent relays&nbsp;with no potentialless contacts, with the fact that switches the same&nbsp;potential. the maximum loadability of contacts is 10a/2500 va/ac1.</p><p>each of the fourteen output contacts is individually controllable and&nbsp;addressable. actuator sa3-014m/e is powered by a bus voltage 27v dc.</p><p>the unit’s status is indicated by the green run led on the front panel&nbsp;</p><p>if the bus supply is connected, but there is no communication via bus&nbsp;with the master, the led run is on continuously.</p><p>if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by bus,&nbsp;the led run fl ashes.</p><p>the contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually&nbsp;by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>the unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. the sync inputs are com 1, 3, 5, 7,&nbsp;9, 11, and 13 against the n terminal.</p><p>sa3-014m/e is normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.&nbsp;sa3-014m/e in design 6-module is designed to be mounted into&nbsp;a switchboard, onto din rail en60715.</p><p>sa3-014m/e is an economic option without manual control buttons on&nbsp;the front panel and status leds for the relay output. (possibility to control&nbsp;via idm software).</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-14m-e.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m_e/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-014m_e.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (17, 'en', 'cY7kkdtoKRIWPlKWpmxkE', '/sa3-014m', true, '-epbQOJ0Z2hbXvz0FIZfM', 'SA3-014M', true, '<p>SA3-014M is a switching actuator containing 14 independent relays&nbsp;with NO potentialless contacts, with the fact that switches the&nbsp;same potential.</p><p>Maximal loadability of contacts is 10A/2500 VA/AC1.</p><p>Each of the fourteen output contacts is individually controllable and&nbsp;addressable.</p><p>Actuator SA3-014M is powered by a bus voltage 27V DC.&nbsp;</p><p>The unit’s status is indicated by the green RUN LED on the front panel</p><p>if the bus supply is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;BUS with the master, the LED RUN is on continuously.</p><p>if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by BUS, the LED RUN fl ashes.</p><p>The unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. The sync inputs are COM 1, 3, 5, 7,&nbsp;9, 11 and 13 against the N terminal.</p><p>SA3-014M is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>SA3-014M in design 6-MODULE is designed to be mounted into a switchboard,&nbsp;on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760090400000, '[]', 'SA3-014M', 'Switching actuator, 14 channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":187,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191241', '9124 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-014m_014m-e_bus_a4_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/SA3-014M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922173290, 1760601374263, '/sa3-014m                                                                                                                                                        sa3-014m                                                                                                                                                         <p>sa3-014m is a switching actuator containing 14 independent relays&nbsp;with no potentialless contacts, with the fact that switches the&nbsp;same potential.</p><p>maximal loadability of contacts is 10a/2500 va/ac1.</p><p>each of the fourteen output contacts is individually controllable and&nbsp;addressable.</p><p>actuator sa3-014m is powered by a bus voltage 27v dc.&nbsp;</p><p>the unit’s status is indicated by the green run led on the front panel</p><p>if the bus supply is connected, but there is no communication via&nbsp;bus with the master, the led run is on continuously.</p><p>if the bus voltage is connected and the unit communicates by bus, the led run fl ashes.</p><p>the unit has synchronized closing and opening of the relay in the zero&nbsp;voltage of the sinusoidal waveform. the sync inputs are com 1, 3, 5, 7,&nbsp;9, 11 and 13 against the n terminal.</p><p>sa3-014m is normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.&nbsp;</p><p>sa3-014m in design 6-module is designed to be mounted into a switchboard,&nbsp;on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-014m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-014m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-014m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (36, 'en', 'F_Ai3GVwm1Qkqr3IhV4XV', '/dac3-04m', true, 'gS8_Px2xe4ZRLDEA7qqSF', 'DAC3-04M', true, '<p>DAC3-04M is a converter from a digital signal to an analog voltage signal.</p><p>The converter generates 4 analog voltage signals, which can be operated, according to the type of controlled device, in a range 0-10 V or 1-10 V.</p><p>This is used for regulating and controlling devices that may be controlled by this signal (dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps and other types of light sources - e.g. LED panels from the assortment of ELKO Lighting, dimming actuator for LED and RGB strips RFDA-73M/ RGB, thermostatic heads, servo drives, elements for measuring and regulation and others).</p><p>The range of output voltage is adjustable in iDM3.</p><p>The converter is equipped with a temperature input for connecting a 2-wire external sensor TC/TZ (see accessories).</p><p>DAC3-04M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'DAC3-04M', 'Digital-analog converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":207,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132565', '3256 standard', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_dac3-04m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/DAC3-04M/3D/3d.html', '', 1760601855768, 1760601877656, '/dac3-04m                                                                                                                                                        dac3-04m                                                                                                                                                         <p>dac3-04m is a converter from a digital signal to an analog voltage signal.</p><p>the converter generates 4 analog voltage signals, which can be operated, according to the type of controlled device, in a range 0-10 v or 1-10 v.</p><p>this is used for regulating and controlling devices that may be controlled by this signal (dimmable ballasts of fluorescent lamps and other types of light sources - e.g. led panels from the assortment of elko lighting, dimming actuator for led and rgb strips rfda-73m/ rgb, thermostatic heads, servo drives, elements for measuring and regulation and others).</p><p>the range of output voltage is adjustable in idm3.</p><p>the converter is equipped with a temperature input for connecting a 2-wire external sensor tc/tz (see accessories).</p><p>dac3-04m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_dac3-04m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/dac3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_dac3-04m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (16, 'en', 'gfB-wMqHwChswMlIVU4vC', '/sa3-06m', true, '0jXIG5nI37APTQz8ZcCv6', 'SA3-06M', true, '<p>The actuator is designed for switching up to six various appliances and loads with potentialless contact.</p><p>&nbsp;SA3-06M is a switching actuator contains 6 independent relays with changeover potentialless contacts.</p><p>&nbsp;Maximum load per contact is 8 A/2000 VA/AC1.</p><p>&nbsp;Each of six output contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;The relays are divided into two groups, the group of four relays on the bottom terminal switches the common potential, a pair of relays on top of the terminal switches the second&nbsp; &nbsp;common potential.</p><p>&nbsp;The actuator is suitable for operating discontinuously controlled thermo drives in the distributor of floor heating.</p><p>&nbsp;LEDs on the front panel signals the status of each output.</p><p>&nbsp;Contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>&nbsp;SA3-06M is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2 contact material.</p><p>&nbsp;SA3-06M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard/DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'SA3-06M', 'Switching actuator, 6-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":191,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132879', '3287 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-06m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-06m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/SA3-06M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759922080743, 1760601390179, '/sa3-06m                                                                                                                                                         sa3-06m                                                                                                                                                          <p>the actuator is designed for switching up to six various appliances and loads with potentialless contact.</p><p>&nbsp;sa3-06m is a switching actuator contains 6 independent relays with changeover potentialless contacts.</p><p>&nbsp;maximum load per contact is 8 a/2000 va/ac1.</p><p>&nbsp;each of six output contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>&nbsp;the relays are divided into two groups, the group of four relays on the bottom terminal switches the common potential, a pair of relays on top of the terminal switches the second&nbsp; &nbsp;common potential.</p><p>&nbsp;the actuator is suitable for operating discontinuously controlled thermo drives in the distributor of floor heating.</p><p>&nbsp;leds on the front panel signals the status of each output.</p><p>&nbsp;contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>&nbsp;sa3-06m is normally supplied in the option agsno2 contact material.</p><p>&nbsp;sa3-06m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard/din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-06m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-06m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-06m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-06m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (15, 'en', 'fviPdy0jkrKKYHoZi2ya4', '/sa3-04m', true, 'ECBiLMY__vG7Pm9-7Cm9k', 'SA3-04M', true, '<p>&nbsp;SA3-04M is a switching actuator containing 4 independent relays with&nbsp;changeover potential-free contacts.</p><p>The maximum load per contact is 16 A/4000 VA/AC1.&nbsp;</p><p>Each of the 4 outputs contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>All four relays are individually decorated input terminals, and therefore can switch various independent potentials.</p><p>The actuator is designed for switching 4 various appliances or loads by&nbsp;relay outputs (potential free contacts).</p><p>Thanks to changeover contacts, it can be used to control up to two&nbsp;drives with 230 V power (such as blinds, shutters or awnings) with appropriate&nbsp;bridging, the contacts can secure hardware blocking the possibility of simultaneous switching of the phase on both outputs, see an example of connection.</p><p>LEDs on the front panel signal the status of each output.</p><p>The contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually&nbsp;by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>Switching actuators SA3 is normally supplied in the option AgSnO2&nbsp;contact material.</p><p>SA3-04M in 3-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard,&nbsp;on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'SA3-04M', 'Switching actuator, 4-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":189,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132381', '3238 standard', 9, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_sa3-04m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/SA3-04M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759151176121, 1760601418754, '/sa3-04m                                                                                                                                                         sa3-04m                                                                                                                                                          <p>&nbsp;sa3-04m is a switching actuator containing 4 independent relays with&nbsp;changeover potential-free contacts.</p><p>the maximum load per contact is 16 a/4000 va/ac1.&nbsp;</p><p>each of the 4 outputs contacts are individually controllable and addressable.</p><p>all four relays are individually decorated input terminals, and therefore can switch various independent potentials.</p><p>the actuator is designed for switching 4 various appliances or loads by&nbsp;relay outputs (potential free contacts).</p><p>thanks to changeover contacts, it can be used to control up to two&nbsp;drives with 230 v power (such as blinds, shutters or awnings) with appropriate&nbsp;bridging, the contacts can secure hardware blocking the possibility of simultaneous switching of the phase on both outputs, see an example of connection.</p><p>leds on the front panel signal the status of each output.</p><p>the contact status of each relay can be changed separately and manually&nbsp;by control buttons on a front panel.</p><p>switching actuators sa3 is normally supplied in the option agsno2&nbsp;contact material.</p><p>sa3-04m in 3-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard,&nbsp;on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_sa3-04m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/sa3-04m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_sa3-04m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (63, 'en', 'lk49_xR8Qwq6H0Sr6zPBZ', '/msb3-40', true, 'su3y2IlrPOsqA7DK-F4M8', 'MSB3-40', true, '<p>Metal switch buttons MSB3-40/XXare&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>MSB3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>MSB3-40/XX is equipped with four touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>The metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>The metal switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>MSB3-40/XX are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm)</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'MSB3-40', 'Metal switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":483,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191425', '9142 standard', 15, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/manual_msb3-x0_bus_a4_en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764330169211, 1764330169211, '/msb3-40                                                                                                                                                         msb3-40                                                                                                                                                          <p>metal switch buttons msb3-40/xxare&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>msb3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>msb3-40/xx is equipped with four touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>the metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>the metal switch button is a design component of the inels system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>msb3-40/xx are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm)</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_msb3-40-60-90.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-40/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_msb3-40.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (74, 'en', '6b1RJeE-qsTnZmn5wtdiK', '/ins4sq', true, '8Z1i7XjWytnsv6tdLXjTJ', 'INS4SQ', true, '<p>The INS4SQ offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and&nbsp;monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display,&nbsp;and support for various interfaces and sensors. Its temperature&nbsp;and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating&nbsp;environments.</p><p>Featuring a high-quality 4" IPS display with a resolution of 480 x 480&nbsp;and a luminance of 400 cd/m2, the INS4SQ offers crisp and clear visuals for an excellent user experience.</p><p>The device runs on the Linux 3.4 operating system supporting up to 200&nbsp;UI objects and 1000 BMS points.</p><p>Equipped with an ARM A7 Single-Core 1.2 GHz processor, 128MB DDR3&nbsp;RAM, and 256MB Nand fl ash, ensuring reliable performance for various&nbsp;applications.</p><p>Integrated with essential sensors, the device includes a humidity sensor&nbsp;with a range of 0% up to 100% RH and a temperature sensor covering&nbsp;a range from -40°C up to +125°C, enabling efficient environmental&nbsp;monitoring.</p><p>The INS4SQ comes with a standard LAN RJ45 10/100Mbps interface, ensuring&nbsp;easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>The INS4SQ offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity&nbsp;and compatibility. These include RS485, DALI 2, Modbus, VRF,&nbsp;BLE Bluetooth 5.0 and Zigbee 3.0</p><p>The INS4SQ operates within a working temperature range of -10°C to&nbsp;+60°C.</p><p>The device can be powered by either 24VDC or 48VDC input, and it&nbsp;also supports Power over Ethernet (POE IEEE 802.3af), providing flexibility&nbsp;in power options.</p><p>Configuration, programming and update applications over the Skythings&nbsp;platform.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'INS4SQ', '4” touch control panel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":502,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', 'INS4SQ', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764335110163, 1764335110163, '/ins4sq                                                                                                                                                          ins4sq                                                                                                                                                           <p>the ins4sq offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and&nbsp;monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display,&nbsp;and support for various interfaces and sensors. its temperature&nbsp;and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating&nbsp;environments.</p><p>featuring a high-quality 4" ips display with a resolution of 480 x 480&nbsp;and a luminance of 400 cd/m2, the ins4sq offers crisp and clear visuals for an excellent user experience.</p><p>the device runs on the linux 3.4 operating system supporting up to 200&nbsp;ui objects and 1000 bms points.</p><p>equipped with an arm a7 single-core 1.2 ghz processor, 128mb ddr3&nbsp;ram, and 256mb nand fl ash, ensuring reliable performance for various&nbsp;applications.</p><p>integrated with essential sensors, the device includes a humidity sensor&nbsp;with a range of 0% up to 100% rh and a temperature sensor covering&nbsp;a range from -40°c up to +125°c, enabling efficient environmental&nbsp;monitoring.</p><p>the ins4sq comes with a standard lan rj45 10/100mbps interface, ensuring&nbsp;easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>the ins4sq offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity&nbsp;and compatibility. these include rs485, dali 2, modbus, vrf,&nbsp;ble bluetooth 5.0 and zigbee 3.0</p><p>the ins4sq operates within a working temperature range of -10°c to&nbsp;+60°c.</p><p>the device can be powered by either 24vdc or 48vdc input, and it&nbsp;also supports power over ethernet (poe ieee 802.3af), providing flexibility&nbsp;in power options.</p><p>configuration, programming and update applications over the skythings&nbsp;platform.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ins4sq/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ins4sq.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (75, 'en', 'Ddu3DNgZxAxEi_qVBFvrc', '/ins10sq', true, 'sW8qV40X1MiXpc01WTcL8', 'INS10SQ', true, '<p>The EST10 offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display, and support for various interfaces and sensors. Its temperature and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating environments.</p><p>Featuring IPS 10“ 1280 x 800 resolution 350 cd/m2 luminance with 5 point capacitive touchscreen.</p><p>The device runs on OS Android 6.0 operating system with A64 QuadCore 1.3 GHz/1GB DDR3 Ram / 8GB Nand fl ash supporting up to 2000 BMS points.</p><p>EST10 touch panel designed to control iNELS with Android OS via iNELS applications.</p><p>Integrated speakers and microphones are primarily designed for intercom operation</p><p>Integrated with essential sensors, the device includes an Ambient illuminance measurement sensor, humidity sensor and temperature sensor, enabling efficient environmental monitoring.</p><p>The EST10 comes with a standard LAN RJ45 10/100Mbps interface, ensuring easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>The EST10 offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity and compatibility. These include iNELS, RS485, Modbus, VRF, and Zigbee 3.0</p><p>The EST10 operates within a working temperature range of -10°C to +60°C.</p><p>The device can be powered by either 24VDC, and it also supports Power over Ethernet (POE IEEE 802.3af), providing flexibility in power options max 30W.</p><p>Configuration, programming, and update applications over the Skythings platform.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764586800000, '[]', 'INS10SQ', '10” touch control panel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":496,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', 'INS10SQ.B', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764595029508, 1764595029508, '/ins10sq                                                                                                                                                         ins10sq                                                                                                                                                          <p>the est10 offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display, and support for various interfaces and sensors. its temperature and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating environments.</p><p>featuring ips 10“ 1280 x 800 resolution 350 cd/m2 luminance with 5 point capacitive touchscreen.</p><p>the device runs on os android 6.0 operating system with a64 quadcore 1.3 ghz/1gb ddr3 ram / 8gb nand fl ash supporting up to 2000 bms points.</p><p>est10 touch panel designed to control inels with android os via inels applications.</p><p>integrated speakers and microphones are primarily designed for intercom operation</p><p>integrated with essential sensors, the device includes an ambient illuminance measurement sensor, humidity sensor and temperature sensor, enabling efficient environmental monitoring.</p><p>the est10 comes with a standard lan rj45 10/100mbps interface, ensuring easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>the est10 offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity and compatibility. these include inels, rs485, modbus, vrf, and zigbee 3.0</p><p>the est10 operates within a working temperature range of -10°c to +60°c.</p><p>the device can be powered by either 24vdc, and it also supports power over ethernet (poe ieee 802.3af), providing flexibility in power options max 30w.</p><p>configuration, programming, and update applications over the skythings platform.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ins10sq/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ins10sq.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (13, 'en', 'pQRTFLLx1PvjmdOw9BPLn', '/bps3-01m', true, '1gCypFDGCHr_lI1iaKUJO', 'BPS3-01M', true, '<p>The BPS3-01M and BPS3-02M units are used for impedance separation of the BUS from the supply voltage source.</p><p>A BPS3-01M or BPS3-02M bus isolator is required for each CU3-XXM&nbsp;central unit.</p><p>&nbsp;BPS3-01M allows the connection of one BUS branch with a load of max. 3 A.</p><p>&nbsp;BPS3-02M allows the connection of two BUS branches with a load of max. 1 A for each branch.</p><p>&nbsp;The outputs are equipped with overcurrent and surge protection.</p><p>&nbsp;Indication of the output voltage of the BUS outputs by LEDs.</p><p>&nbsp;BPS3-01M, BPS3-02M in 1-MODULE design are designed for mounting in a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'BPS3-01M', 'BUS separator from power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":173,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132442', '3244 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-01m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_bps3-0xm.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/BPS3-01M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759149032729, 1760601477575, '/bps3-01m                                                                                                                                                        bps3-01m                                                                                                                                                         <p>the bps3-01m and bps3-02m units are used for impedance separation of the bus from the supply voltage source.</p><p>a bps3-01m or bps3-02m bus isolator is required for each cu3-xxm&nbsp;central unit.</p><p>&nbsp;bps3-01m allows the connection of one bus branch with a load of max. 3 a.</p><p>&nbsp;bps3-02m allows the connection of two bus branches with a load of max. 1 a for each branch.</p><p>&nbsp;the outputs are equipped with overcurrent and surge protection.</p><p>&nbsp;indication of the output voltage of the bus outputs by leds.</p><p>&nbsp;bps3-01m, bps3-02m in 1-module design are designed for mounting in a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-01m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_bps3-01m_bps3-02m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-01m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_bps3-01m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (12, 'en', 'ssTgw25KUJnxwexoNAKR0', '/bps3-02m', true, 'Cgu9wxGXs1XIwgaIB21Yd', 'BPS3-02M', true, '<p>Units BPS3-01M and BPS3-02M serve for impedance separation of BUS from supply voltage power.</p><p>A BPS3-01M or BPS3-02M bus isolator is required for each CU3-XXM&nbsp;central unit.</p><p>BPS3-01M allows you to connect one BUS with max. load 3 A.</p><p>BPS3-02M allows you to connect two separate BUS1 and BUS2 with max. load 1 A for each line.</p><p>Outputs are equipped with overcurrent and overvoltage protection.</p><p>Indication of output voltage outputs BUS LED.</p><p>BPS3-01M and BPS3-02M in 1-MODULE version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'BPS3-02M', 'BUS separator from power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":174,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132435', '3243 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_bps3-0xm.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/BPS3-02M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759148974859, 1760601498216, '/bps3-02m                                                                                                                                                        bps3-02m                                                                                                                                                         <p>units bps3-01m and bps3-02m serve for impedance separation of bus from supply voltage power.</p><p>a bps3-01m or bps3-02m bus isolator is required for each cu3-xxm&nbsp;central unit.</p><p>bps3-01m allows you to connect one bus with max. load 3 a.</p><p>bps3-02m allows you to connect two separate bus1 and bus2 with max. load 1 a for each line.</p><p>outputs are equipped with overcurrent and overvoltage protection.</p><p>indication of output voltage outputs bus led.</p><p>bps3-01m and bps3-02m in 1-module version is designed for mounting into a switchboard, on din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_bps3-01m_bps3-02m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/bps3-02m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_bps3-02m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (52, 'en', 'b-nKYLAG9rVl2_PZyWdk-', '/gsb3-290', true, 'ovsQ5-Honi2md55vn5RLE', 'GSB3-290', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers GSB3-XXX are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40, GSB3-60, and GSB3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the GSB3-240, GSB3-260, and GSB3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>GSB3-40 and GSB3-240 are equipped with four, GSB3-60, GSB3-260 six and GSB3-&nbsp;90, GSB3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/B) and white (GSB3-XXX/W) versions.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue LED indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-290', 'Glass switch button', '[{"image":{"uploadId":392,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189613', '8961 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763992426878, 1763992433738, '/gsb3-290                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-290                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass touch controllers gsb3-xxx are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40, gsb3-60, and gsb3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the gsb3-240, gsb3-260, and gsb3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>gsb3-40 and gsb3-240 are equipped with four, gsb3-60, gsb3-260 six and gsb3-&nbsp;90, gsb3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/b) and white (gsb3-xxx/w) versions.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue led indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-290/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-290_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (128, 'en', 'VgScoffeXQBOQ7-scbm-4', '/rfti-20', true, 'j5dfmgxim48_usaNWIE_m', 'RFTI-20', true, '<p>With an integrated digital sensor, it measures temperature and humidity&nbsp;in the range of -10 to +50 °C and at regular intervals of 20 min.&nbsp;sends it to the system device (eLAN-RF, RF-Touch).</p><p>In the event of a sudden change in temperature and humidity, it sends&nbsp;a signal within 1 min.</p><p>(2x 3 V batteries CR 2032 - included in the package) with a lifetime</p><p>Approx. 1 year (according to ambient temperature cycling).</p><p>Range up to 160m (in open space), in case of insufficient signal between&nbsp;the controller and the device, use RFRP-20 signal repeater or&nbsp;devices with RFIO2 protocol that support this function.</p><p>Communication frequency with two-way RFIO protocol.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFTI-20', 'Temperature and humidity sensor', '[{"image":{"uploadId":791,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188134019', '3401', 31, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfti-20/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfti-20.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFTI-20/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171011235, 1769171011235, '/rfti-20                                                                                                                                                         rfti-20                                                                                                                                                          <p>with an integrated digital sensor, it measures temperature and humidity&nbsp;in the range of -10 to +50 °c and at regular intervals of 20 min.&nbsp;sends it to the system device (elan-rf, rf-touch).</p><p>in the event of a sudden change in temperature and humidity, it sends&nbsp;a signal within 1 min.</p><p>(2x 3 v batteries cr 2032 - included in the package) with a lifetime</p><p>approx. 1 year (according to ambient temperature cycling).</p><p>range up to 160m (in open space), in case of insufficient signal between&nbsp;the controller and the device, use rfrp-20 signal repeater or&nbsp;devices with rfio2 protocol that support this function.</p><p>communication frequency with two-way rfio protocol.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfti-20/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfti-20.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfti-20/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_rfti-20.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (10, 'en', 'dhkTu9WkN681KTBcflYql', '/ps3-30inels', true, 'VA_LEEmZWuVBid_10Dm_k', 'PS3-30/iNELS', true, '<p>&nbsp;PS3-30/iNELS is a switched stabilized power supply with a total power of 30 W.</p><p>&nbsp;PS3-30/iNELS is used to power central units and external masters within the iNELS bus wiring.</p><p>&nbsp;PS3-30/iNELS It is equipped with electronic protection against short circuits, overvoltage, power and temperature overload.</p><p>&nbsp;The power supply includes an internally integrated BPS3-01M bus isolator to power one branch of the BUS, from which the iNELS peripheral units are further powered.</p><p>&nbsp;PS3-30/iNELS 3-MODULE is designed for mounting in a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'PS3-30/iNELS', 'Power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":176,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188180115', '8011 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/manual_ps3-30.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/PS3-30_iNELS/3D/3d.html', '', 1759148816388, 1760601527287, '/ps3-30inels                                                                                                                                                     ps3-30/inels                                                                                                                                                     <p>&nbsp;ps3-30/inels is a switched stabilized power supply with a total power of 30 w.</p><p>&nbsp;ps3-30/inels is used to power central units and external masters within the inels bus wiring.</p><p>&nbsp;ps3-30/inels it is equipped with electronic protection against short circuits, overvoltage, power and temperature overload.</p><p>&nbsp;the power supply includes an internally integrated bps3-01m bus isolator to power one branch of the bus, from which the inels peripheral units are further powered.</p><p>&nbsp;ps3-30/inels 3-module is designed for mounting in a switchboard on din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ps3-30_inels.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ps3-30_inels/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_ps3-30-inels.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (8, 'en', 'UY52Kvq9iRi4w7mM5lf2U', '/psm3-60inels', true, 'C22Ro0Cz44e4CCXaoyWKm', 'PSM3-60/iNELS', true, '<p>Used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation iNELS.</p><p>Through BUS separators from the supply voltage BPS3-01M and&nbsp;BPS3-02M, it supplies BUS lines from which iNELS peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>Rated output voltage 27V DC with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>High efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>Low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>Protection: Overload, Over voltage and Short circuit.</p><p>Continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'PSM3-60/iNELS', 'Power supply', '[{"image":{"uploadId":180,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184779', '8477 standard', 7, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-60_inels/share_dokumentace/en/manual_psm3_en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/PSM3-60_iNELS/3D/3d.html', '', 1759148605977, 1760601589037, '/psm3-60inels                                                                                                                                                    psm3-60/inels                                                                                                                                                    <p>used to supply central units and external master within intelligent&nbsp;electroinstallation inels.</p><p>through bus separators from the supply voltage bps3-01m and&nbsp;bps3-02m, it supplies bus lines from which inels peripheral units are&nbsp;also powered.</p><p>rated output voltage 27v dc with the possibility of regulation.&nbsp;</p><p>high efficiency of up to 90%.&nbsp;</p><p>low ripple &amp; noise.&nbsp;</p><p>protection: overload, over voltage and short circuit.</p><p>continuously adjustable output voltage to adapt to the specific&nbsp;application, e.g. the need to compensate for the voltage drop caused by the length of the line.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-60_inels/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_psm3-30_inels_psm3-60_inels_psm3-100_inels.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/psm3-60_inels/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_psm3-60_inels_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (3, 'en', 'zA6jvt-uPa6rWj_s5du0m', '/cu3-08m', true, 'cWgdaJuoE1_z_IGScisAD', 'CU3-08M', true, '<p>CU3-08M is one of the basic system control of iNELS BUS installations.</p><p>The unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can be controlled by the IP-MASTER as part of a larger Project.</p><p>The units is equipped with two BUS, to which it is possible to connect a total of up to 64 elements (2x32) from the iNELS BUS portfolio.</p><p>The current load of one line is max. 1 A. BPS3-01M with 3 A can be used in the case of a connected device with more than 1 A.</p><p>The RJ45 100 Mbps Ethernet connector is used for direct communication with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the superior unit within the iNELS IP topology.</p><p>Configuration takes place in the iNELS3 Designer &amp; Manager software (iDM3). Through iDM3 it is possible to update the firmware of central units and bus-connected peripheral units.</p><p>The central unit is implemented with MQTT protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>The unit is powered by 27 V DC from iNELS power supply. BUS1 can power the central unit.</p><p>System units CU3-08M in 1-MODULE design are designed for mounting into a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p><p><br></p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1759140000000, '[]', 'CU3-08M', 'Central unit with 2x BUS', '[{"image":{"uploadId":172,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191630', '9163 standard', 3, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-08m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_cu3-08m_bus.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/CU3-08M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759147150161, 1760601679714, '/cu3-08m                                                                                                                                                         cu3-08m                                                                                                                                                          <p>cu3-08m is one of the basic system control of inels bus installations.</p><p>the unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can be controlled by the ip-master as part of a larger project.</p><p>the units is equipped with two bus, to which it is possible to connect a total of up to 64 elements (2x32) from the inels bus portfolio.</p><p>the current load of one line is max. 1 a. bps3-01m with 3 a can be used in the case of a connected device with more than 1 a.</p><p>the rj45 100 mbps ethernet connector is used for direct communication with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the superior unit within the inels ip topology.</p><p>configuration takes place in the inels3 designer &amp; manager software (idm3). through idm3 it is possible to update the firmware of central units and bus-connected peripheral units.</p><p>the central unit is implemented with mqtt protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>the unit is powered by 27 v dc from inels power supply. bus1 can power the central unit.</p><p>system units cu3-08m in 1-module design are designed for mounting into a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p><p><br></p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-08m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_cu3-08m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-08m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_cu3-08m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (53, 'en', 'UefrXPZXVDkZwshrjHxOn', '/gsb3-260s', true, '7267SjLrJAYrejBqlKkBe', 'GSB3-260/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-XX/S are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the GSB3-240/S, GSB3-260/S, and GSB3-290/S models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, GSB3-240/S are equipped with four, GSB3-60/S, GSB3-260/S six&nbsp;and GSB3-90/S, GSB3-290/S nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/&nbsp;TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/SB) and white (GSB3-XXX/SW) versions.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>In addition to all the features in symbol models. The glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the SBP/SWP version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>SWP/SBP models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-260/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":396,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189651', '8965 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260s/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763992521014, 1763992569803, '/gsb3-260s                                                                                                                                                       gsb3-260/s                                                                                                                                                       <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-xx/s are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the gsb3-240/s, gsb3-260/s, and gsb3-290/s models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, gsb3-240/s are equipped with four, gsb3-60/s, gsb3-260/s six&nbsp;and gsb3-90/s, gsb3-290/s nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.<br>• engraving of symbols is possible upon request.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/&nbsp;tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well and&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/sb) and white (gsb3-xxx/sw) versions.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise, and white.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>in addition to all the features in symbol models. the glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the sbp/swp version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>swp/sbp models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260s/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260s/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-260_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (2, 'en', 'YXhV4-5uF527LlsfWStR7', '/cu3-09mdali', true, 'Ztt8yslU3WYYh9sbmlc4A', 'CU3-09M/DALI', true, '<p>CU3-09M is one of the basic system control units of iNELS BUS installations.&nbsp;</p><p>The unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can&nbsp;be controlled by the central software as part of a larger project.</p><p>The unit is equipped with one BUS to switch it is possible to connect up&nbsp;to 32 elements from the iNELS BUS portfolio.</p><p>The current load of one line is max. 1 A. BPS3-01M with 3 A can be used in case&nbsp;of a connected device with more than 1 A.</p><p>The CU3-09M/DALI system unit is equipped with one DALI1/DALI2 bus.</p><p>The DALI system bus allows control of up to 64 independent DALI devices.</p><p>Addressing DALI can be done via the iDM3 software.</p><p>The RJ45 100 Mbps Ethernet connector is used for direct communication&nbsp;with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the&nbsp;superior unit within the iNELS IP topology.</p><p>Configuration takes place in the iNELS3 Designer &amp; Manager software&nbsp;(iDM3).</p><p>Through iDM3 it is possible to update the firmware of central units and&nbsp;bus-connected peripheral units.</p><p>The central unit is implemented with MQTT protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>The unit is powered by 27 V DC from iNELS power supply. BUS1 can&nbsp;power the central unit.</p><p>System units CU3-09M/DALI in 1-MODULE design are designed for mounting&nbsp;into a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1759140000000, '[]', 'CU3-09M/DALI', 'Central unit with 1x BUS, 1x DALI', '[{"image":{"uploadId":169,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184656', '8465', 3, '["2"]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-09m-dali/share_dokumentace/en/manual_cu3-09m_dali_bus.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/CU3-09M-DALI/3D/3d.html', '', 1759128888479, 1760601694184, '/cu3-09mdali                                                                                                                                                     cu3-09m/dali                                                                                                                                                     <p>cu3-09m is one of the basic system control units of inels bus installations.&nbsp;</p><p>the unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can&nbsp;be controlled by the central software as part of a larger project.</p><p>the unit is equipped with one bus to switch it is possible to connect up&nbsp;to 32 elements from the inels bus portfolio.</p><p>the current load of one line is max. 1 a. bps3-01m with 3 a can be used in case&nbsp;of a connected device with more than 1 a.</p><p>the cu3-09m/dali system unit is equipped with one dali1/dali2 bus.</p><p>the dali system bus allows control of up to 64 independent dali devices.</p><p>addressing dali can be done via the idm3 software.</p><p>the rj45 100 mbps ethernet connector is used for direct communication&nbsp;with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the&nbsp;superior unit within the inels ip topology.</p><p>configuration takes place in the inels3 designer &amp; manager software&nbsp;(idm3).</p><p>through idm3 it is possible to update the firmware of central units and&nbsp;bus-connected peripheral units.</p><p>the central unit is implemented with mqtt protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>the unit is powered by 27 v dc from inels power supply. bus1 can&nbsp;power the central unit.</p><p>system units cu3-09m/dali in 1-module design are designed for mounting&nbsp;into a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-09m-dali/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_cu3-09m_dali.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-09m-dali/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_cu3-09m_dali.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (4, 'en', 'v4D7nIuUUcSJDE7MnVqsI', '/cu3-10m', true, 'VjE0OFKBcmR2gRKuqo5q5', 'CU3-10M', true, '<p>CU3-10M is one of the basic system control units of iNELS BUS installations.</p><p>The unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can&nbsp;be controlled by the IP-MASTER as part of a larger project.</p><p>The unit is equipped with one BUS to switch it is possible to connect up&nbsp;to 32 elements from the iNELS BUS portfolio.</p><p>The current load of one line is max. 1 A. BPS3-01M with 3 A can be used in the case&nbsp;of a connected device with more than 1 A.</p><p>The CU3-10M system unit is equipped with one Modbus system bus.&nbsp;The Modbus system bus allows control of Modbus thermostat and Air&nbsp;condition units (RS-485).</p><p>The RJ45 100 Mbps Ethernet connector is used for direct communication&nbsp;with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the&nbsp;superior unit within the iNELS IP topology.</p><p>Configuration takes place in the iNELS3 Designer &amp; Manager software&nbsp;(iDM3). Through iDM3 it is possible to update the firmware of central&nbsp;units and bus connected peripheral units.</p><p>The central unit is implemented with MQTT protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>The unit is powered by 27 V DC from iNELS power supply.&nbsp;</p><p>System units CU3-10M in 1-MODULE design are designed for mounting&nbsp;into a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760004000000, '[]', 'CU3-10M', 'Central unit with 1x BUS, 1x MODBUS', '[{"image":{"uploadId":171,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188185219', '8521 standard', 3, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/CU3-10M/3D/3d.html', '', 1759147343576, 1760601708865, '/cu3-10m                                                                                                                                                         cu3-10m                                                                                                                                                          <p>cu3-10m is one of the basic system control units of inels bus installations.</p><p>the unit can work independently, as an autonomous project, or it can&nbsp;be controlled by the ip-master as part of a larger project.</p><p>the unit is equipped with one bus to switch it is possible to connect up&nbsp;to 32 elements from the inels bus portfolio.</p><p>the current load of one line is max. 1 a. bps3-01m with 3 a can be used in the case&nbsp;of a connected device with more than 1 a.</p><p>the cu3-10m system unit is equipped with one modbus system bus.&nbsp;the modbus system bus allows control of modbus thermostat and air&nbsp;condition units (rs-485).</p><p>the rj45 100 mbps ethernet connector is used for direct communication&nbsp;with the cloud for mobile app control or for communication with the&nbsp;superior unit within the inels ip topology.</p><p>configuration takes place in the inels3 designer &amp; manager software&nbsp;(idm3). through idm3 it is possible to update the firmware of central&nbsp;units and bus connected peripheral units.</p><p>the central unit is implemented with mqtt protocol for 3rd party communication.&nbsp;</p><p>the unit is powered by 27 v dc from inels power supply.&nbsp;</p><p>system units cu3-10m in 1-module design are designed for mounting&nbsp;into a switchboard on din rail en60715.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-10m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_cu3-10m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/cu3-10m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_cu3-10m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (54, 'en', 'omOCBm9h50DY-Gcv_Jdch', '/gsb3-260', true, 'aYcvw8WKba3uK0aWOY3Fz', 'GSB3-260', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers GSB3-XXX are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40, GSB3-60, and GSB3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the GSB3-240, GSB3-260, and GSB3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>GSB3-40 and GSB3-240 are equipped with four, GSB3-60, GSB3-260 six and GSB3-&nbsp;90, GSB3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/B) and white (GSB3-XXX/W) versions.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue LED indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-260', 'Glass switch button', '[{"image":{"uploadId":393,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189590', '8959 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/GSB3-260/3D/3d.html', '', 1763992752111, 1763992752111, '/gsb3-260                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-260                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass touch controllers gsb3-xxx are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40, gsb3-60, and gsb3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the gsb3-240, gsb3-260, and gsb3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>gsb3-40 and gsb3-240 are equipped with four, gsb3-60, gsb3-260 six and gsb3-&nbsp;90, gsb3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/b) and white (gsb3-xxx/w) versions.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue led indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-260/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-260_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (129, 'en', 'APsm6KP6q1F0fN0V3ByAU', '/tz', true, 'BgL21dDiKd3N0EiiG8MZS', 'TZ', true, '<p>Thermister temperature sensors are made of Negative Temperature&nbsp;Coefficient (NTC) embedded in a PVC or metal sleeve with a thermally conductive&nbsp;sealer.</p><p>Cable VO3SS-F 2D x 0.5 mm/0.02” with silicone insulation for use in&nbsp;high-temperature applications.</p><p>Silicone insulation for use in high-temperature applications.</p><p>Temperature sensors can be connected directly to the terminal block&nbsp;</p><p>Cable lengths can not be changed, connected or modified.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'TZ', 'Temperature sensor', '[{"image":{"uploadId":789,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188140600', '209970800015', 31, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/Accessories/TZ/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171083172, 1769171083172, '/tz                                                                                                                                                              tz                                                                                                                                                               <p>thermister temperature sensors are made of negative temperature&nbsp;coefficient (ntc) embedded in a pvc or metal sleeve with a thermally conductive&nbsp;sealer.</p><p>cable vo3ss-f 2d x 0.5 mm/0.02” with silicone insulation for use in&nbsp;high-temperature applications.</p><p>silicone insulation for use in high-temperature applications.</p><p>temperature sensors can be connected directly to the terminal block&nbsp;</p><p>cable lengths can not be changed, connected or modified.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/tc/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_tc_tz_pt100.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (37, 'en', '1QjAI-KTARa9jw-aMGVxA', '/elan-ir-003', true, '8k3VcP1aUZbPNm22fBEqg', 'eLAN-IR-003', true, '<p>&nbsp;The applications iHC-MAIR and iHC-MIIR provide universal control for all Audio/Video devices (including air conditioning).</p><p>&nbsp;The application is connected via a smartphone connected to the smart IR box eLAN-IR-003, which communicates with audio/video devices</p><p>&nbsp;via IR sensor.</p><p>&nbsp;The intuitive application environment makes it simple for anyone to control.</p><p>&nbsp;What can you control? Home theater, TV, DVD or Blue Ray player, amplifier, set-top box, satellite receiver, air-conditioning, projector and more.</p><p>&nbsp;It can control up to 100 arbitrary commands with various controllers that you normally have at home.</p><p>&nbsp;With the scenes function you can perform multiple functions simultaneously with a single click command (e.g. you are going to bed you and switch off all AV appliances in the entire home with a single press).</p><p>&nbsp;It is possible to integrate into a single application an unlimited number of IR boxes, meaning that in one application, you have control over the living room, children‘s rooms, etc.</p><p>&nbsp;It is also possible to control remotely from anywhere using a Wi-Fi network (e.g. from work or vacation).</p><p>&nbsp;Thanks to auto-IP acquisition from the DHCP server, you need not set up a network (if you have no set fixed IP address).</p><p>&nbsp;You can connect three sensors to the smart IR box eLAN-IR-003 for three directions of control.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'eLAN-IR-003', 'Ethernet-IR transmitter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":209,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132831', '3283 standard', 12, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/elan/elan-ir-003/share_dokumentace/en/manual_elan-ir-003.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/eLAN/eLAN-IR-003/3D/3d.html', '', 1760602461293, 1760602461293, '/elan-ir-003                                                                                                                                                     elan-ir-003                                                                                                                                                      <p>&nbsp;the applications ihc-mair and ihc-miir provide universal control for all audio/video devices (including air conditioning).</p><p>&nbsp;the application is connected via a smartphone connected to the smart ir box elan-ir-003, which communicates with audio/video devices</p><p>&nbsp;via ir sensor.</p><p>&nbsp;the intuitive application environment makes it simple for anyone to control.</p><p>&nbsp;what can you control? home theater, tv, dvd or blue ray player, amplifier, set-top box, satellite receiver, air-conditioning, projector and more.</p><p>&nbsp;it can control up to 100 arbitrary commands with various controllers that you normally have at home.</p><p>&nbsp;with the scenes function you can perform multiple functions simultaneously with a single click command (e.g. you are going to bed you and switch off all av appliances in the entire home with a single press).</p><p>&nbsp;it is possible to integrate into a single application an unlimited number of ir boxes, meaning that in one application, you have control over the living room, children‘s rooms, etc.</p><p>&nbsp;it is also possible to control remotely from anywhere using a wi-fi network (e.g. from work or vacation).</p><p>&nbsp;thanks to auto-ip acquisition from the dhcp server, you need not set up a network (if you have no set fixed ip address).</p><p>&nbsp;you can connect three sensors to the smart ir box elan-ir-003 for three directions of control.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/elan/elan-ir-003/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_elan-ir-003.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/elan/elan-ir-003/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_elan-ir-003.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (38, 'en', '3H39__2-q3la8HV7NH80r', '/wmr3-21', true, 'LCb6v6BCceTl6l6TiYyl_', 'WMR3-21', true, '<p>WMR3-21 is a wall-mounted card reader that is designed to read contactless&nbsp;media (smart cards, key chains, etc.), which are used for controlling&nbsp;access to buildings or their parts.</p><p>With the glass controller, WMR3-21 users will appreciate the easy of&nbsp;control using two push buttons, which can be assigned different control&nbsp;functions lighting, shading, scenes, heating, etc.</p><p>WMR3-21 reader can be used to control the security system (locking/&nbsp;unlocking) access system (opening doors, gates, etc.), or appliances&nbsp;(based on assigned rights).</p><p>WMR3-21 supports RFID media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 MHz.&nbsp;Supported card types MIFARE Ultralight, DESFire 2K (EV1), DESFire 4K&nbsp;(EV1).</p><p>WMR3-21 is also equipped with 8 A relay output with changeover contact&nbsp;AgSnO2, by which controlled devices can be switched directly (or&nbsp;any actuator in the system can be set in software iDM3).</p><p>Indication two-color LED in the controller cover can indicate not only&nbsp;the status of the controlled appliance but also the status of any sensor or&nbsp;actuator in the system.</p><p>Wall card reader WMR3-21 is compatible with both types of frames&nbsp;LOGUS90 (85.6 x 85.6 or 94 x 94 mm), therefore you can combine them&nbsp;with double and triple frames and classic products of the series.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'WMR3-21', 'Wall card reader', '[{"image":{"uploadId":211,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132756', '3275 standard', 13, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wmr3-21/share_dokumentace/en/manual_wmr3-21.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/WMR3-21/3D/3d.html', '', 1760614684406, 1760614684406, '/wmr3-21                                                                                                                                                         wmr3-21                                                                                                                                                          <p>wmr3-21 is a wall-mounted card reader that is designed to read contactless&nbsp;media (smart cards, key chains, etc.), which are used for controlling&nbsp;access to buildings or their parts.</p><p>with the glass controller, wmr3-21 users will appreciate the easy of&nbsp;control using two push buttons, which can be assigned different control&nbsp;functions lighting, shading, scenes, heating, etc.</p><p>wmr3-21 reader can be used to control the security system (locking/&nbsp;unlocking) access system (opening doors, gates, etc.), or appliances&nbsp;(based on assigned rights).</p><p>wmr3-21 supports rfid media with a carrier frequency of 13.56 mhz.&nbsp;supported card types mifare ultralight, desfire 2k (ev1), desfire 4k&nbsp;(ev1).</p><p>wmr3-21 is also equipped with 8 a relay output with changeover contact&nbsp;agsno2, by which controlled devices can be switched directly (or&nbsp;any actuator in the system can be set in software idm3).</p><p>indication two-color led in the controller cover can indicate not only&nbsp;the status of the controlled appliance but also the status of any sensor or&nbsp;actuator in the system.</p><p>wall card reader wmr3-21 is compatible with both types of frames&nbsp;logus90 (85.6 x 85.6 or 94 x 94 mm), therefore you can combine them&nbsp;with double and triple frames and classic products of the series.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wmr3-21/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_wmr3-21.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wmr3-21/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_wmr3-21.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (97, 'en', 'Wpk_0nMEV__ZkcIRE1s42', '/rf-key-60b', true, 'bm3lnSdwznHGX8mKnmGWM', 'RF KEY-60/B', true, '<p>Key fob - sized remote control, available in black and white.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF/ON, blinds up/down).</p><p>RF KEY-40: four buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>RF KEY-60: six buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>Battery power supply (3 V CR 2032 battery - included in the supply)&nbsp;with battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RF KEY-60/B', 'Key fob - 6 buttons - color BLACK', '[{"image":{"uploadId":754,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188180771', '8077', 23, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rf_key-40_60_a4_en-cz.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RF_KEY-60/share_dokumentace/AKTUAL/3D/3d.html', '', 1768998143647, 1768998143647, '/rf-key-60b                                                                                                                                                      rf key-60/b                                                                                                                                                      <p>key fob - sized remote control, available in black and white.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off/on, blinds up/down).</p><p>rf key-40: four buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>rf key-60: six buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>battery power supply (3 v cr 2032 battery - included in the supply)&nbsp;with battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rf_key.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfkey-60.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (130, 'en', 'zbFPuAwF8bIGo_ymgdkTp', '/tc', true, '2rZAJHpT-ldXBHcfW_rzp', 'TC', true, '<p>Thermister temperature sensors are made of Negative Temperature&nbsp;Coefficient (NTC) embedded in a PVC or metal sleeve with a thermally conductive sealer.</p><p>The Lead-in cable to sensor TC is made of wire CYSY 2D x 0.5 mm/0.02”.</p><p>Temperature sensors can be connected directly to the terminal block</p><p>Cable lengths can not be changed, connected or modified.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'TC', 'Temperature sensor', '[{"image":{"uploadId":792,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188110617', '209970800011', 31, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/TC/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171136502, 1769171136502, '/tc                                                                                                                                                              tc                                                                                                                                                               <p>thermister temperature sensors are made of negative temperature&nbsp;coefficient (ntc) embedded in a pvc or metal sleeve with a thermally conductive sealer.</p><p>the lead-in cable to sensor tc is made of wire cysy 2d x 0.5 mm/0.02”.</p><p>temperature sensors can be connected directly to the terminal block</p><p>cable lengths can not be changed, connected or modified.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/tc/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_tc_tz_pt100.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (55, 'en', 'QQMdqJi6kvK7DIyQkR3eW', '/gsb3-240s', true, 'HZhqak10yZbBMrE7LvEvt', 'GSB3-240/S', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers with symbols GSB3-XX/S are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40/S, GSB3-60/S, and GSB3-90/S models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the GSB3-240/S, GSB3-260/S, and GSB3-290/S models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>GSB3-40/S, and GSB3-240/S is equipped with four, GSB3-60/S, GSB3-260/S six&nbsp;and GSB3-90/S, GSB3-290/S nine touch buttons whose functions can easily&nbsp;modify by the software.</p><p>Engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/SB) and white (GSB3-XXX/SW) versions.</p><p>Individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>In addition to all the features in symbol models. The glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the SBP/SWP version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>SWP/SBP models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;Based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the iDM3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-240/S', 'Glass switch button with symbols', '[{"image":{"uploadId":391,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189637', '8963 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240s/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0-s_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763993324662, 1763993522129, '/gsb3-240s                                                                                                                                                       gsb3-240/s                                                                                                                                                       <p>glass touch controllers with symbols gsb3-xx/s are part of a comprehensive&nbsp;range of glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all&nbsp;projects for example as a part of a guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40/s, gsb3-60/s, and gsb3-90/s models feature a square design,&nbsp;while the gsb3-240/s, gsb3-260/s, and gsb3-290/s models come in a round&nbsp;design.</p><p>gsb3-40/s, and gsb3-240/s is equipped with four, gsb3-60/s, gsb3-260/s six&nbsp;and gsb3-90/s, gsb3-290/s nine touch buttons whose functions can easily&nbsp;modify by the software.</p><p>engraving of symbols is possible upon request.&nbsp;</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature sensor.&nbsp;it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which can be&nbsp;used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as well as&nbsp;the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/sb) and white (gsb3-xxx/sw) versions.</p><p>individual symbols can be illuminated in one of seven colors - red, green,&nbsp;blue, yellow, pink, turquoise and white.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and are designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p><p>in addition to all the features in symbol models. the glass touch controllers&nbsp;in the sbp/swp version are equipped with a proximity sensor, which can light&nbsp;up the symbols by approaching the unit to approx. 0.25 m.</p><p>swp/sbp models are also equipped with a sensor of ambient light intensity.&nbsp;based on information from the sensor it can switch the backlight of symbols or&nbsp;perform various actions in the idm3 software, for example, also switch the&nbsp;lighting circuits in the room.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240s/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb-xx-s_gsb-2xx-s.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240s/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-240_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (39, 'en', '3sK8GerVZsXUYfkBCIKZk', '/wsb3-20', true, '-S5zQ4zMkV5nmM4dyeM67', 'WSB3-20', true, '<p>&nbsp;Wall controllers with low-upstroke control WSB3-20 and WSB-20H are the main and most frequently used units (controller) in the iNELS system.</p><p>&nbsp;Built-in micro-buttons with low upstroke offer elegant and easy controlling.</p><p>&nbsp;Wall switches WSB3-20 and WSB3-20H are available in a 2-channel version.</p><p>&nbsp;Double color (red/green) LED diode indicates either status of controlled appliances or the status of any sensor or actuator in the system.</p><p>&nbsp;Each controller is equipped with a temperature sensor. It is also equipped with two analog/digital inputs (AIN/DIN), which can be used to connect two potentialless contacts or one external temperature sensor TC/TZ (e.g. for measuring floor temperature).</p><p>&nbsp;Compared to standard wall buttons WSB3-20 and WSB3-20H are more flexible and multifunctional. You can, for example, control appliances with a short and long push of the button (e.g.: dimming, shutter control, scenes).</p><p>&nbsp;Each button can control any appliance in the system and can use a variety of centralized or time-controlled features. Accordingly, the customer can choose the simplicity/complexity of the operation. The big advantage is the possibility to change the method of control by only making software modifications without physical interventions</p><p>&nbsp;into the structure of the building.</p><p>&nbsp;Each button (fold) can have different functional modes besides lighting control:<br>a) Classic wall-switch:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- upper button ON, bottom button OFF<br>b) Button controller (impulse relay):<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- first press ON, second press OFF<br>c) Dimmer:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - short press – ON/OFF<br>d) Time switch:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - ON after press, automatically OFF after set time<br>e) Setting light scenes – for example: for watching TV:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - shutters down<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - main light 30% intensity<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - wall-lamps 50% intensity</p><p>&nbsp;WSB3 in LOGUS90 design is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1760608800000, '[]', 'WSB3-20', 'Wall switch button, 2 buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":212,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188132343', '3234 standard', 13, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-20/share_dokumentace/en/manual_wsb3-20x.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/INELS-III/WSB3-20/3D/3d.html', '', 1760614814934, 1760614814934, '/wsb3-20                                                                                                                                                         wsb3-20                                                                                                                                                          <p>&nbsp;wall controllers with low-upstroke control wsb3-20 and wsb-20h are the main and most frequently used units (controller) in the inels system.</p><p>&nbsp;built-in micro-buttons with low upstroke offer elegant and easy controlling.</p><p>&nbsp;wall switches wsb3-20 and wsb3-20h are available in a 2-channel version.</p><p>&nbsp;double color (red/green) led diode indicates either status of controlled appliances or the status of any sensor or actuator in the system.</p><p>&nbsp;each controller is equipped with a temperature sensor. it is also equipped with two analog/digital inputs (ain/din), which can be used to connect two potentialless contacts or one external temperature sensor tc/tz (e.g. for measuring floor temperature).</p><p>&nbsp;compared to standard wall buttons wsb3-20 and wsb3-20h are more flexible and multifunctional. you can, for example, control appliances with a short and long push of the button (e.g.: dimming, shutter control, scenes).</p><p>&nbsp;each button can control any appliance in the system and can use a variety of centralized or time-controlled features. accordingly, the customer can choose the simplicity/complexity of the operation. the big advantage is the possibility to change the method of control by only making software modifications without physical interventions</p><p>&nbsp;into the structure of the building.</p><p>&nbsp;each button (fold) can have different functional modes besides lighting control:<br>a) classic wall-switch:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- upper button on, bottom button off<br>b) button controller (impulse relay):<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- first press on, second press off<br>c) dimmer:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - short press – on/off<br>d) time switch:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - on after press, automatically off after set time<br>e) setting light scenes – for example: for watching tv:<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - shutters down<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - main light 30% intensity<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; - wall-lamps 50% intensity</p><p>&nbsp;wsb3 in logus90 design is designed for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-20/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_wsb3-20_wsb3-20h.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/wsb3-20/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_wsb3-20.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (56, 'en', 'AXqMmN464QRVPc2lhlqqT', '/gsb3-240', true, 'dY-NMOTOQYkpe8EuBPaEV', 'GSB3-240', true, '<p>Glass touch controllers GSB3-XXX are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass iNELS control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (GRMS).</p><p>The GSB3-40, GSB3-60, and GSB3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the GSB3-240, GSB3-260, and GSB3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>GSB3-40 and GSB3-240 are equipped with four, GSB3-60, GSB3-260 six and GSB3-&nbsp;90, GSB3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>The glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). It is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>The glass touch panel is a design component of the iNELS system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (GSB3-XXX/B) and white (GSB3-XXX/W) versions.</p><p>The individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue LED indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1763982000000, '[]', 'GSB3-240', 'Glass switch button', '[{"image":{"uploadId":390,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189576', '8957 standard', 14, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240/share_dokumentace/en/manual_gsb3-x0_bus_a4-en.pdf', '', '', '', 1763993629296, 1763993629296, '/gsb3-240                                                                                                                                                        gsb3-240                                                                                                                                                         <p>glass touch controllers gsb3-xxx are part of a comprehensive range of&nbsp;glass inels control units and can be advantageously used in all projects&nbsp;for example as a part of guest room management system (grms).</p><p>the gsb3-40, gsb3-60, and gsb3-90 models feature a square design, while&nbsp;the gsb3-240, gsb3-260, and gsb3-290 models come in a round design.</p><p>gsb3-40 and gsb3-240 are equipped with four, gsb3-60, gsb3-260 six and gsb3-&nbsp;90, gsb3-290 nine touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the&nbsp;software.</p><p>the glass touch controller is equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature as&nbsp;well and the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions). it is&nbsp;therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances at once.</p><p>the glass touch panel is a design component of the inels system and is available&nbsp;in elegant black (gsb3-xxx/b) and white (gsb3-xxx/w) versions.</p><p>the individual capacitive buttons are point-illuminated by a blue led indicating&nbsp;the status of the controlled output.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm) and designed&nbsp;for mounting into an installation box.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_gsb3-xx_gsb3-2xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/gsb3-240/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_gsb3-240_xx.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (64, 'en', '8g4TD5sA39r-EVtTUbWcI', '/msb3-60', true, 'HSXftLfxF5KADtUf7CO_c', 'MSB3-60', true, '<p>Metal switch buttons MSB3-60/XX&nbsp; are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of iNELS control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>MSB3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>MSB3-60/XX is equipped with six touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>The metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. It is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (AIN/DIN), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor TC/TZ (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>Advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>Each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. Also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>It is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>The metal switch button is a design component of the iNELS system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>Individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>MSB3-60/XX are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>All versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'MSB3-60', 'Metal switch buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":484,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188191500', '9150 standard', 15, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-60/share_dokumentace/en/manual_msb3-x0_bus_a4_en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764330629123, 1764330629123, '/msb3-60                                                                                                                                                         msb3-60                                                                                                                                                          <p>metal switch buttons msb3-60/xx&nbsp; are&nbsp;part of a comprehensive range of inels control units and can be advantageously&nbsp;used in all projects.</p><p>msb3 comes with premium metal plates in antique copper, satin&nbsp;brass, brushed silver, and graphite black finish.</p><p>msb3-60/xx is equipped with six touch buttons whose functions can easily be modified by the software.</p><p>the metal switch buttons are equipped with an integrated temperature&nbsp;sensor. it is also equipped with analog-to-digital input (ain/din), which&nbsp;can be used to connect potential-free contact or external temperature&nbsp;sensor tc/tz (for example temperature measurement of the floor).&nbsp;</p><p>advantages over conventional switches/buttons are saving space, signaling&nbsp;the state of any system output, the ability to measure temperature&nbsp;as well as the ability to connect external buttons or detectors.</p><p>each button can control any actuator (appliance) in the system. also, you&nbsp;can assign each button a different function or macro (set of functions).</p><p>it is therefore possible to use one button to control several appliances&nbsp;at once.</p><p>the metal switch button is a design component of the inels system and&nbsp;is available in antique copper, satin brass, brushed silver, and graphite&nbsp;black versions.</p><p>individual buttons can be illuminated in white.&nbsp;</p><p>msb3-60/xx are designed for mounting&nbsp;into an installation box.</p><p>all versions are in the size of the standard module (94x94 mm).</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-60/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_msb3-40-60-90.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/msb3-60/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_msb3-60.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (66, 'en', 'Z3HpNbAVbnZBTmnVSS71W', '/rc3-610mdali', true, 'qGXuFeSAiGbppc-CR0463', 'RC3-610M/DALI', true, '<p>The RC3-610M/DALI is an I/O actuator equipped with 6 binary inputs, of&nbsp;which 2 can be confi gured as temperature inputs and 8 independent&nbsp;relays with switching potential-free and potential contacts. It also&nbsp;includes two analog outputs 0(1)-10 V with a load capacity of up to 10 mA.</p><p>Binary inputs RC3-610M/DALI are used for connecting up to 6 devices&nbsp;with a non-decimal contact (such as switches, switches, buttons of other&nbsp;designs, EZS and EPS detectors and others).</p><p>Temperature inputs support the connection of TC/TZ temperature&nbsp;sensors in a 2-wire connection for temprature sensing needs.</p><p>The actuator is designed for switching up to eight different appliances&nbsp;and loads by relay output (potential-free contact).</p><p>The maximum load capacity of the relay contacts is 10 A/2500 VA/&nbsp;AC1. Each of the output contacts is individually controllable. Relays&nbsp;are divided into four pairs, where each pair switches on its common&nbsp;potential.</p><p>The DALI system BUS allows control of up to 16 independent DALI (Digital&nbsp;Addressable Lighting Interface) ballast addresses for fluorescent, LED, and other luminaires.</p><p>Analog outputs are considered for use with thermoregulation heads,&nbsp;air-conditioning ventilation flaps, various other dimmers or other&nbsp;devices with an analog control voltage of 0-10 V or 1-10 V.</p><p>The parameters of all confi gurable inputs and outputs are set in the&nbsp;iNELS Designer &amp; Manager configuration software environment, which&nbsp;is designed for Windows 7, 8 and 10 operating systems.</p><p>RC3-610M/DALI in 6-MODULE version is designed for mounting into&nbsp;a switchboard on DIN rail EN60715</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764327600000, '[]', 'RC3-610M/DALI', 'Room controller with DALI dimmer', '[{"image":{"uploadId":489,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184663', '8466 standard', 17, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/rc3-610m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rc3-610m_a4_en.pdf', '', '', '', 1764331596237, 1764331720810, '/rc3-610mdali                                                                                                                                                    rc3-610m/dali                                                                                                                                                    <p>the rc3-610m/dali is an i/o actuator equipped with 6 binary inputs, of&nbsp;which 2 can be confi gured as temperature inputs and 8 independent&nbsp;relays with switching potential-free and potential contacts. it also&nbsp;includes two analog outputs 0(1)-10 v with a load capacity of up to 10 ma.</p><p>binary inputs rc3-610m/dali are used for connecting up to 6 devices&nbsp;with a non-decimal contact (such as switches, switches, buttons of other&nbsp;designs, ezs and eps detectors and others).</p><p>temperature inputs support the connection of tc/tz temperature&nbsp;sensors in a 2-wire connection for temprature sensing needs.</p><p>the actuator is designed for switching up to eight different appliances&nbsp;and loads by relay output (potential-free contact).</p><p>the maximum load capacity of the relay contacts is 10 a/2500 va/&nbsp;ac1. each of the output contacts is individually controllable. relays&nbsp;are divided into four pairs, where each pair switches on its common&nbsp;potential.</p><p>the dali system bus allows control of up to 16 independent dali (digital&nbsp;addressable lighting interface) ballast addresses for fluorescent, led, and other luminaires.</p><p>analog outputs are considered for use with thermoregulation heads,&nbsp;air-conditioning ventilation flaps, various other dimmers or other&nbsp;devices with an analog control voltage of 0-10 v or 1-10 v.</p><p>the parameters of all confi gurable inputs and outputs are set in the&nbsp;inels designer &amp; manager configuration software environment, which&nbsp;is designed for windows 7, 8 and 10 operating systems.</p><p>rc3-610m/dali in 6-module version is designed for mounting into&nbsp;a switchboard on din rail en60715</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/rc3-610m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rc3-610m_dali.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/rc3-610m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rc3-610m_dali.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (76, 'en', 'FnboKK2EYNJ--G5Bz55iI', '/ins8sq', true, 's5FU8yA9a6_guXdgGM5OB', 'INS8SQ', true, '<p>The INS8SQ offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display, and support for various interfaces and sensors. Its temperature and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating environments.</p><p>Featuring IPS 8“ 1280 x 800 resolution 350 cd/m2 luminance with a 5-point capacitive touchscreen.</p><p>The device runs on OS Android 6.0 operating system with A64 Quad-Core 1.3 GHz/1GB DDR3 Ram / 8GB Nand flash supporting up to 1000 BMS points.</p><p>INS8SQ touch panel designed to control iNELS with Android OS via iNELS applications.</p><p>Integrated speakers and microphones are primarily designed for intercom operation</p><p>Integrated with essential sensors, the device includes an Ambient illuminance measurement sensor, humidity sensor, and temperature sensor, enabling efficient environmental monitoring.</p><p>The INS8SQ comes with a standard LAN RJ45 10/100Mbps interface, ensuring easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>The INS8SQ offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity and compatibility. These include iNELS, RS485, Modbus, VRF, and Zigbee 3.0</p><p>The INS8SQ operates within a working temperature range of -10°C to +60°C.</p><p>The device can be powered by either 24VDC, and it also supports Power over Ethernet (POE IEEE 802.3af), providing flexibility in power options max 30W.</p><p>Configuration, programming, and update applications over the Skythings platform.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1764586800000, '[]', 'INS8SQ', '8” touch control panel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":496,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', 'INS8SQ.B', 6, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1764595093953, 1764595093953, '/ins8sq                                                                                                                                                          ins8sq                                                                                                                                                           <p>the ins8sq offers a feature-rich and versatile solution for control and monitoring applications, with its powerful hardware, user-friendly display, and support for various interfaces and sensors. its temperature and humidity tolerance make it a reliable choice in different operating environments.</p><p>featuring ips 8“ 1280 x 800 resolution 350 cd/m2 luminance with a 5-point capacitive touchscreen.</p><p>the device runs on os android 6.0 operating system with a64 quad-core 1.3 ghz/1gb ddr3 ram / 8gb nand flash supporting up to 1000 bms points.</p><p>ins8sq touch panel designed to control inels with android os via inels applications.</p><p>integrated speakers and microphones are primarily designed for intercom operation</p><p>integrated with essential sensors, the device includes an ambient illuminance measurement sensor, humidity sensor, and temperature sensor, enabling efficient environmental monitoring.</p><p>the ins8sq comes with a standard lan rj45 10/100mbps interface, ensuring easy network connectivity for data transfer and communication.</p><p>the ins8sq offers a variety of optional interfaces for enhanced connectivity and compatibility. these include inels, rs485, modbus, vrf, and zigbee 3.0</p><p>the ins8sq operates within a working temperature range of -10°c to +60°c.</p><p>the device can be powered by either 24vdc, and it also supports power over ethernet (poe ieee 802.3af), providing flexibility in power options max 30w.</p><p>configuration, programming, and update applications over the skythings platform.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/inels-iii/ins8sq/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_ins8sq.pdf', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (77, 'en', 'Os_rC-NgfAE8sWo81UX-Z', '/rfowb-20', true, 'puxjktrDI94tJh-GxFORq', 'RFOWB-20', true, '<p><span>The wireless push-button controller with IP65 protection is used to&nbsp;</span>control iNELS RF components and protect them from the outdoor environment.</p><p>2 buttons allow (independently of each other) control of an unlimited number of components (actuators).</p><p>The controller is suitable for control from the pool, garden, terrace, and pergola. It can be used as an uncovered bell button.</p><p>Fastening with screws or double-sided tape.</p><p>Battery power supply (3 V CR 2032 battery - included in the supply) with a battery life of around 5 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p><strong>TECHNICAL PARAMETERS</strong></p><p>Number of channels: 2</p><p>Power supply:&nbsp;3 V battery CR 2032</p><p>Design:&nbsp;IP65</p><p>Colour:&nbsp;white</p><p>Dimensions:&nbsp;64 x 74 x 44 mm</p><p>Protocol:&nbsp;RFIO2</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768388400000, '[]', 'RFOWB-20', 'Outdoor controller - 2 buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":694,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188181471', '8147', 19, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfowb-20/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfowb-20.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFOWB-20/3D/3d.html', '', 1768395289563, 1768395289563, '/rfowb-20                                                                                                                                                        rfowb-20                                                                                                                                                         <p><span>the wireless push-button controller with ip65 protection is used to&nbsp;</span>control inels rf components and protect them from the outdoor environment.</p><p>2 buttons allow (independently of each other) control of an unlimited number of components (actuators).</p><p>the controller is suitable for control from the pool, garden, terrace, and pergola. it can be used as an uncovered bell button.</p><p>fastening with screws or double-sided tape.</p><p>battery power supply (3 v cr 2032 battery - included in the supply) with a battery life of around 5 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p><strong>technical parameters</strong></p><p>number of channels: 2</p><p>power supply:&nbsp;3 v battery cr 2032</p><p>design:&nbsp;ip65</p><p>colour:&nbsp;white</p><p>dimensions:&nbsp;64 x 74 x 44 mm</p><p>protocol:&nbsp;rfio2</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfowb-20/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfowb-20.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfowb-20/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfowb-20.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (78, 'en', 'gcye6q7ZQXA8sbn9Wj0Fr', '/rfwb-20g', true, 'wrOGlXiD8vj1zdb00WdRW', 'RFWB-20/G', true, '<p>On-wall button controller is used to control switches and dimmers (lights, gates, garage doors, blinds, etc.).</p><p><strong>Two buttons enable control of two units independently.</strong></p><p>The flat design with level base makes it ideal for fast installation on any surface (fixation with adhesive or screws in the installation box).</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming, time switching OFF/ON, blinds up/down).</p><p>Sending a command is indicated by a red LED.</p><p>In LOGUS90 switch frame design (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>Battery power supply (3 V CR 2032 battery - included in the supply)with a battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol component RFIO2 that support this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>RFWB enables communication (RFIO2) and can thus communicate with the CU3-02M.</p><p><strong>RFWB-20/G - bílá varianta, RFWB-20/GB - černá varianta</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>TECHNICAL PARAMETERS</strong></p><p>Number of channels: 2</p><p>Power supply:&nbsp;3 V battery CR 2032&nbsp;</p><p>Design:&nbsp;LOGUS90</p><p>Colour:&nbsp;85 x 85 x 16 mm</p><p>Protocol:&nbsp;RFIO2</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768388400000, '[]', 'RFWB-20/G', 'On-wall button controller - 2 buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":693,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188140379', '8136', 19, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-20_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfwb.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFWB-20_G/share_dokumentace/AKTUAL/3D/3d.html', '', 1768395719435, 1768395719435, '/rfwb-20g                                                                                                                                                        rfwb-20/g                                                                                                                                                        <p>on-wall button controller is used to control switches and dimmers (lights, gates, garage doors, blinds, etc.).</p><p><strong>two buttons enable control of two units independently.</strong></p><p>the flat design with level base makes it ideal for fast installation on any surface (fixation with adhesive or screws in the installation box).</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming, time switching off/on, blinds up/down).</p><p>sending a command is indicated by a red led.</p><p>in logus90 switch frame design (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control units of inels rf control.</p><p>battery power supply (3 v cr 2032 battery - included in the supply)with a battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol component rfio2 that support this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>rfwb enables communication (rfio2) and can thus communicate with the cu3-02m.</p><p><strong>rfwb-20/g - bílá varianta, rfwb-20/gb - černá varianta</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>technical parameters</strong></p><p>number of channels: 2</p><p>power supply:&nbsp;3 v battery cr 2032&nbsp;</p><p>design:&nbsp;logus90</p><p>colour:&nbsp;85 x 85 x 16 mm</p><p>protocol:&nbsp;rfio2</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-20_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfwb-20g_40g_20gb_40gb.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-20_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfwb-20g.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (98, 'en', '1A_7omZWi9IYGnN93wLr5', '/rf-key-60w', true, 'TBEZpc6LUOh_4L0ZGs2Nr', 'RF KEY-60/W', true, '<p>Key fob - sized remote control, available in black and white.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF/ON, blinds up/down).</p><p><strong>RF KEY-60</strong>: six buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>Battery power supply (3 V CR 2032 battery - included in the supply)&nbsp;with battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RF KEY-60/W', 'Key fob - 6 buttons - color WHITE', '[{"image":{"uploadId":753,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188180764', '8076', 23, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rf_key-40_60_a4_en-cz.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RF_KEY-60/share_dokumentace/AKTUAL/3D/3d.html', '', 1768998208902, 1768998208902, '/rf-key-60w                                                                                                                                                      rf key-60/w                                                                                                                                                      <p>key fob - sized remote control, available in black and white.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off/on, blinds up/down).</p><p><strong>rf key-60</strong>: six buttons enable control of four units independently.</p><p>battery power supply (3 v cr 2032 battery - included in the supply)&nbsp;with battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rf_key.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rf_key-60/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfkey-60.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (122, 'en', 'MStwexAQP_mnNsPyxuB9Y', '/rftc-10g', true, 'nuGBJ2JIv9z9kssFVdmR8', 'RFTC-10/G', true, '<p>RFTC-10/G is used for temperature measurement (in the range of 0 to 55 ° C) and correction of the pre-set temperature in RF Touch or eLANRF system devices in the range of ± 5° C. The temperature correction is valid until the next program change in the given system device.</p><p>The backlit LCD display displays the current and set temperature, status (ON/OFF), battery status, etc.</p><p>Range up to 100 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.&nbsp;</p><p>Color combination of heating unit in design of frames LOGUS90 (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFTC-10/G', 'System temperature controller', '[{"image":{"uploadId":784,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188145329', 'RFTC-10/G/BR/BR standard', 29, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-10_g/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rftc-10g.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFTC-10_G/3D/3d.html', '', 1769161284595, 1769161284595, '/rftc-10g                                                                                                                                                        rftc-10/g                                                                                                                                                        <p>rftc-10/g is used for temperature measurement (in the range of 0 to 55 ° c) and correction of the pre-set temperature in rf touch or elanrf system devices in the range of ± 5° c. the temperature correction is valid until the next program change in the given system device.</p><p>the backlit lcd display displays the current and set temperature, status (on/off), battery status, etc.</p><p>range up to 100 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.&nbsp;</p><p>color combination of heating unit in design of frames logus90 (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-10_g/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rftc-10g.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-10_g/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rftc-10g.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (131, 'en', 'ku1ekwyvie1ThDAP9iLyg', '/', true, 'hpychq9ESKbwTHF15lpHz', 'RFATV-2', true, '<p>The thermostatic radiator valve is used to regulate the temperature in the room.&nbsp;It is installed directly on the radiator valve, where it immediately measures&nbsp;the temperature in the room with the help of an internal temperature sensor&nbsp;and regulates the radiator valve with the built-in motor. The valve can also be&nbsp;installed on valves in distribution boards when a temperature sensor from&nbsp;another element of the iNELS Wireless system will be used to measure the&nbsp;temperature in the room.</p><p>To use the functions of the valve, it is necessary to connect it to the eLAN-RF&nbsp;or RF Touch system units, which will ensure heating and control of the valve&nbsp;from the app (Android, iOS, Samsung Smart TV) and the system unit with&nbsp;manual or automatic temperature modes.</p><p>The valve measures the temperature in the range of 0...50°C and receives control&nbsp;instructions from the system units at a regular interval of every 6 minutes.</p><p>The valve supports functions of anti-freeze mode, open window detection,&nbsp;communication failure with the system unit and valve stiffening, which are&nbsp;described in detail below.</p><p>The valve supports hysteresis and offsets functions that can be set in the&nbsp;application or system unit.</p><p>Battery power 2x AA 1.5 V batteries (included in the package)</p><p>Communication range with system unit up to 200m (in open space), to increase&nbsp;the range or change the direction of the signal, it is possible to use the</p><p>RFRP-20N repeater or other units of the system with support for the repeater&nbsp;function.</p><p>In the base, the head is compatible with M30x1,5 valves, adapters that are&nbsp;not included in the package can be used for other valves.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFATV-2', 'Thermostatic radiator valve', '[{"image":{"uploadId":798,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188182591', '8259', 30, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfatv-2/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfatv-2_a4.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFATV-2/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171313808, 1769171313808, '/                                                                                                                                                                rfatv-2                                                                                                                                                          <p>the thermostatic radiator valve is used to regulate the temperature in the room.&nbsp;it is installed directly on the radiator valve, where it immediately measures&nbsp;the temperature in the room with the help of an internal temperature sensor&nbsp;and regulates the radiator valve with the built-in motor. the valve can also be&nbsp;installed on valves in distribution boards when a temperature sensor from&nbsp;another element of the inels wireless system will be used to measure the&nbsp;temperature in the room.</p><p>to use the functions of the valve, it is necessary to connect it to the elan-rf&nbsp;or rf touch system units, which will ensure heating and control of the valve&nbsp;from the app (android, ios, samsung smart tv) and the system unit with&nbsp;manual or automatic temperature modes.</p><p>the valve measures the temperature in the range of 0...50°c and receives control&nbsp;instructions from the system units at a regular interval of every 6 minutes.</p><p>the valve supports functions of anti-freeze mode, open window detection,&nbsp;communication failure with the system unit and valve stiffening, which are&nbsp;described in detail below.</p><p>the valve supports hysteresis and offsets functions that can be set in the&nbsp;application or system unit.</p><p>battery power 2x aa 1.5 v batteries (included in the package)</p><p>communication range with system unit up to 200m (in open space), to increase&nbsp;the range or change the direction of the signal, it is possible to use the</p><p>rfrp-20n repeater or other units of the system with support for the repeater&nbsp;function.</p><p>in the base, the head is compatible with m30x1,5 valves, adapters that are&nbsp;not included in the package can be used for other valves.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfatv-2/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfatv-2.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfatv-2/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfatv-2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (80, 'en', 'tbCv9sV2g_fZoXLukEMG-', '/rfgb-20', true, 'Ik4oOKrH5xiyIwOoJAWJI', 'RFGB-20', true, '<p>The glass touch controller is a designed RF (wireless) Control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>Only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>RFGB-20:</strong> 2 capacitive buttons allow to control of 2 devices.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF / ON, blinds up/down). Sending a command is indicated by a red LED.</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>The rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>Battery power supply (2x 3 V/CR2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.</p><p><strong>TECHNICAL SUPPORT</strong></p><p>Number of channels: 2</p><p>Power supply:&nbsp;2x 3 V batteries CR 2032</p><p>Design:&nbsp;glass - sharp</p><p>Color: W - white, B - black</p><p>Dimensions:&nbsp;94 x 94 x 8 mm</p><p>Protocol:&nbsp;RFIO2</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768388400000, '[]', 'RFGB-20', 'Glass touch controller - 2 buttons, SHARP', '[{"image":{"uploadId":691,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188176798', '7679', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-20/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfgb-20,40,220,240.pdf', '', '', '', 1768399737185, 1768399737185, '/rfgb-20                                                                                                                                                         rfgb-20                                                                                                                                                          <p>the glass touch controller is a designed rf (wireless) control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>rfgb-20:</strong> 2 capacitive buttons allow to control of 2 devices.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off / on, blinds up/down). sending a command is indicated by a red led.</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of inels rf control.</p><p>the rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>battery power supply (2x 3 v/cr2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.</p><p><strong>technical support</strong></p><p>number of channels: 2</p><p>power supply:&nbsp;2x 3 v batteries cr 2032</p><p>design:&nbsp;glass - sharp</p><p>color: w - white, b - black</p><p>dimensions:&nbsp;94 x 94 x 8 mm</p><p>protocol:&nbsp;rfio2</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-20/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfgb-20-w,%20rfgb-20-b,%20rfgb-40-w,%20rfgb-40-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-20/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfgb-20.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (79, 'en', 'GK-Hx725QfqAABz_Mfq9q', '/rfwb-40g', true, 'OlHHOqIECaWeGC6Ze2CFv', 'RFWB-40/G', true, '<p>On-wall button controller is used to control switches and dimmers (lights, gates, garage doors, blinds, etc.).</p><p><strong>Four buttons enable control of four units independently.</strong></p><p>The flat design with level base makes it ideal for fast installation on any surface (fixation with adhesive or screws in the installation box).</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming, time switching OFF/ON, blinds up/down).</p><p>Sending a command is indicated by a red LED.</p><p>In LOGUS90 switch frame design (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>Battery power supply (3 V CR 2032 battery - included in the supply)with a battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol component RFIO2 that support this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>RFWB enables communication (RFIO2) and can thus communicate with the CU3-02M.</p><p><strong>RFWB-20/G - bílá varianta, RFWB-20/GB - černá varianta</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>TECHNICAL PARAMETERS</strong></p><p>Number of channels: 4</p><p>Power supply:&nbsp;3 V battery CR 2032&nbsp;</p><p>Design:&nbsp;LOGUS90</p><p>Colour:&nbsp;85 x 85 x 16 mm</p><p>Protocol:&nbsp;RFIO2</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768388400000, '[]', 'RFWB-40/G', 'On-wall button controller - 4 buttons', '[{"image":{"uploadId":695,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188140607', '8098', 19, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-20_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfwb.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFWB-40_G/share_dokumentace/AKTUAL/3D/3d.html', '', 1768397299039, 1768397494076, '/rfwb-40g                                                                                                                                                        rfwb-40/g                                                                                                                                                        <p>on-wall button controller is used to control switches and dimmers (lights, gates, garage doors, blinds, etc.).</p><p><strong>four buttons enable control of four units independently.</strong></p><p>the flat design with level base makes it ideal for fast installation on any surface (fixation with adhesive or screws in the installation box).</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming, time switching off/on, blinds up/down).</p><p>sending a command is indicated by a red led.</p><p>in logus90 switch frame design (plastic, glass, wood, metal, stone).</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control units of inels rf control.</p><p>battery power supply (3 v cr 2032 battery - included in the supply)with a battery life of around 5 years based on frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol component rfio2 that support this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>rfwb enables communication (rfio2) and can thus communicate with the cu3-02m.</p><p><strong>rfwb-20/g - bílá varianta, rfwb-20/gb - černá varianta</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>technical parameters</strong></p><p>number of channels: 4</p><p>power supply:&nbsp;3 v battery cr 2032&nbsp;</p><p>design:&nbsp;logus90</p><p>colour:&nbsp;85 x 85 x 16 mm</p><p>protocol:&nbsp;rfio2</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-20_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfwb-20g_40g_20gb_40gb.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfwb-40_g/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfwb-40g.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (99, 'en', 'C7us7I0ROPvZp7cb_BqP2', '/rfsai-61bpf-sl', true, '8YLon1toCNREmEYp76fma', 'RFSAI-61BPF-SL', true, '<p><strong>Switch unit with input for external button, 1 channel</strong></p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFSAI-61BPF-SL', 'Switch unit with input for external button, 1 channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":762,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189101', '8910', 26, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsai-61bpf-sl/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsai-xxb-sl_a4_rev1_en-cz_.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSAI-61BPF-SL/3D/3d.html', '', 1768998618308, 1768998618308, '/rfsai-61bpf-sl                                                                                                                                                  rfsai-61bpf-sl                                                                                                                                                   <p><strong>switch unit with input for external button, 1 channel</strong></p>                                                                                    public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsai-61bpf-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsai-61b-sl,%20rfsai-62b-sl,%20rfsai-11b-sl,%20rfsai-61bpf-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsai-61bpf-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsai-61bpf-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (81, 'en', 'HFi9yWHRRMbv1t1pBwRdN', '/rfgb-40', true, 'wtYocLbSKS-D52IgEB45p', 'RFGB-40', true, '<p>The glass touch controller is a designed RF (wireless) Control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>Only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>RFGB-40:</strong> 4 capacitive buttons allow to control of 4 devices.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF / ON, blinds up/down). Sending a command is indicated by a red LED.</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>The rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>Battery power supply (2x 3 V/CR2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768820400000, '[]', 'RFGB-40', 'Glass touch controller - 4 buttons, SHARP', '[{"image":{"uploadId":692,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188176811', '7681', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfgb-20,40,220,240.pdf', '', '', '', 1768827971368, 1768828023262, '/rfgb-40                                                                                                                                                         rfgb-40                                                                                                                                                          <p>the glass touch controller is a designed rf (wireless) control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>rfgb-40:</strong> 4 capacitive buttons allow to control of 4 devices.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off / on, blinds up/down). sending a command is indicated by a red led.</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of inels rf control.</p><p>the rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>battery power supply (2x 3 v/cr2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfgb-20-w,%20rfgb-20-b,%20rfgb-40-w,%20rfgb-40-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-40/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfgb-40.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (106, 'en', 'p0MebmeB6CkT8np8Y65iB', '/rfsa-66mi', true, 'h8za85wmMOTSEW_Dro_S5', 'RFSA-66MI', true, '<p>The switching unit with an integrated antenna with 6 output channels 8 A is used&nbsp;for independent control of up to 6 appliances, sockets, or lights.</p><p>The 3-MODULE design of the unit into a switchboard.</p><p>Each of the channels may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>It is suitable for placement in cabinets with plastic doors.&nbsp;</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay, and time function of a delayed start or return with a time setting range of 2 s - 60 min</p><p>The programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>Memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFSA-66MI', 'Switching units, 6-channels', '[{"image":{"uploadId":768,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188181556', '8155', 26, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-66mi/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsa-6xm_mi.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSA-66MI/3D/3d.html', '', 1769002004536, 1769002004536, '/rfsa-66mi                                                                                                                                                       rfsa-66mi                                                                                                                                                        <p>the switching unit with an integrated antenna with 6 output channels 8 a is used&nbsp;for independent control of up to 6 appliances, sockets, or lights.</p><p>the 3-module design of the unit into a switchboard.</p><p>each of the channels may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>it is suitable for placement in cabinets with plastic doors.&nbsp;</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay, and time function of a delayed start or return with a time setting range of 2 s - 60 min</p><p>the programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-66mi/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsa-66mx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-66mi/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-66mi_110-230.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-66mi/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-66mi_24v.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (132, 'en', 'VigtrMB7DJgyhQpev2gQ1', '/rfim-40b230-sl', true, 'ZBySyiqpEKltlFG_sdSxR', 'RFIM-40B/230-SL', true, '<p>RFIM-40B / 230-SL: the contact converter changes the button / switch&nbsp;with local mains supply to wireless.</p><p>4 inputs allow controlling 4 devices independently</p><p>mains supply, the inputs respond to the supply of mains supply</p><p>It can be used to transmit contact closing information (detector, buttons,&nbsp;technology, logic output).</p><p>When the button is pressed, it sends the set command (ON / OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time off / on, pull/pull).</p><p>Ability to set scenes where you control multiple iNELS RF Control components&nbsp;with a single press.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the&nbsp;controller and the component, use the RFRP-20 signal repeater or elements&nbsp;with the RFIO2 protocol that support this function.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional RFIO protocol.</p><p>The BOX version offers to mount directly in the installation box under&nbsp;the button/switch.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFIM-40B/230-SL', 'Input contact converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":799,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184076', '8407', 33, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_230-sl/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfim-40b-sl.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFIM-40B_230-SL/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171497366, 1769171497366, '/rfim-40b230-sl                                                                                                                                                  rfim-40b/230-sl                                                                                                                                                  <p>rfim-40b / 230-sl: the contact converter changes the button / switch&nbsp;with local mains supply to wireless.</p><p>4 inputs allow controlling 4 devices independently</p><p>mains supply, the inputs respond to the supply of mains supply</p><p>it can be used to transmit contact closing information (detector, buttons,&nbsp;technology, logic output).</p><p>when the button is pressed, it sends the set command (on / off, dimming,&nbsp;time off / on, pull/pull).</p><p>ability to set scenes where you control multiple inels rf control components&nbsp;with a single press.</p><p>range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the&nbsp;controller and the component, use the rfrp-20 signal repeater or elements&nbsp;with the rfio2 protocol that support this function.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional rfio protocol.</p><p>the box version offers to mount directly in the installation box under&nbsp;the button/switch.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_230-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfim-40b-bp-sl_rfim-40b-230-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_230-sl/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfim-40b-230-sl.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (88, 'en', 'SU8HCFu6mIpfsQS-eDDLD', '/rfsw-242', true, '-d102EyV4jyUVaAhM74LV', 'RFSW-242', true, '<p>The glass design controller with two output relays is used to control appliances and lights.</p><p>The touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control the output relay as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless, or system components.</p><p>6 functions – button, impulse relay, and time function of a delayed start or return with a time setting of 2 s - 60 min. Any function can be assigned to each output relay.</p><p>Possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>Each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels (1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768906800000, '[]', 'RFSW-242', 'Glass touch controller with output relays, round', '[{"image":{"uploadId":700,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188188920', '8892', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-242/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsw-xx2_en-cz.pdf', '', '', '', 1768911772075, 1768911772075, '/rfsw-242                                                                                                                                                        rfsw-242                                                                                                                                                         <p>the glass design controller with two output relays is used to control appliances and lights.</p><p>the touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control the output relay as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless, or system components.</p><p>6 functions – button, impulse relay, and time function of a delayed start or return with a time setting of 2 s - 60 min. any function can be assigned to each output relay.</p><p>possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels (1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-242/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsw-xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-242/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsw-xx_230v_v2.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-242/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsw-xx_24v_v2.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (103, 'en', 'h9f9NWgze50j3XoPM0AaV', '/rfsa-61b230v', true, 'h3a8YcLUMIDga6ZDo4RlL', 'RFSA-61B/230V', true, '<p>The switching unit with 1 output channel 16 A is used to control appliances, and lights (easy to integrate it to control garage doors or gates).</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS RF Control, or system components.</p><p>RFSA-61B: multifunction design – button, impulse relay, and time&nbsp;function of delayed ON or OFF with time setting of 2 s – 60 min.</p><p>The switching unit may be controlled by up to 25-channels.</p><p>The programming button on the unit is also used for manual control&nbsp;of the output.</p><p>Memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that support this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>The BOX design lets you mount it right in an installation box, a ceiling, or a controlled appliance cover.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFSA-61B/230V', 'Switch unit, 1 channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":758,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188136242', '4995', 26, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsa-x1b.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSA-61B/3D/3d.html', '', 1768999135303, 1769002044780, '/rfsa-61b230v                                                                                                                                                    rfsa-61b/230v                                                                                                                                                    <p>the switching unit with 1 output channel 16 a is used to control appliances, and lights (easy to integrate it to control garage doors or gates).</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels rf control, or system components.</p><p>rfsa-61b: multifunction design – button, impulse relay, and time&nbsp;function of delayed on or off with time setting of 2 s – 60 min.</p><p>the switching unit may be controlled by up to 25-channels.</p><p>the programming button on the unit is also used for manual control&nbsp;of the output.</p><p>memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that support this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>the box design lets you mount it right in an installation box, a ceiling, or a controlled appliance cover.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsa-61b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-61b_rfsa-11b_230v.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (107, 'en', 'vK7SoFAxLEW9BYzhdcBAu', '/rfsa-61m', true, 'eE69aBCYKGCkJyRY_ptpp', 'RFSA-61M', true, '<p>The switching unit with 1 output channel 16 A is used for controlling appliances, sockets or lights.<br>- the one-module design of the unit into a switchboard.<br>- the switching unit may be controlled by up to 25 channels.<br>- the package includes an internal antenna AN-I, in case of locating the element in a metal switchboard, you can use the external antenna AN-E for better signal reception</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay and time function of delayed start or return with time setting range of 2 s - 60 min.</p><p>The programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>Memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFSA-61M', 'Switch unit, 1 channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":765,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188137003', '7721', 26, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsa-6xm_mi.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSA-61M/3D/3d.html', '', 1769002118238, 1769002118238, '/rfsa-61m                                                                                                                                                        rfsa-61m                                                                                                                                                         <p>the switching unit with 1 output channel 16 a is used for controlling appliances, sockets or lights.<br>- the one-module design of the unit into a switchboard.<br>- the switching unit may be controlled by up to 25 channels.<br>- the package includes an internal antenna an-i, in case of locating the element in a metal switchboard, you can use the external antenna an-e for better signal reception</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay and time function of delayed start or return with time setting range of 2 s - 60 min.</p><p>the programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsa-61mx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-61m_230v.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-61m_110-230.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (118, 'en', '6eitjD1xhWdZ8SiMacl7D', '/rftc-3', true, 'b23BR5UeCFoD017RuVgEJ', 'RFTC-3', true, '<p>Designed to control 2 and 4 pipe fan coils, chillers</p><p>3x relays for fan speed (LOW, MEDIUM, High), 2x relays for heating/cooling&nbsp;mode</p><p>2x analog outputs 0-10V for proportional control of valves</p><p>2x inputs for connecting wired detectors (magnet doors/windows); of&nbsp;which 1 input can</p><p>Built-in digital temperature and humidity sensor</p><p>Proximity sensor to activate display backlight/buttons</p><p>VA/TN LCD display, 8 touch backlit buttons</p><p>Screwless angle clamps for easy wire connection</p><p>WiFi for thermostat setup (via web browser) and connection to iNELS Cloud, iNELS APP and MRS via MQTT protocol</p><p>Modbus RTU for external HVAC devices and higher-level systems</p><p>Power supply: AC 110 – 230V AC</p><p>Black or white finish</p><p>Box for mounting on EU/BS installation boxes</p><p>Possibility of custom tuning and design modifications (button functions,&nbsp;icon options, logos): icons.inels.com</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFTC-3', 'Glass touch thermostat for fancoils', '[{"image":{"uploadId":782,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188189156', '8915', 29, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-3/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rftc-3_9q_a4_76x52.pdf', 'https://youtu.be/y7lsgJ719VU', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFTC-3/3D/3d.html', '', 1769160376462, 1769160376462, '/rftc-3                                                                                                                                                          rftc-3                                                                                                                                                           <p>designed to control 2 and 4 pipe fan coils, chillers</p><p>3x relays for fan speed (low, medium, high), 2x relays for heating/cooling&nbsp;mode</p><p>2x analog outputs 0-10v for proportional control of valves</p><p>2x inputs for connecting wired detectors (magnet doors/windows); of&nbsp;which 1 input can</p><p>built-in digital temperature and humidity sensor</p><p>proximity sensor to activate display backlight/buttons</p><p>va/tn lcd display, 8 touch backlit buttons</p><p>screwless angle clamps for easy wire connection</p><p>wifi for thermostat setup (via web browser) and connection to inels cloud, inels app and mrs via mqtt protocol</p><p>modbus rtu for external hvac devices and higher-level systems</p><p>power supply: ac 110 – 230v ac</p><p>black or white finish</p><p>box for mounting on eu/bs installation boxes</p><p>possibility of custom tuning and design modifications (button functions,&nbsp;icon options, logos): icons.inels.com</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-3/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rftc-3.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rftc-3/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rftc-3.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (90, 'en', 'GNjuqskplWqScOa6XRLW-', '/rfmb-22', true, '-WE1dqMJczhprpHXvPfVn', 'RFMB-22', true, '<p>The metall front plate design controller with two output relays.</p><p>The 2 buttons controls on the built-in allow you to directly&nbsp;control the built-in output relays as well as, other iNELS Wireless units.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>Possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>Each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>Power supply AC 230V is galvanically isolated from the output relay&nbsp;contacts.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768906800000, '[]', 'RFMB-22', 'Wireless metal pushbutton controller with switching relays', '[{"image":{"uploadId":751,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '', '', 21, '[]', 0, 'EUR', '', '', '', '', 1768913588873, 1768913588873, '/rfmb-22                                                                                                                                                         rfmb-22                                                                                                                                                          <p>the metall front plate design controller with two output relays.</p><p>the 2 buttons controls on the built-in allow you to directly&nbsp;control the built-in output relays as well as, other inels wireless units.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>possibility to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>power supply ac 230v is galvanically isolated from the output relay&nbsp;contacts.</p> public visible', '', '[]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (82, 'en', 'uNzu0eix0f9uyUN9rBpsd', '/rfgb-220', true, 'fAGMNdsq0B_5RuB-QDDIM', 'RFGB-220', true, '<p>The glass touch controller is a designed RF (wireless) Control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>Only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>RFGB-220:</strong> 2 capacitive buttons allow to control of 2 devices.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF / ON, blinds up/down). Sending a command is indicated&nbsp;by a red LED.</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>The rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>Battery power supply (2x 3 V/CR2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768820400000, '[]', 'RFGB-220', 'Glass touch controller - 2 buttons, ROUND', '[{"image":{"uploadId":689,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188176842', '7684', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-220/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfgb-20,40,220,240.pdf', '', '', '', 1768828170871, 1768828357649, '/rfgb-220                                                                                                                                                        rfgb-220                                                                                                                                                         <p>the glass touch controller is a designed rf (wireless) control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>rfgb-220:</strong> 2 capacitive buttons allow to control of 2 devices.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off / on, blinds up/down). sending a command is indicated&nbsp;by a red led.</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of inels rf control.</p><p>the rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>battery power supply (2x 3 v/cr2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-220/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfgb-220-w,%20rfgb-220-b,%20rfgb-240-w,%20rfgb-240-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-220/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_rfgb-220_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (108, 'en', '8WJ_b71eVIEy-h1nRqtcg', '/rfsa-61mi', true, 'elMKh2aJl6KvvnPrcAZA-', 'RFSA-61MI', true, '<p>RFSA-61MI: same design and function as RFSA-61M, but with integrated antenna. It is suitable for placement in cabinets with plastic doors.</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay and time function of delayed start or return with time setting range of 2 s - 60 min.</p><p>The programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>Memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768993200000, '[]', 'RFSA-61MI', 'Switch unit with integrated antenna, 1 channel', '[{"image":{"uploadId":766,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188181549', '8154', 26, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61mi/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsa-6xm_mi.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSA-61MI/3D/3d.html', '', 1769002176978, 1769002176978, '/rfsa-61mi                                                                                                                                                       rfsa-61mi                                                                                                                                                        <p>rfsa-61mi: same design and function as rfsa-61m, but with integrated antenna. it is suitable for placement in cabinets with plastic doors.</p><p>6 function: button, impulse relay and time function of delayed start or return with time setting range of 2 s - 60 min.</p><p>the programming button on the unit is also used for manual control of the output.</p><p>memory status can be pre-set in the event of a power failure.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61mi/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsa-61mx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsa-61mi/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsa-61mi_110-230.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (83, 'en', 'wHPvQYqic1pXWPVE1bWfK', '/rfgb-240', true, '45FY66KYpgr5cemvMEKkw', 'RFGB-240', true, '<p>The glass touch controller is a designed RF (wireless) Control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>Only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>RFGB-240: </strong>4 capacitive buttons allow to control of 4 devices.</p><p>When pressing the button, it sends a set signal (ON/OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time switching OFF / ON, blinds up/down). Sending a command is indicated&nbsp;by a red LED.</p><p>Option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of iNELS RF Control.</p><p>The rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>Battery power supply (2x 3 V/CR2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20 or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768820400000, '[]', 'RFGB-240', 'Glass touch controller - 4 buttons, ROUND', '[{"image":{"uploadId":690,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188176866', '7686', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-240/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfgb-20,40,220,240.pdf', '', '', '', 1768828657431, 1768828657431, '/rfgb-240                                                                                                                                                        rfgb-240                                                                                                                                                         <p>the glass touch controller is a designed rf (wireless) control unit and is&nbsp;available in elegant black and white variants.</p><p>only 8 mm thick.</p><p><strong>rfgb-240: </strong>4 capacitive buttons allow to control of 4 devices.</p><p>when pressing the button, it sends a set signal (on/off, dimming,&nbsp;time switching off / on, blinds up/down). sending a command is indicated&nbsp;by a red led.</p><p>option of setting light scenes, where with a single press, you can control&nbsp;units of inels rf control.</p><p>the rear base allows for being attached to installation using screws, double-sided tape, or keeping the controller on the table.</p><p>battery power supply (2x 3 v/cr2032 - included in the supply) with a battery&nbsp;life of around 2 years based on the frequency of use.</p><p>range up to 200 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20 or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-240/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfgb-220-w,%20rfgb-220-b,%20rfgb-240-w,%20rfgb-240-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfgb-240/share_dokumentace/aktual/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_conformity_rfgb-240_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (84, 'en', 'LHzLqZPreKZ1pBG1VqVqJ', '/rfdw-71', true, 'ldrWZ2r3bOpD5qGhtgOsX', 'RFDW-71', true, '<p>The glass design controller with dimmer and touch buttons is used to&nbsp;control light sources:&nbsp;</p><p>R – classic lamps (resistive load)</p><p>L – halogen lamps with wound transformer (inductive load)</p><p>C – halogen lamps with electronic transformer (capacity load)</p><p>ESL – dimmable energy-efficient fluorescent lamps</p><p>LED – LED light sources (230 V) equipped with LED.</p><p>The touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control&nbsp;the integrated dimmer as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless, or&nbsp;system components for output control from other locations.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s – 30 min.&nbsp;</p><p>When switched off, the set level is stored in the memory, and when&nbsp;switched back on, it returns to the most recently set value.</p><p>Thanks for setting the min. the brightness you will eliminate flashing of&nbsp;the LED and ESL light sources.</p><p>The universal dimmer may be controlled by up to 25 channels.&nbsp;</p><p>Possibility to set the memory status in case of power failure.&nbsp;</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768820400000, '[]', 'RFDW-71', 'Glass touch controller - 4 buttons, SHARP', '[{"image":{"uploadId":698,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188188944', '8894', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-71/share_dokumentace/rfdw-71b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfdw-71_271_en-cz.pdf', '', '', '', 1768828826201, 1768828826201, '/rfdw-71                                                                                                                                                         rfdw-71                                                                                                                                                          <p>the glass design controller with dimmer and touch buttons is used to&nbsp;control light sources:&nbsp;</p><p>r – classic lamps (resistive load)</p><p>l – halogen lamps with wound transformer (inductive load)</p><p>c – halogen lamps with electronic transformer (capacity load)</p><p>esl – dimmable energy-efficient fluorescent lamps</p><p>led – led light sources (230 v) equipped with led.</p><p>the touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control&nbsp;the integrated dimmer as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless, or&nbsp;system components for output control from other locations.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s – 30 min.&nbsp;</p><p>when switched off, the set level is stored in the memory, and when&nbsp;switched back on, it returns to the most recently set value.</p><p>thanks for setting the min. the brightness you will eliminate flashing of&nbsp;the led and esl light sources.</p><p>the universal dimmer may be controlled by up to 25 channels.&nbsp;</p><p>possibility to set the memory status in case of power failure.&nbsp;</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-71/share_dokumentace/rfdw-71b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfdw-71-w,%20rfdw-71-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-71/share_dokumentace/rfdw-71b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfdw-71.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (133, 'en', 'RGw6_BckJhGD5upGcLzwB', '/rfim-40bbp-sl', true, 'lpEdpGoN_7YSwproz5i8o', 'RFIM-40B/BP-SL', true, '<p>The wireless contact converter changes the wired&nbsp;button / switch to wireless</p><p>4 inputs allow controlling 4 devices independently</p><p>Battery supply (3 V battery CR123A - included in the package) with a lifespan&nbsp;of about 8 years according to the frequency of use</p><p>The contact can be permanently closed</p><p>It can be used to transmit contact closing information (detector, buttons,&nbsp;technology, logic output).</p><p>When the button is pressed, it sends the set command (ON / OFF, dimming,&nbsp;time off / on, pull/pull).</p><p>Ability to set scenes where you control multiple iNELS RF Control components&nbsp;with a single press.</p><p>Range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the&nbsp;controller and the component, use the RFRP-20 signal repeater or elements&nbsp;with the RFIO2 protocol that supports this function.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional RFIO protocol.&nbsp;</p><p>The BOX version offers to mount directly in the installation box under&nbsp;the button/switch.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFIM-40B/BP-SL', 'Input contact converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":800,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188184069', '8406', 33, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_bp-sl/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfim-40b-sl.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFIM-40B_BP-SL/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171773544, 1769171773544, '/rfim-40bbp-sl                                                                                                                                                   rfim-40b/bp-sl                                                                                                                                                   <p>the wireless contact converter changes the wired&nbsp;button / switch to wireless</p><p>4 inputs allow controlling 4 devices independently</p><p>battery supply (3 v battery cr123a - included in the package) with a lifespan&nbsp;of about 8 years according to the frequency of use</p><p>the contact can be permanently closed</p><p>it can be used to transmit contact closing information (detector, buttons,&nbsp;technology, logic output).</p><p>when the button is pressed, it sends the set command (on / off, dimming,&nbsp;time off / on, pull/pull).</p><p>ability to set scenes where you control multiple inels rf control components&nbsp;with a single press.</p><p>range up to 200 m (outdoors), in case of insufficient signal between the&nbsp;controller and the component, use the rfrp-20 signal repeater or elements&nbsp;with the rfio2 protocol that supports this function.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional rfio protocol.&nbsp;</p><p>the box version offers to mount directly in the installation box under&nbsp;the button/switch.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_bp-sl/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfim-40b-bp-sl_rfim-40b-230-sl.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfim-40b_bp-sl/share_dokumentace/en/declaration_of_confirmity_rfim-40b-bp-sl_en.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (85, 'en', 'F5YgQpuk0R17PkpYrf4ZI', '/rfdw-271', true, '73bKHMkKZHyhZjmuQ4pPd', 'RFDW-271', true, '<p>The glass design controller with dimmer and touch buttons is used to&nbsp;control light sources:</p><p>R – classic lamps (resistive load)&nbsp;</p><p>L – halogen lamps with wound transformer (inductive load)</p><p>C – halogen lamps with electronic transformer (capacity load)</p><p>ESL – dimmable energy-efficient fluorescent lamps</p><p>LED – LED light sources (230 V) equipped with LED.</p><p>The touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control&nbsp;the integrated dimmer as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless, or&nbsp;system components for output control from other locations.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s – 30 min.</p><p>When switched off, the set level is stored in the memory, and when&nbsp;switched back on, it returns to the most recently set value.</p><p>Thanks for setting the min. the brightness you will eliminate flashing of&nbsp;the LED and ESL light sources.</p><p>The universal dimmer may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>Possibility to set the memory status in case of power failure.</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N or protocol&nbsp;component RFIO2 that supports this feature.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768820400000, '[]', 'RFDW-271', 'Glass touch controller with dimmer, ROUND', '[{"image":{"uploadId":701,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188188951', '8895', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-271/share_dokumentace/rfdw-271b/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfdw-71_271_en-cz.pdf', '', '', '', 1768828913248, 1768828913248, '/rfdw-271                                                                                                                                                        rfdw-271                                                                                                                                                         <p>the glass design controller with dimmer and touch buttons is used to&nbsp;control light sources:</p><p>r – classic lamps (resistive load)&nbsp;</p><p>l – halogen lamps with wound transformer (inductive load)</p><p>c – halogen lamps with electronic transformer (capacity load)</p><p>esl – dimmable energy-efficient fluorescent lamps</p><p>led – led light sources (230 v) equipped with led.</p><p>the touch buttons on the circuit breaker allow you to directly control&nbsp;the integrated dimmer as well as other components of the installation.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless, or&nbsp;system components for output control from other locations.</p><p>7 light functions – smooth increase or decrease with time setting&nbsp;2 s – 30 min.</p><p>when switched off, the set level is stored in the memory, and when&nbsp;switched back on, it returns to the most recently set value.</p><p>thanks for setting the min. the brightness you will eliminate flashing of&nbsp;the led and esl light sources.</p><p>the universal dimmer may be controlled by up to 25 channels.</p><p>possibility to set the memory status in case of power failure.</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between&nbsp;the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n or protocol&nbsp;component rfio2 that supports this feature.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-271/share_dokumentace/rfdw-271b/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfdw-71-w,%20rfdw-71-b.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfdw-271/share_dokumentace/rfdw-271b/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfdw-271.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (134, 'en', 'jopkxWuzzTOQJbh_gDlZa', '/rfsg-1m', true, 'J6ATLe_Hg8T9TT8zZWaka', 'RFSG-1M', true, '<p>This wireless contact converter is especially appropriate for the wireless transmission of information on switching HDO.</p><p>Thanks to the permanent power supply, it can also be used for partial transmission of information for control of an appliance or device.</p><p>After leading in power to the “S” terminals, it periodically transmits the command switch on in an interval of 2 min. When disconnecting the power supply, immediately switch it off.</p><p>The button TEST on the controller is used to assign to a switching unit.</p><p>The package includes an internal antenna AN-I, in case of locating the converter in a metal switchboard, you can use the external antenna AN-E for better signal reception.</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater RFRP-20N.</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO.</p><p>1-MODULE design of the unit with mounting into the switchboard.</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1769166000000, '[]', 'RFSG-1M', 'Input contact converter', '[{"image":{"uploadId":801,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188142847', '8240', 33, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsg-1m/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsg-1m.pdf', '', 'https://www.elkoep.com/media/import/Elko/RFx/RFSG-1M/3D/3d.html', '', 1769171835697, 1769171835697, '/rfsg-1m                                                                                                                                                         rfsg-1m                                                                                                                                                          <p>this wireless contact converter is especially appropriate for the wireless transmission of information on switching hdo.</p><p>thanks to the permanent power supply, it can also be used for partial transmission of information for control of an appliance or device.</p><p>after leading in power to the “s” terminals, it periodically transmits the command switch on in an interval of 2 min. when disconnecting the power supply, immediately switch it off.</p><p>the button test on the controller is used to assign to a switching unit.</p><p>the package includes an internal antenna an-i, in case of locating the converter in a metal switchboard, you can use the external antenna an-e for better signal reception.</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space), if the signal is insufficient between the controller and unit, use the signal repeater rfrp-20n.</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio.</p><p>1-module design of the unit with mounting into the switchboard.</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsg-1m/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsg-1m.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsg-1m/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsg-1m.pdf"}]');
INSERT INTO products VALUES (87, 'en', 'Kb6G3-b_0XKj08YWnnzGI', '/rfsw-62', true, 'OVzq37zAqSj67ZqT4Fcde', 'RFSW-62', true, '<p>The glass design controller with two output relays is used to control&nbsp;appliances and lights.</p><p>The 6-button touch controls on the circuit breaker allow you to&nbsp;directly control the output relay as well as other components of the&nbsp;installation.</p><p>The backlight intensity (white LED) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>They can be combined with detectors, controllers, iNELS Wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>6 functions – button, impulse relay and time function of a delayed&nbsp;start or return with a time setting of 2 s - 60 min. Any function can be&nbsp;assigned to each output relay.&nbsp;</p><p>It is possible to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>Each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>Range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>Communication frequency with bidirectional protocol RFIO2.</p><p>Available with AC 230V or AC/DC 24V power supply with the option of&nbsp;galvanically isolated relay output contacts from the power supply</p>', true, NULL, '[]', 'product', 1768906800000, '[]', 'RFSW-62', 'Glass touch controller with output relays, 6 buttons, sharp', '[{"image":{"uploadId":699,"alt":""},"alt":""}]', '8595188193269', '9326', 20, '[]', 0, 'EUR', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-62/share_dokumentace/en/manual_rfsw-xx2_en-cz.pdf', '', '', '', 1768911544997, 1768911544997, '/rfsw-62                                                                                                                                                         rfsw-62                                                                                                                                                          <p>the glass design controller with two output relays is used to control&nbsp;appliances and lights.</p><p>the 6-button touch controls on the circuit breaker allow you to&nbsp;directly control the output relay as well as other components of the&nbsp;installation.</p><p>the backlight intensity (white led) of the buttons is automatically&nbsp;adjusted depending on the ambient lighting.</p><p>they can be combined with detectors, controllers, inels wireless or&nbsp;system components.</p><p>6 functions – button, impulse relay and time function of a delayed&nbsp;start or return with a time setting of 2 s - 60 min. any function can be&nbsp;assigned to each output relay.&nbsp;</p><p>it is possible to set the memory of the output state during a power&nbsp;failure and subsequent restoration of the power supply.</p><p>each of the outputs can be controlled by up to 12/12 channels&nbsp;(1 channel represents one button on the controller).</p><p>range up to 160 m (in open space).</p><p>communication frequency with bidirectional protocol rfio2.</p><p>available with ac 230v or ac/dc 24v power supply with the option of&nbsp;galvanically isolated relay output contacts from the power supply</p> public visible', 'https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-62/share_dokumentace/en/datasheet_rfsw-xx.pdf', '[{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-62/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsw-xx_230v_v2.pdf"},{"url":"https://eshop.elkoep.com/documents/rfx/rfsw-62/share_dokumentace/en/ec_declaration_of_conformity_rfsw-xx_24v_v2.pdf"}]');
